            "content": "# Daemon (`factoryd`)\n\n**Active contributors**: factory-sherry, factory-octavian, Alvin Sng, factory-jerry, Nikita Lilichenko, Luke Alvoeiro, Leo Tchourakov\n\n## Purpose\n\n`factoryd` is the background daemon process that acts as the session lifecycle manager for Droid. It runs on the user's local machine (via Electron) or on a remote Cloud Development Environment (CDE) sandbox. Clients — the CLI, web app, and desktop app — connect to it over WebSocket JSON-RPC and drive agent sessions through it.\n\nThe daemon is responsible for:\n\n- Spawning and managing `droid` CLI sub-processes (one per session)\n- Relaying JSON-RPC messages between clients and those sub-processes\n- Managing pseudo-terminal (PTY) sessions for raw terminal access\n- Sending periodic heartbeats to the backend API to signal liveness\n- Running automation due-run polling and recovering interrupted runs\n- Optionally proxying VS Code Server (`code-server`) over HTTP/WebSocket\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/daemon/\n├── src/\n│   ├── index.ts                  # Entry point: CLI argument parsing, auto-update, DaemonCore wiring\n│   ├── environment.ts            # Resolves env vars into typed DaemonEnvironment\n│   ├── constants.ts              # Default host binding\n│   ├── services/\n│   │   └── UpdateService.ts      # Auto-update wrapper around @factory/updater\n│   └── telemetry/\n│       └── DaemonOtelTracingClient.ts  # OpenTelemetry tracing client\npackages/daemon-core/src/\n├── index.ts                      # DaemonCore class (start / stop lifecycle)\n├── types.ts                      # DaemonCoreConfig interface\n├── server/\n│   ├── daemon-server.ts          # DaemonServer: wires all subsystems\n│   ├── web-socket-server.ts      # DaemonWebSocketServer: Bun WebSocket + HTTP fetch handler\n│   ├── web-socket-request-router.ts  # Routes JSON-RPC messages to terminal or droid handlers\n│   ├── websocket-auth-adapter.ts # Authentication + connection management per WebSocket\n│   ├── handlers/\n│   │   ├── droid-request-handler.ts    # Handles daemon.* droid methods (sessions, messages)\n│   │   └── terminal-request-handler.ts # Handles daemon.* terminal methods (PTY)\n│   └── code-server-proxy.ts      # HTTP + WebSocket proxy for code-server\n├── droid/\n│   └── droid-registry.ts         # Tracks active droid processes per session\n├── terminal/\n│   └── terminal-manager.ts       # PTY session lifecycle via bun-pty\n├── automations/\n│   ├── poller.ts                 # Polls for due automation runs\n│   ├── control-plane.ts          # Dispatches and monitors automation runs\n│   └── recovery.ts               # Recovers interrupted runs on startup\n├── relay/\n│   ├── RelayConnection.ts        # Outbound WebSocket relay for Computer daemon mode\n│   └── WebSocketTransport.ts\n└── services/\n    ├── ApiClient.ts              # HTTP client for backend REST calls\n    └── HeartbeatService.ts       # Periodic heartbeat to backend API\npackages/daemon-client/src/\n├── DaemonClient.ts               # High-level typed client used by CLI/web\n└── WebSocketConnection.ts        # WebSocket connection with retry + backoff\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| Abstraction | File | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `DaemonCore` | `packages/daemon-core/src/index.ts` | Top-level start/stop lifecycle wrapper |\n| `DaemonServer` | `packages/daemon-core/src/server/daemon-server.ts` | Orchestrates all subsystems (WebSocket, heartbeat, automations, relay) |\n| `DaemonWebSocketServer` | `packages/daemon-core/src/server/web-socket-server.ts` | Bun HTTP + WebSocket server; routes connections to auth adapter, tunnel handler, or code-server proxy |\n| `WebSocketAuthAdapter` | `packages/daemon-core/src/server/websocket-auth-adapter.ts` | Authenticates each WebSocket connection; manages per-connection request routing |\n| `WebSocketRequestRouter` | `packages/daemon-core/src/server/web-socket-request-router.ts` | Dispatches JSON-RPC requests to `TerminalRequestHandler` or `DroidRequestHandler` |\n| `DroidRequestHandler` | `packages/daemon-core/src/server/handlers/droid-request-handler.ts` | Implements all `daemon.{initialize,load,add_user_message,interrupt}_session` methods |\n| `TerminalRequestHandler` | `packages/daemon-core/src/server/handlers/terminal-request-handler.ts` | Implements all `daemon.{create,write,resize,close,list}_terminal` methods |\n| `DroidRegistry` | `packages/daemon-core/src/droid/droid-registry.ts` | Tracks live droid processes; broadcasts notifications to all connected clients |\n| `TerminalManager` | `packages/daemon-core/src/terminal/terminal-manager.ts` | Creates and manages PTY processes via `bun-pty` |\n| `HeartbeatService` | `packages/daemon-core/src/services/HeartbeatService.ts` | Sends periodic pings to `/api/daemon/heartbeat` when activity is detected |\n| `DueRunPoller` | `packages/daemon-core/src/automations/poller.ts` | Polls filesystem for scheduled automation triggers every 60 seconds |\n| `RelayConnection` | `packages/daemon-core/src/relay/RelayConnection.ts` | Connects outbound to relay server (Computer mode) so remote clients can reach daemon |\n| `UpdateService` | `apps/daemon/src/services/UpdateService.ts` | Checks `downloads.factory.ai` for newer `factoryd` binary; replaces in-place and restarts |\n| `DaemonClient` | `packages/daemon-client/src/DaemonClient.ts` | Typed RPC client used by CLI and web frontend to call all daemon methods |\n\n## How it works\n\n### Startup sequence\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant main as index.ts\n    participant env as environment.ts\n    participant upd as UpdateService\n    participant core as DaemonCore\n    participant srv as DaemonServer\n    participant ws as DaemonWebSocketServer\n\n    main->>env: initializeEnvironment()\n    main->>upd: runAutoUpdate() — checks CDN / backend API\n    upd-->>main: updated binary (restart) or no-op\n    main->>core: new DaemonCore(config)\n    main->>core: core.start()\n    core->>srv: new DaemonServer(config)\n    srv->>ws: start() — Bun.serve() on port 37643 / 41723\n    srv->>srv: heartbeatService.start()\n    srv->>srv: recoverInterruptedRuns()\n    srv->>srv: dueRunPoller.start()\n    ws-->>main: listening, health endpoint available\n```\n\n### WebSocket connection lifecycle\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant Client as CLI / web / desktop\n    participant WS as DaemonWebSocketServer\n    participant Auth as WebSocketAuthAdapter\n    participant Router as WebSocketRequestRouter\n    participant Handler as DroidRequestHandler\n\n    Client->>WS: WebSocket upgrade (ws://localhost:37643)\n    WS->>Auth: open(ws)\n    Auth->>Auth: validate JWT / API key\n    Auth-->>Client: authentication challenge / accept\n    Client->>WS: JSON-RPC request (e.g. daemon.initialize_session)\n    WS->>Auth: message(ws, data)\n    Auth->>Router: handleMessage(ws, data)\n    Router->>Handler: handleRequest(ws, request)\n    Handler-->>Router: response\n    Router-->>Client: JSON-RPC response\n    Handler-->>Client: daemon.session_notification (async events)\n```\n\n### Droid session management\n\nEach call to `daemon.initialize_session` spawns a `droid` CLI child process. The `DroidRegistry` tracks the mapping between session IDs and those processes. When the droid process produces output (LLM tokens, tool results, status changes), `DroidRequestHandler` relays it to all connected WebSocket clients as `daemon.session_notification` events.\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    Client[\"CLI / web\"] -->|\"daemon.add_user_message\"| Handler[\"DroidRequestHandler\"]\n    Handler -->|\"stdin JSON-RPC\"| DroidProcess[\"droid process\\n(child process)\"]\n    DroidProcess -->|\"stdout JSON-RPC\"| Handler\n    Handler -->|\"daemon.session_notification\"| Client\n    Handler -->|\"daemon.request_permission\"| Client\n    Client -->|\"permission response\"| Handler\n```\n\n### Machine types and deployment\n\nThe daemon adapts its behavior based on `MachineType`:\n\n| Machine type | Where it runs | Port | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `Local` | Developer laptop | 41723 (dev) / 37643 (prod) | Bundled with Electron; `FACTORYD_DISABLE_AUTO_UPDATE=true` when launched from app |\n| `Ephemeral` | E2B CDE sandbox | 37643 | Downloaded from `downloads.factory.ai` at workspace init; auto-updates |\n| `Computer` | Factory Computer | 37643 | Connects outbound via relay; auto-update runs on idle |\n\nPort binding prevents multiple daemon instances: starting a second instance while one is running returns an error.\n\n## Integration points\n\n| System | Direction | Details |\n|---|---|---|\n| CLI / web / desktop | Inbound WebSocket | JSON-RPC 2.0 over `ws://localhost:<port>` |\n| Backend API (`/api/daemon/heartbeat`) | Outbound REST | `HeartbeatService` pings every interval with active session count |\n| Relay server | Outbound WebSocket | `RelayConnection` (Computer mode only); enables remote client access without port forwarding |\n| `droid` CLI process | Child process stdio | JSON-RPC 2.0 over stdin/stdout |\n| `downloads.factory.ai` | Outbound HTTPS | `UpdateService` checks for newer `factoryd` binary on startup |\n| PTY (OS) | Local | `TerminalManager` creates PTY processes via `bun-pty` for raw terminal sessions |\n\nSee [overview/architecture.md](../overview/architecture.md) for system-level diagrams.\n\n## Entry points for modification\n\n- **Add a new JSON-RPC method**: register it in `@factory/common/daemon` enums, then implement a handler in `packages/daemon-core/src/server/handlers/droid-request-handler.ts` or a new handler; register it in `packages/daemon-core/src/server/web-socket-request-router.ts`.\n- **Change session spawn behavior**: edit `packages/daemon-core/src/droid/droid-registry.ts` and the `DroidRequestHandler`.\n- **Change auto-update behavior**: edit `apps/daemon/src/services/UpdateService.ts` and `apps/daemon/src/index.ts`.\n- **Adjust heartbeat timing or payload**: edit `packages/daemon-core/src/services/HeartbeatService.ts`.\n- **Add a new automation trigger**: extend `packages/daemon-core/src/automations/`.\n- **Change transport (TCP ↔ Unix socket)**: pass `--unix <path>` CLI option; the WebSocket server switches to Unix socket mode automatically.\n\nFor local development, run `npm run dev` inside `apps/daemon/` (logs stream to `/tmp/factory-dev-daemon.log`). See [apps/cli/index.md](cli/index.md) for the CLI that connects to the daemon. See [features/sessions.md](../features/sessions.md) for session lifecycle from the user perspective. See [how-to-monitor/logging.md](../how-to-monitor/logging.md) for log locations and structure. See [reference/configuration.md](../reference/configuration.md) for all environment variables.\n",
