            "content": "# Backend API\n\n**Active contributors**: factory-sherry, factory-octavian, Alvin Sng, factory-jerry, Nikita Lilichenko, Luke Alvoeiro, David Vendrow\n\n## Purpose\n\n`apps/backend` is the central backend API for Factory. It is a Next.js 15 application deployed on Vercel and serves as:\n\n- An **LLM proxy** — translates requests from Droid clients into provider-specific API calls (Anthropic, Vertex AI, AWS Bedrock, OpenAI, Google, Fireworks, Baseten, xAI) and streams responses back\n- An **auth gateway** — integrates with WorkOS for user authentication and organization management\n- A **billing engine** — manages subscriptions, usage tracking, and metering through Orb and Stripe\n- A **data store** — reads and writes session, organization, and user data to Firestore\n- A **platform hub** — handles integrations (GitHub, GitLab, Linear, Jira, Slack, Notion, Google Docs), daemon heartbeats, and scheduled background jobs\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/backend/\n├── src/\n│   ├── app/                    # Next.js App Router\n│   │   ├── api/\n│   │   │   ├── llm/            # LLM proxy routes (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google, custom)\n│   │   │   ├── sessions/       # Session CRUD and management\n│   │   │   ├── billing/        # Payment methods, limits, overage\n│   │   │   ├── auth/           # Token verification, OAuth actions\n│   │   │   ├── daemon/         # Daemon heartbeat endpoint\n│   │   │   ├── cron/           # Cron job endpoints (15 jobs)\n│   │   │   ├── integrations/   # OAuth + integration data routes\n│   │   │   ├── organization/   # Org management endpoints\n│   │   │   ├── webhooks/       # Webhook receivers (Orb, WorkOS, Jira, Linear, Slack)\n│   │   │   ├── github/         # GitHub App routes\n│   │   │   ├── feature-flags/  # Statsig server-side evaluation\n│   │   │   ├── admin/          # Internal admin endpoints\n│   │   │   └── ...             # health, echo, debug, tools, v0, v1, etc.\n│   │   └── cli/                # CLI-specific Next.js pages (download plans, etc.)\n│   ├── features/\n│   │   ├── llm/\n│   │   │   ├── model-ids.ts    # Maps internal ModelID → provider-specific string\n│   │   │   └── streaming/      # Token usage tracking and metrics recording\n│   │   ├── droids/             # Droid configuration feature logic\n│   │   ├── feature-flags/      # Statsig integration helpers\n│   │   ├── integrations/       # Integration context and OAuth helpers\n│   │   ├── prompts/            # Prompt management\n│   │   └── workspace/          # Workspace feature helpers\n│   ├── services/\n│   │   ├── workos/             # WorkOS: session, webhooks, directory sync, reconciliation\n│   │   ├── orb/                # Orb: subscriptions, usage, webhooks, billing events\n│   │   ├── billing/            # Billing constants, limit helpers\n│   │   ├── stripe/             # Stripe payment handling\n│   │   ├── computer/           # CDE provider abstraction (E2B, etc.)\n│   │   ├── e2b/                # E2B sandbox management\n│   │   ├── integrations/       # GitHub, GitLab, Linear, Jira, Slack, Notion, OAuth\n│   │   ├── bigquery/           # BigQuery export for analytics\n│   │   ├── segment/            # Segment analytics event tracking\n│   │   ├── fraud/              # Fraud detection helpers\n│   │   ├── exa/                # Exa search API wrapper\n│   │   ├── loops/              # Loops email integration\n│   │   ├── referrals/          # Referral program logic\n│   │   ├── remote-update/      # Remote daemon update orchestration\n│   │   ├── telemetry/          # OpenTelemetry backend tracing client\n│   │   └── you/                # You.com search integration\n│   ├── middleware.ts            # Edge middleware: CORS validation, security headers\n│   ├── instrumentation.ts       # Sentry + OpenTelemetry initialization\n│   ├── constants.ts             # Allowed CORS origins, CSP header\n│   └── routes.ts                # AppRoutes — typed frontend URL helpers\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| Abstraction | File | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| LLM proxy (`/api/llm/a/v1/messages`) | `src/app/api/llm/a/v1/messages/route.ts` | Proxies Anthropic-compatible requests to Anthropic, Vertex AI, AWS Bedrock, or Fireworks; streams SSE back to caller |\n| LLM proxy (`/api/llm/o/v1/*`) | `src/app/api/llm/o/` | OpenAI-compatible proxy (chat completions, responses API) |\n| LLM proxy (`/api/llm/g/v1/*`) | `src/app/api/llm/g/` | Google Gemini proxy |\n| `getApiProviderModelId` | `src/features/llm/model-ids.ts` | Translates internal `ModelID` enum values to provider-specific model strings; kept server-side to avoid leaking unreleased model IDs |\n| `handleRouteMiddleware` | `src/app/api/_utils/middleware.ts` | Shared Next.js route handler wrapper: extracts authenticated user, org, Firestore ID, and start time |\n| `isAllowedOrigin` | `src/middleware.ts` | Pre-compiled CORS origin validator used at the edge for all routes |\n| WorkOS service | `src/services/workos/` | Session management, webhook processing, directory sync (SCIM), org reconciliation |\n| Orb service | `src/services/orb/` | Subscription CRUD, usage metering, webhook ingestion, trial/cancellation logic |\n| `HeartbeatService` consumer (`/api/daemon/heartbeat`) | `src/app/api/daemon/heartbeat/route.ts` | Receives daemon pings; extends E2B sandbox timeouts for both ephemeral sandboxes and Computer provider instances |\n| Integrations service | `src/services/integrations/` | OAuth flows and API clients for GitHub, GitLab, Linear, Jira, Slack, Notion, Google Docs, PagerDuty, Sentry |\n| Cron endpoints | `src/app/api/cron/` | 15 cron jobs for billing, usage sync, trial emails, workspace cleanup, and WorkOS seat sync |\n\n## How it works\n\n### Request lifecycle\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant Client as CLI / web / desktop\n    participant Edge as Edge middleware<br/>(middleware.ts)\n    participant Handler as Route handler<br/>(handleRouteMiddleware)\n    participant WorkOS as WorkOS\n    participant Firestore as Firestore\n    participant Service as Service layer\n\n    Client->>Edge: HTTP request (with JWT / API key)\n    Edge->>Edge: validate Origin (CORS), set security headers\n    Edge-->>Client: preflight response (OPTIONS) or continue\n    Handler->>WorkOS: verify JWT → user identity\n    Handler->>Firestore: load org record → firestoreOrgId\n    Handler->>Service: business logic\n    Service-->>Handler: result\n    Handler-->>Client: JSON / SSE response\n```\n\n### LLM proxy flow\n\nThe LLM proxy routes at `src/app/api/llm/` translate requests from the Droid client into provider-specific calls. The route chooses a provider (Anthropic, Vertex AI, Bedrock, OpenAI, Google, Fireworks, Baseten, xAI) based on the `x-api-provider` header and the internal `ModelID` enum. API credentials are resolved from AWS Secrets Manager at request time.\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant Droid as Droid CLI / daemon\n    participant Proxy as /api/llm/a/v1/messages\n    participant Validate as validateProxyRequest\n    participant Billing as recordMessageUsage\n    participant Provider as LLM provider\n\n    Droid->>Proxy: POST with model ID + messages\n    Proxy->>Validate: auth, rate limits, model mapping\n    Validate-->>Proxy: apiProvider, apiProviderModelId, effectivePool\n    Proxy->>Provider: provider-specific request (Anthropic / Vertex / Bedrock / etc.)\n    Provider-->>Proxy: SSE token stream\n    Proxy-->>Droid: SSE pass-through (or Bedrock event-stream transform)\n    Proxy->>Billing: recordMessageUsage (tokens, model, org)\n```\n\nFor BYOK (Bring Your Own Key) users the proxy forwards to Anthropic directly using the user's own key, bypassing Factory's pool.\n\n### Auth integration\n\nWorkOS is the identity provider. All API routes verify the user's JWT via the `handleRouteMiddleware` helper. The middleware also accepts Factory API keys for non-interactive (daemon) use. WorkOS webhooks at `src/app/api/webhooks/workos/` handle directory sync events for enterprise SSO/SCIM.\n\n### Billing\n\nBilling uses Orb for usage-based metering and Stripe for payment processing. The `src/services/orb/` layer handles subscription creation, trial management, usage event ingestion, and webhook processing from Orb. Cron jobs in `src/app/api/cron/` keep subscriptions in sync:\n\n| Cron job | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `sync-orb-usage` | Pushes LLM token usage to Orb for billing |\n| `resync-orb-subscription` | Reconciles subscription state with Orb |\n| `cancel-expiring-trials` | Cancels trials before they convert without payment |\n| `cancel-unpaid-subscriptions` | Terminates subscriptions with failed payment |\n| `sync-extra-usage-balance` | Syncs overage balance for pay-as-you-go orgs |\n| `process-paid-referrals` | Issues referral credits after successful payment |\n| `send-trial-end-emails` | Sends trial expiry reminders via Loops |\n| `ban-duplicate-cards` | Fraud detection for duplicate payment instruments |\n| `cleanup-failed-workspaces` | Removes stale sandbox workspaces from Firestore |\n| `directory-sync` | Runs WorkOS directory sync for SCIM orgs |\n| `refresh-workspace-repo` | Refreshes GitHub repo metadata on workspaces |\n| `sync-workos-seats` | Reconciles WorkOS seat counts with org membership |\n\n### Firestore data model\n\nThe backend reads and writes to Firestore. The main collections are sessions, organizations, users, workspaces, sessions, computers, and integration tokens. Data models live in `src/data/models/`.\n\n### Daemon heartbeat\n\nWhen a daemon starts and its machine is an E2B sandbox or Computer, it sends `POST /api/daemon/heartbeat` periodically. The route at `src/app/api/daemon/heartbeat/route.ts` calls the E2B API to reset the sandbox kill timer, preventing the sandbox from being destroyed during active use.\n\n### Observability\n\n`src/instrumentation.ts` initializes Sentry (error tracking) and optionally OpenTelemetry (distributed traces exported to Axiom) for the Node.js runtime. The edge runtime registers a separate Sentry instance. See [how-to-monitor/logging.md](../how-to-monitor/logging.md).\n\n## Integration points\n\n| System | Direction | Details |\n|---|---|---|\n| Droid CLI / daemon | Inbound REST | LLM proxy, sessions API, daemon heartbeat, billing, integrations |\n| WorkOS | Outbound + Webhooks inbound | Auth token verification, user provisioning, SCIM directory sync |\n| Orb | Outbound + Webhooks inbound | Subscription management, usage metering |\n| Stripe | Outbound | Payment method management, portal sessions |\n| E2B | Outbound | Sandbox provisioning and timeout extension |\n| Anthropic / OpenAI / Google / AWS Bedrock / Fireworks / Baseten / xAI | Outbound | LLM provider calls via proxy |\n| GitHub / GitLab / Linear / Jira / Slack / Notion / Google Docs | Outbound + Webhooks inbound | OAuth flows, data reads, webhook ingestion |\n| Statsig | Outbound | Feature flag evaluation (`src/features/feature-flags/`) |\n| Segment | Outbound | Analytics event tracking |\n| Sentry | Outbound | Error capture |\n| Axiom (via OTLP) | Outbound | Distributed trace export when `FACTORY_OTEL_ENABLED=true` |\n\nSee [overview/architecture.md](../overview/architecture.md) for system-level diagrams. See [features/llm-integration.md](../features/llm-integration.md) for the LLM provider abstraction. See [security.md](../security/index.md) for auth, authorization, and secrets handling. See [reference/configuration.md](../reference/configuration.md) for environment variables.\n\n## Entry points for modification\n\n- **Add an LLM provider or model**: add a `ModelID` entry to `@factory/common/src/llm/`, map it in `src/features/llm/model-ids.ts`, then wire up the provider call in the relevant `route.ts` under `src/app/api/llm/`.\n- **Add a REST endpoint**: create a new directory under `src/app/api/` following Next.js App Router conventions; share auth by calling `handleRouteMiddleware`.\n- **Add a cron job**: create a new route handler under `src/app/api/cron/`, add a schedule in `vercel.json`, and add cleanup/safety logic for idempotent execution.\n- **Add an integration**: add OAuth handling in `src/services/integrations/oauth/`, add an API client in `src/services/integrations/<provider>/`, and expose routes under `src/app/api/integrations/`.\n- **Change CORS policy**: update `allowedOrigins` in `src/constants.ts`.\n- **Change security headers**: edit `setSecurityHeaders` and `cspHeader` in `src/middleware.ts` and `src/constants.ts`.\n",
