            "content": "# Apps overview\n\n_Active contributors: Alvin Sng, factory-jerry, David Vendrow, Luke Alvoeiro, factory-sherry_\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe `apps/` directory contains every deployable or installable unit in the monorepo: the end-user clients (web, desktop, CLI), the server-side services (backend, daemon, relay, signal, functions), the IDE integrations (VS Code, JetBrains), and supporting tooling (admin dashboard, storybook, scripts).\n\nAll apps share packages from the `packages/` workspace. UI apps depend on `@factory/core-ui` for components and `@factory/frontend` for shared React features. The CLI/daemon are built with Bun. Web and admin use Next.js or Vite. See [overview/architecture.md](../overview/architecture.md) for how all the pieces connect.\n\n## App inventory\n\n| App | Description | Tech | Dev port |\n|-----|-------------|------|----------|\n| [`apps/web`](./web.md) | Main browser UI for Droid | Vite + React 19 | 3002 |\n| [`apps/desktop`](./desktop.md) | Electron desktop app, bundles daemon | Electron 39, Vite + React 19 | — |\n| [`apps/admin`](./admin.md) | Internal admin dashboard (Factory staff) | Next.js 15 | 3001 |\n| [`apps/backend`](./backend.md) | REST API + LLM proxy | Next.js 15 | 3000 |\n| [`apps/cli`](./cli/index.md) | Primary Droid CLI tool | Bun | — |\n| [`apps/daemon`](./daemon.md) | `factoryd` session management daemon | Bun | 4001/4002 |\n| [`apps/factory-vscode-extension`](./vscode-extension.md) | VS Code integration | TypeScript, VS Code API | — |\n| [`apps/factory-jetbrains-plugin`](./other-apps.md#jetbrains-plugin) | JetBrains IDE integration | Kotlin/Gradle | — |\n| [`apps/signal`](./other-apps.md#signal) | Signal processing GCP function | Node.js | — |\n| [`apps/functions`](./other-apps.md#functions) | Firebase cloud functions | Firebase Functions v2 | — |\n| [`apps/relay`](./other-apps.md#relay) | WebSocket relay for BYOI computers | Bun | 8080 |\n| [`apps/scripts`](./other-apps.md#scripts) | Operational and release scripts | TypeScript | — |\n| [`apps/storybook`](./other-apps.md#storybook) | Component showcase | Storybook 8 | 6006 |\n| `apps/bridge` | Placeholder (empty) | — | — |\n| `apps/migrations` | Placeholder (scripts at `apps/scripts/src/migrations/`) | — | — |\n\n## How they relate\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    CLI[\"apps/cli<br/>(Droid CLI)\"] -->|stdin/stdout JSON-RPC| DAEMON\n    WEB[\"apps/web<br/>(Browser)\"] -->|WebSocket JSON-RPC| DAEMON\n    DESKTOP[\"apps/desktop<br/>(Electron)\"] -->|WebSocket JSON-RPC| DAEMON\n    DESKTOP -->|spawns| DAEMON[\"apps/daemon<br/>(factoryd)\"]\n    VSCODE[\"apps/factory-vscode-extension\"] -->|opens terminal| CLI\n    VSCODE -->|MCP HTTP| CLI\n    JETBRAINS[\"apps/factory-jetbrains-plugin\"] -->|opens terminal| CLI\n    DAEMON -->|HTTP| BACKEND[\"apps/backend<br/>(LLM proxy / API)\"]\n    WEB -->|HTTP| BACKEND\n    RELAY[\"apps/relay\"] -->|WS relay| DAEMON\n    WEB -->|WS| RELAY\n```\n\nThe **daemon** is the central hub. All UI clients connect to it over WebSocket JSON-RPC. The **desktop app** is special in that it spawns the daemon as a child process and manages its lifecycle. The **CLI** communicates with a daemon via stdin/stdout RPC. The **backend** serves as both the REST API for user data and the LLM proxy for AI calls. The **relay** handles BYOI (Bring Your Own Infrastructure) computer connections, multiplexing browser clients to daemon agents.\n\n## Starting the dev environment\n\n```bash\n# Start backend, web, storybook, admin, daemon together\nnpm run dev:web\n\n# Desktop only (local machine, not SSH)\nnpm run dev:desktop\n```\n\nLog files stream to `/tmp/factory-dev-backend.log`, `/tmp/factory-dev-admin.log`, `/tmp/factory-dev-desktop.log`, `/tmp/factory-dev-daemon.log`.\n\nSee [deployment/index.md](../deployment/index.md) for production deployment.\n",
