            "content": "# apps/web — Main web application\n\n_Active contributors: Alvin Sng, Nikita Lilichenko, Andrei Savin, Ricky S, factory-sherry_\n\n## Purpose\n\n`apps/web` is the browser-based client for Droid. It gives users access to all the same core features as the CLI — starting and resuming sessions, reviewing session history, configuring settings, viewing analytics, managing automations, browsing the wiki — packaged as a Vite + React 19 single-page application deployed to Vercel.\n\nIt is intentionally thin. Almost all feature logic and routing live in `packages/frontend`; the web app's own source tree handles only auth bootstrapping and the entry point.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/web/\n├── src/\n│   ├── main.tsx                   # React root, mounts WebAuthProvider\n│   ├── auth/\n│   │   ├── WebAuth.provider.tsx   # WorkOS auth wrapper + router mount\n│   │   └── utils.ts               # returnTo path validation\n│   ├── config/                    # Runtime environment helpers\n│   └── types/                     # App-level type declarations\n├── index.html\n├── vite.config.ts\n├── playwright.config.ts           # E2E test config\n└── package.json\n```\n\nRouting and every feature page live in [`packages/frontend`](../packages/frontend/index.md).\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| Abstraction | File | Role |\n|-------------|------|------|\n| `WebAuthProvider` | `src/auth/WebAuth.provider.tsx` | Wraps app in WorkOS `AuthKitProvider`, handles OAuth callback, E2E bypass |\n| `RootApp` | `packages/frontend/src/router/RootApp.tsx` | Top-level component mounted by every client (web, desktop) |\n| `initRouter` | `packages/frontend/src/router/initRouter.ts` | Creates a TanStack Router instance; web uses browser history |\n| `DaemonClient` | `packages/daemon-client/src/DaemonClient.ts` | WebSocket JSON-RPC client used by session features |\n| E2E auth bypass | `src/auth/WebAuth.provider.tsx` | Reads `e2e:access-token` from `localStorage`, skips WorkOS |\n\n## How it works\n\n### Boot sequence\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant Browser\n    participant WebAuthProvider\n    participant WorkOS\n    participant RootApp\n    participant DaemonClient\n\n    Browser->>WebAuthProvider: load index.html\n    WebAuthProvider->>WorkOS: AuthKitProvider initializes (VITE_WORKOS_CLIENT_ID)\n    WorkOS-->>WebAuthProvider: isLoading=false, user or null\n    WebAuthProvider->>RootApp: render with authContext\n    RootApp->>DaemonClient: connect ws://localhost:PORT\n    DaemonClient-->>RootApp: connection established\n```\n\n### Auth flow\n\n1. `WebAuthProvider` in `src/auth/WebAuth.provider.tsx` wraps the entire app in `@workos-inc/authkit-react`'s `AuthKitProvider`.\n2. If the user is not authenticated, `RootApp` redirects to the login page which calls `auth.signIn()` with a `returnTo` state param.\n3. WorkOS redirects back to `/callback`. `handleRedirectCallback` validates `returnTo`, then navigates the user to their requested path.\n4. In E2E tests, a JWT stored under `e2e:access-token` in `localStorage` bypasses WorkOS entirely; `WebAuthProvider` decodes it and produces a synthetic `AuthContextValue`.\n5. Auth times out after 5 000 ms to avoid blocking CI environments where WorkOS is unavailable.\n\n### Route structure\n\nRoutes are defined in `packages/frontend/src/router/createAppRouter.ts`. All routes except `/callback`, `/login`, and `/logout` require authentication.\n\n| Path | Page |\n|------|------|\n| `/sessions` | Sessions list |\n| `/sessions/$sessionId` | Session detail |\n| `/settings` | Settings shell |\n| `/settings/organization` | Organization settings |\n| `/settings/billing` | Billing |\n| `/settings/usage` | Usage dashboard |\n| `/settings/api-keys` | API keys |\n| `/settings/droid-computers` | Droid computer management |\n| `/settings/enterprise-controls` | Enterprise policy controls |\n| `/analytics` | Analytics overview |\n| `/analytics/readiness` | Agent readiness |\n| `/analytics/tokens` | Token usage |\n| `/analytics/activity` | Activity dashboard |\n| `/automations` | Automations |\n| `/wiki` | Wiki browser |\n| `/callback` | WorkOS OAuth callback |\n\n### Connection to daemon\n\nAfter auth, the `sessions` feature in `packages/frontend/src/features/sessions/` creates a `DaemonClient` (from `packages/daemon-client`) that connects over WebSocket to `factoryd`. The URL defaults to `ws://localhost:4002` (production) or `ws://localhost:4001` (dev). All session interaction — creating sessions, sending messages, streaming tool calls — flows through this WebSocket channel. See [apps/daemon.md](./daemon.md) and [features/sessions.md](../features/sessions.md) for details.\n\n## Integration points\n\n- **Backend API** (`apps/backend`): the app calls backend endpoints for user data, billing info, integrations, and analytics. See [apps/backend.md](./backend.md).\n- **Daemon** (`apps/daemon`): live session interaction over WebSocket JSON-RPC. See [apps/daemon.md](./daemon.md).\n- **WorkOS**: authentication via `@workos-inc/authkit-react`. Client ID from `VITE_WORKOS_CLIENT_ID`.\n- **Shared frontend features**: all major feature modules live in `packages/frontend`. See [packages/frontend/index.md](../packages/frontend/index.md).\n- **Design system**: all UI components come from `@factory/core-ui`. See [packages/core-ui.md](../packages/core-ui.md).\n\n## Entry points for modification\n\n| What to change | Where to start |\n|---------------|----------------|\n| Auth behavior or WorkOS config | `apps/web/src/auth/WebAuth.provider.tsx` |\n| Add a new route | `packages/frontend/src/router/createAppRouter.ts` |\n| Add a new feature page | `packages/frontend/src/features/<feature>/pages/` |\n| Vite build config | `apps/web/vite.config.ts` |\n| E2E tests | `apps/web/e2e/` (Playwright, `npm run e2e`) |\n| Unit tests | `apps/web/src/**/*.test.ts` (Vitest, `npm run test`) |\n",
