            "content": "# apps/desktop — Electron desktop app\n\n_Active contributors: factory-jerry, Alvin Sng, factory-sherry, Luke Alvoeiro, David Vendrow_\n\n## Purpose\n\n`apps/desktop` is the Electron 39 application that ships Factory Droid as a native macOS, Windows, and Linux desktop client. It bundles the `droid` CLI binary and launches it as the `factoryd` daemon subprocess when the app starts. The renderer process runs the same `@factory/frontend` React application as `apps/web`, giving users the full Droid UI experience without a browser.\n\nThe desktop app's main distinctions from the web app are:\n\n- It owns the daemon lifecycle (spawns, monitors, and stops `factoryd`).\n- Auth uses the OS keychain via `@factory/runtime/auth` rather than WorkOS browser redirects.\n- It installs the `droid` CLI symlink for terminal use.\n- It auto-updates from Factory's S3 distribution bucket.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/desktop/\n├── src/\n│   ├── main/                          # Electron main process (Node.js)\n│   │   ├── index.ts                   # Entry: runs bootstrap then initLifecycle\n│   │   ├── bootstrap.ts               # Early init: Squirrel events, system CAs\n│   │   ├── initLifecycle.ts           # App lifecycle: auto-updater, daemon, window\n│   │   ├── ipc.ts                     # IPC handlers (auth, dialog, notifications)\n│   │   ├── menu.ts                    # Native application menu\n│   │   ├── window.ts                  # BrowserWindow creation\n│   │   ├── deeplink.ts                # Custom protocol (factory://) deep link handling\n│   │   ├── daemon/\n│   │   │   ├── manager.ts             # DaemonManager: spawn/stop droid daemon\n│   │   │   └── enums.ts               # DaemonState enum\n│   │   ├── auth/\n│   │   │   ├── workos.ts              # OAuth browser flow (opens system browser)\n│   │   │   └── migrateLegacyElectronAuth.ts\n│   │   └── droid/                     # CLI setup: symlinks, PATH\n│   ├── renderer/                      # Electron renderer process (React)\n│   │   ├── main.tsx                   # Mounts DesktopAuthProvider\n│   │   └── auth/\n│   │       └── DesktopAuth.provider.tsx  # IPC-based auth provider\n│   ├── preload/                        # Preload script: exposes electronAPI\n│   └── config/                        # Release channel / env constants\n├── forge.config.ts                    # Electron Forge build / publish config\n├── vite.main.config.ts\n├── vite.renderer.config.ts\n└── package.json\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| Abstraction | File | Role |\n|-------------|------|------|\n| `DaemonManager` | `src/main/daemon/manager.ts` | Spawns and monitors `droid daemon` as a child process |\n| `initLifecycle` | `src/main/initLifecycle.ts` | Orchestrates startup: auto-updater, single instance, daemon, window |\n| `ipc` | `src/main/ipc.ts` | All `ipcMain.handle` registrations: auth, dialogs, notifications |\n| `DesktopAuthProvider` | `src/renderer/auth/DesktopAuth.provider.tsx` | Renderer auth: polls main process via `window.electronAPI.auth` |\n| `window.electronAPI` | `src/preload/` | Contextbridge-exposed API surface for renderer ↔ main communication |\n| `update-electron-app` | `initLifecycle.ts` | Auto-update from S3 static storage |\n\n## How it works\n\n### Startup sequence\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant OS\n    participant Main as Main process\n    participant Daemon as factoryd (child)\n    participant Renderer\n\n    OS->>Main: app ready\n    Main->>Main: load shell environment (PATH, SHELL)\n    Main->>Main: register factory:// protocol\n    Main->>Main: check version (production only)\n    Main->>Daemon: spawn `droid daemon --enable-code-server --remote-access`\n    Main->>Renderer: createWindow()\n    Renderer->>Main: auth:getAuthData (IPC)\n    Main-->>Renderer: user + access token from OS keychain\n    Renderer->>Daemon: connect WebSocket JSON-RPC\n```\n\n### Daemon management\n\n`DaemonManager` (`src/main/daemon/manager.ts`) resolves the correct command at startup:\n\n- **Packaged app**: `process.resourcesPath/bin/droid` (or `droid.exe` on Windows).\n- **Development**: `droid-dev` from `$PATH`.\n\nThe daemon is launched with `--enable-code-server` (embedded code editor) and `--remote-access` (relay connection for BYOI computers). The WebSocket port is `4002` for production and `4001` for development, controllable via `VITE_DAEMON_PORT`.\n\nOn `before-quit`, the main process stops the daemon gracefully with a 10-second timeout before forcing exit.\n\n### Auth flow\n\nDesktop auth bypasses the WorkOS browser redirect. Instead:\n\n1. `DesktopAuthProvider` calls `window.electronAPI.auth.getAuthData()` on mount.\n2. The main process handler in `ipc.ts` calls `getAuthToken()` from `@factory/runtime/auth`, which reads tokens from the OS keychain.\n3. If not signed in, the renderer triggers `window.electronAPI.auth.signIn()`, which opens the system browser to the WorkOS OAuth URL.\n4. WorkOS redirects to `factory://auth/callback`; the main process intercepts the deep link, extracts the auth code, exchanges it for tokens, and stores them via `@factory/runtime/auth`.\n5. Main notifies the renderer via `auth:success` IPC event.\n\nSign-out stops the daemon first (to clear in-memory auth state), then clears keychain credentials.\n\n### Auto-updater\n\nProduction builds check for updates every 10 minutes (staging: every 2 hours) via `update-electron-app`. The update URL is:\n\n```\n${FACTORY_PUBLIC_DOWNLOADS_BASE_URL}/${releaseChannel}/factory-desktop/updates/${platform}/${arch}\n```\n\nThe release channel is injected at build time as `__FACTORY_RELEASE_CHANNEL__` via Vite.\n\n### Differences from web app\n\n| Aspect | Web (`apps/web`) | Desktop (`apps/desktop`) |\n|--------|-----------------|--------------------------|\n| Auth | WorkOS browser redirect | IPC to main process + OS keychain |\n| Router | Browser history | Hash history (`historyType: 'hash'`) |\n| Daemon | External (user must run separately) | Owned: spawned at app start |\n| Updates | Vercel deploy | Electron auto-updater from S3 |\n| CLI setup | N/A | `setupCliIfNeeded()` creates symlinks |\n\n## Integration points\n\n- **`apps/daemon`**: spawned as a child process; communicates with renderer via the same WebSocket JSON-RPC as the web app. See [apps/daemon.md](./daemon.md).\n- **`@factory/frontend`**: renderer uses `RootApp` and all feature pages from the shared package. See [packages/frontend/index.md](../packages/frontend/index.md).\n- **`@factory/runtime/auth`**: keychain credential storage and JWT management.\n- **`apps/relay`**: daemon is started with `--remote-access`, connecting it to the relay for BYOI computer sessions.\n- **Electron Forge + S3**: build packaging and distribution. Publisher config in `forge.config.ts`.\n\n## Entry points for modification\n\n| What to change | Where to start |\n|---------------|----------------|\n| Daemon startup flags or binary resolution | `src/main/daemon/manager.ts` |\n| IPC handlers (new native capabilities) | `src/main/ipc.ts` + `src/preload/` |\n| Auth flow | `src/main/auth/workos.ts`, `src/renderer/auth/DesktopAuth.provider.tsx` |\n| App lifecycle (startup/shutdown) | `src/main/initLifecycle.ts` |\n| Auto-updater configuration | `src/main/initLifecycle.ts` (search `updateElectronApp`) |\n| Build / packaging targets | `forge.config.ts` |\n| Renderer UI | `packages/frontend/src/` (shared with web) |\n",
