            "content": "# apps/admin — Admin dashboard\n\n_Active contributors: Alvin Sng, Nikita Lilichenko, nikhil-factory, Abhay Singhal, factory-sherry_\n\n## Purpose\n\n`apps/admin` is an internal Next.js 15 dashboard used exclusively by Factory staff. It provides privileged access to operational data that regular users cannot see: raw organization state, member management, billing promotions, fraud signals, pilot program configuration, analytics query tooling, and session inspection across all organizations.\n\nIt runs on port 3001 and is protected behind a Firebase-authenticated admin gateway — only accounts in the Factory Google Workspace can access it.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/admin/\n├── src/\n│   ├── app/                           # Next.js 15 App Router\n│   │   ├── layout.tsx                 # Root layout: Redux, styled-components, AdminAuthGateway\n│   │   ├── page.tsx                   # Home/welcome page\n│   │   ├── analytics/page.tsx         # Analytics API query viewer\n│   │   ├── audit-log/                 # Audit log viewer\n│   │   ├── fraud-detection/           # Fraud signal dashboard\n│   │   ├── organizations/\n│   │   │   ├── page.tsx               # Organization list\n│   │   │   └── [orgId]/\n│   │   │       ├── page.tsx           # Org detail: members, usage limits, sessions\n│   │   │       └── sessions/          # Org session list\n│   │   ├── pilots/                    # Pilot program management\n│   │   ├── promotions/                # Discount/promotion management\n│   │   └── api/                       # API route handlers\n│   │       ├── analytics/             # Proxy to backend analytics endpoints\n│   │       ├── auth/                  # Firebase auth verification\n│   │       ├── cron/                  # Cron job endpoints\n│   │       ├── fraud-detection/       # Fraud data endpoints\n│   │       ├── health/                # Health check\n│   │       ├── orgs/                  # Organization management endpoints\n│   │       ├── pilots/                # Pilot endpoints\n│   │       └── promotions/            # Promotion endpoints\n│   ├── components/                    # Admin-specific React components\n│   │   ├── AdminAuthGateway.tsx       # Firebase auth gate (renders children only if authorized)\n│   │   ├── AdminLayout/               # Nav shell\n│   │   ├── FraudDetection/            # Fraud signal display components\n│   │   ├── members/                   # MemberManagementTable\n│   │   ├── organizations/             # UsageLimitsForm, MemoryPanel, IndexingStatusSection\n│   │   ├── pilots/                    # Pilot detail and analytics components\n│   │   ├── promotions/                # Promotion management UI\n│   │   ├── sessions/                  # SessionsList (cross-org)\n│   │   └── TopNav/                    # Top navigation bar\n│   ├── hooks/                         # useAdminAuth, useAuthenticatedFetch, etc.\n│   ├── services/                      # Data access wrappers (Firestore, Axiom, BigQuery)\n│   ├── state/                         # Redux Toolkit store + slices\n│   ├── types/                         # Admin-specific TypeScript types\n│   └── ui/                            # Admin design primitives (styled-components)\n│       ├── layout/                    # Group, Stack layout helpers\n│       └── typography/                # Heading, Text\n└── package.json\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| Abstraction | File | Role |\n|-------------|------|------|\n| `AdminAuthGateway` | `src/components/AdminAuthGateway.tsx` | Firebase auth gate; only Factory staff accounts pass |\n| `useAdminAuth` | `src/hooks/useAdminAuth.ts` | Hook that reads the signed-in Firebase user |\n| `useAuthenticatedFetch` | `src/hooks/useAuthenticatedFetch.ts` | Fetch wrapper that attaches Firebase ID token |\n| `store` | `src/state/store.ts` | Redux Toolkit store used for cross-component admin state |\n| Organization detail page | `src/app/organizations/[orgId]/page.tsx` | Central hub for per-org operations |\n| `UsageLimitsForm` | `src/components/organizations/UsageLimitsForm.tsx` | Edit token/usage caps per org |\n| `MemberManagementTable` | `src/components/members/MemberManagementTable.tsx` | Invite, remove, and role-change org members |\n| `SessionsList` | `src/components/sessions/SessionsList.tsx` | Browse all sessions for an org |\n\n## How it works\n\n### Authentication\n\nThe admin app uses Firebase Authentication directly (separate from WorkOS used in `apps/web`). `AdminAuthGateway` (`src/components/AdminAuthGateway.tsx`) checks the signed-in Firebase user on every render. Only accounts in the permitted Factory Google domain are allowed through. All API routes (`src/app/api/`) verify the Firebase ID token server-side via `src/app/api/auth/`.\n\n### Key features\n\n**Organization management** (`/organizations`, `/organizations/[orgId]`): list all Firestore orgs, view/edit member roles, set usage limits (token caps, rate limits), inspect memory, view integration status, and browse sessions for any org.\n\n**Analytics viewer** (`/analytics`): a debug tool that calls the same backend analytics API endpoints as the product UI, impersonating any organization ID. Supports querying tokens, tools, activity, productivity, and user data with date ranges and group-by options.\n\n**Fraud detection** (`/fraud-detection`): surface signals and risk scores for fraud review; uses BigQuery and Axiom data via the API routes under `src/app/api/fraud-detection/`.\n\n**Pilot programs** (`/pilots`): configure which organizations are in experimental feature programs; includes AI-generated summary blurbs per pilot and an analytics dashboard.\n\n**Promotions** (`/promotions`): create and manage discount codes and subscription promotions.\n\n**Audit log** (`/audit-log`): read-only view of admin actions for compliance purposes.\n\n### Data sources\n\nThe admin app pulls from multiple backends:\n\n- **Firestore** (`firebase-admin`): org documents, member records, pilot configs.\n- **Axiom** (`@axiomhq/js`): log-based analytics and usage metrics.\n- **BigQuery** (`@google-cloud/bigquery`): aggregated analytics queries.\n- **Algolia** (`algoliasearch`): full-text search over session content.\n- **Backend API** (`apps/backend`): proxied via admin API routes, e.g. `/api/analytics/query`.\n\n### Routing (Next.js App Router)\n\nThe admin uses the Next.js 15 App Router with all pages server-rendered by default. The root `layout.tsx` wraps the tree in a Redux `Provider` and `AdminAuthGateway`. Pages that need client-side interactivity carry `'use client'` directives.\n\n## Integration points\n\n- **`apps/backend`**: admin API routes proxy analytics and org management calls to the backend. See [apps/backend.md](./backend.md).\n- **Firebase / Firestore**: primary org data store; admin has privileged read/write access via `firebase-admin`.\n- **Axiom / BigQuery**: analytics data for the fraud detection and analytics viewer.\n- **`@factory/models`**, **`@factory/services`**, **`@factory/common`**: shared Firestore models and service wrappers.\n\n## Entry points for modification\n\n| What to change | Where to start |\n|---------------|----------------|\n| Add a new admin page | `src/app/<page>/page.tsx` (Next.js App Router convention) |\n| Add an API endpoint | `src/app/api/<endpoint>/route.ts` |\n| Change org detail capabilities | `src/app/organizations/[orgId]/page.tsx` |\n| Member management logic | `src/components/members/MemberManagementTable.tsx` |\n| Fraud detection rules | `src/app/api/fraud-detection/`, `src/components/FraudDetection/` |\n| Auth gateway logic | `src/components/AdminAuthGateway.tsx` |\n| Global admin state | `src/state/store.ts` |\n",
