            "content": "# apps/factory-vscode-extension — VS Code extension\n\n_Active contributors: Arman Bolat, Alvin Sng, Varin Nair, factory-jerry_\n\n## Purpose\n\n`apps/factory-vscode-extension` integrates Factory Droid into VS Code. It does two things:\n\n1. **Launches Droid in the IDE**: registers a `factory-vscode-extension.openFactory` command (and an editor title-bar button) that opens a VS Code terminal running the `droid` CLI alongside the user's code.\n2. **Exposes IDE context to the CLI via MCP**: starts an HTTP server implementing the [Model Context Protocol](https://modelcontextprotocol.io) (MCP). The CLI connects to this server to read open files, text selections, diagnostics, and to display proposed diffs inside VS Code's native diff viewer.\n\nThe extension is installed as a `.vsix` package into VS Code. The equivalent plugin for JetBrains IDEs is `apps/factory-jetbrains-plugin`.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/factory-vscode-extension/\n├── src/\n│   ├── extension.ts               # Activation / deactivation, command registration\n│   ├── ide-server.ts              # IDEServer: MCP HTTP server (Express + @modelcontextprotocol/sdk)\n│   ├── open-files-manager.ts      # Tracks active/open files and text selections\n│   ├── diagnostics-manager.ts     # Collects VS Code errors/warnings (diagnostics)\n│   ├── diff-manager.ts            # Opens diffs in VS Code's diff viewer\n│   ├── diff-content-provider.ts   # TextDocumentContentProvider for diff scheme\n│   ├── lock-file-utils.ts         # Write/read port discovery lock file\n│   ├── lock-file-helpers.ts       # Helpers for lock file path resolution\n│   ├── constants.ts               # DIFF_SCHEME constant\n│   └── types.ts                   # LockFileData type\n├── resources/icons/               # Droid icon assets (.svg, .png)\n├── package.json                   # VS Code extension manifest + build scripts\n└── esbuild.config.js              # esbuild bundler config\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| Abstraction | File | Role |\n|-------------|------|------|\n| `activate` | `src/extension.ts` | VS Code lifecycle entry point; starts MCP server and registers commands |\n| `IDEServer` | `src/ide-server.ts` | MCP HTTP server; one `Server` instance per CLI session |\n| `OpenFilesManager` | `src/open-files-manager.ts` | EventEmitter tracking `activeFileChanged`, `openFilesChanged`, `activeSelectionChanged` |\n| `DiagnosticsManager` | `src/diagnostics-manager.ts` | EventEmitter for `stateChanged` on VS Code diagnostic updates |\n| `DiffManager` | `src/diff-manager.ts` | Opens proposed diffs in VS Code's built-in diff viewer |\n| Lock file | `src/lock-file-utils.ts` | JSON file at a well-known path advertising the MCP server's port |\n\n## How it works\n\n### Extension lifecycle\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant VSCode\n    participant Extension\n    participant IDEServer\n    participant CLI\n\n    VSCode->>Extension: activate()\n    Extension->>IDEServer: start() → Express server on random port\n    IDEServer->>IDEServer: write lock file with port number\n    VSCode->>Extension: user clicks toolbar icon\n    Extension->>VSCode: createTerminal({ name: 'Factory', location: Editor })\n    Extension->>VSCode: terminal.sendText('droid')\n    CLI->>IDEServer: HTTP POST /mcp (MCP initialize)\n    IDEServer-->>CLI: session established\n    CLI->>IDEServer: tools/call (get_open_files, get_diagnostics, …)\n    IDEServer-->>CLI: VS Code state snapshot\n    CLI->>IDEServer: tools/call (apply_diff)\n    IDEServer->>VSCode: DiffManager.openDiff()\n```\n\n### MCP server\n\n`IDEServer` (`src/ide-server.ts`) is an Express HTTP server using `StreamableHTTPServerTransport` from `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk`. Each CLI session that connects (`POST /mcp`) gets its own `Server` instance, keyed by the `sessionId` header. The server:\n\n- Exposes MCP tools that the CLI can call to read IDE state (open files, selections, diagnostics).\n- Receives `apply_diff` calls and delegates to `DiffManager` to open VS Code's native diff viewer.\n- Sends proactive MCP notifications to the CLI when the active file or diagnostics change.\n- Writes a heartbeat to the lock file every 60 seconds.\n\n### Port discovery via lock file\n\nOn startup, `IDEServer` writes a lock file containing the bound port and workspace metadata. The CLI reads this file to locate the running MCP server without needing an environment variable. `FACTORY_VSCODE_MCP_PORT` env var set on the terminal provides a direct fallback.\n\n### Editor context capture\n\n`OpenFilesManager` listens to `vscode.window.onDidChangeActiveTextEditor` and `vscode.workspace.onDidChangeTextEditorSelection`. `DiagnosticsManager` listens to `vscode.languages.onDidChangeDiagnostics`. Both emit events that cause `IDEServer` to proactively push notifications to connected CLI sessions.\n\n`IDEServer` keeps a `lastActiveEditorSnapshot` — the last file-backed editor that had focus before the terminal stole it — so it can always report a meaningful \"active file\" even while the terminal is focused.\n\n### Command\n\nThe extension contributes one command:\n\n- `factory-vscode-extension.openFactory` — opens a new \"Factory\" terminal in the editor area, sends `droid`, then moves it to the side split group. Accessible from the editor title bar icon and the VS Code command palette.\n\n## Integration points\n\n- **CLI** (`apps/cli`): the primary consumer of the MCP server. The CLI connects to `IDEServer` to read open files and diagnostics and to apply diffs. See [apps/cli/index.md](./cli/index.md).\n- **`@modelcontextprotocol/sdk`**: provides `Server`, `StreamableHTTPServerTransport`, tool schema definitions.\n- **VS Code API** (`vscode`): all editor interaction goes through the VS Code extension host API.\n- **JetBrains plugin** (`apps/factory-jetbrains-plugin`): parallel implementation for IntelliJ-family IDEs; same MCP-based architecture.\n\n## Entry points for modification\n\n| What to change | Where to start |\n|---------------|----------------|\n| Add a new MCP tool | `src/ide-server.ts` — `createMcpServer()`, register in `ListToolsRequestSchema` + `CallToolRequestSchema` handlers |\n| Change how diffs are shown | `src/diff-manager.ts` |\n| Track additional VS Code state | `src/open-files-manager.ts` or `src/diagnostics-manager.ts` |\n| Change the terminal launch behavior | `src/extension.ts` — `factory-vscode-extension.openFactory` command handler |\n| Build and install the extension locally | `npm run build:vscode-extension` in `apps/factory-vscode-extension/` |\n| Port discovery logic | `src/lock-file-utils.ts`, `src/lock-file-helpers.ts` |\n",
