            "content": "# Backend REST API endpoints\n\nThe backend is a Next.js 15 app deployed on Vercel. All routes use the App Router and live under `apps/backend/src/app/api/`. Route handlers call `handleRouteMiddleware` (or one of its variants) from `apps/backend/src/app/api/_utils/middleware.ts`, which handles authentication, organisation lookup, role checks, rate limiting, and Sentry scope configuration before invoking the route logic.\n\n## Route groups\n\n| Prefix | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `/api/auth/` | Token verification, WorkOS OAuth actions, integration token storage |\n| `/api/sessions/` | Session CRUD — create, load, search, archive; remediation |\n| `/api/llm/` | LLM proxy — Anthropic, OpenAI, Vertex AI, Bedrock, custom providers |\n| `/api/billing/` | Payment methods, subscription portal, usage limits, overage, extra-usage balance |\n| `/api/integrations/` | OAuth flow helpers, SCM integration data, Slack connection |\n| `/api/github/` | GitHub App installation routes |\n| `/api/webhooks/` | Inbound webhooks from Orb, WorkOS, Jira, Linear, Slack |\n| `/api/organization/` | Org management — members, invitations, seats, settings |\n| `/api/admin/` | Internal-only endpoints for analytics, org management, visualisations |\n| `/api/cron/` | Scheduled background jobs (invoked by Vercel cron) |\n| `/api/daemon/` | Daemon heartbeat |\n| `/api/feature-flags/` | Server-side Statsig flag evaluation |\n| `/api/telemetry/` | Client-side telemetry ingest, OTLP traces |\n| `/api/tools/` | Tool definitions for LLM context |\n| `/api/search/` | Cross-session search |\n| `/api/user/` | User profile reads/writes |\n| `/api/bug-reports/` | Bug report submission |\n| `/api/desktop/` | Desktop app version/download metadata |\n| `/api/health/` | Health check |\n| `/api/v0/` | Legacy versioned routes (analytics, sessions, settings, snapshots, users) |\n\n## Auth and middleware\n\nEvery route handler wraps its logic in one of three middleware helpers:\n\n- **`handleRouteMiddleware`** — standard user routes. Verifies the WorkOS access token or Factory API key (`fk_…`), resolves the organisation from Firestore, checks the user's role, optionally enforces a rate limit, and injects a `RouteCallbackInput` with `user`, `firestoreOrgId`, and `factoryUser`.\n- **`handleAdminRouteMiddleware`** — internal admin routes. Validates a static API key stored in AWS Secrets Manager.\n- **`handleCronMiddleware`** — Vercel cron routes. Verifies the `Authorization: Bearer <CRON_SECRET>` header.\n\nSee [security.md](../security.md) for how authentication and authorisation work end-to-end.\n\n## LLM proxy routes\n\nRoutes under `/api/llm/` are the highest-traffic endpoints. They:\n\n1. Authenticate the caller.\n2. Look up the user's billing tier and check usage limits.\n3. Apply a rate limit (per-user and per-org, enforced via Vercel Firewall).\n4. Translate the request body to the provider's format.\n5. Stream the response back over SSE.\n6. Record token-usage metrics after the stream completes.\n\nThe provider routing logic and provider-specific transformations live in `apps/backend/src/app/api/_utils/llm-proxy/`.\n\n## Webhooks\n\nRoutes under `/api/webhooks/` receive events from external services:\n\n- `/api/webhooks/orb` — billing events (subscription changes, invoice creation)\n- `/api/webhooks/workos` — user/directory sync events\n- `/api/webhooks/jira`, `/api/webhooks/linear`, `/api/webhooks/slack` — integration event notifications\n\nWebhook routes typically skip the standard auth middleware and instead verify the inbound request using an HMAC signature or secret token provided by the external service.\n\n## Cron jobs\n\nCron schedules are declared in `apps/backend/vercel.json`. Jobs are invoked by Vercel on the configured schedule:\n\n| Route | Schedule | Purpose |\n|-------|----------|---------|\n| `/api/cron/sync-orb-usage` | every 15 min | Sync usage metrics to Orb |\n| `/api/cron/refresh-workspace-repo` | every 15 min | Refresh workspace repository data |\n| `/api/cron/process-paid-referrals` | every 15 min | Process pending referral payouts |\n| `/api/cron/sync-extra-usage-balance` | every 10 min | Sync extra-usage balance |\n| `/api/cron/cancel-expiring-trials` | hourly (xx:45) | Cancel trials approaching expiry |\n| `/api/cron/send-trial-end-emails` | hourly (xx:00) | Send trial-end email notifications |\n| `/api/cron/send-user-feedback-emails` | hourly (xx:15) | Send feedback request emails |\n| `/api/cron/sync-workos-seats` | daily 18:00 UTC | Sync WorkOS seat counts |\n| `/api/cron/cancel-unpaid-subscriptions` | hourly (xx:30) | Cancel unpaid subscriptions |\n| `/api/cron/directory-sync` | hourly (xx:45) | Directory sync with WorkOS |\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [API overview](index.md)\n- [Backend app](../apps/backend.md)\n- [Security](../security.md)\n- [Error handling patterns](../how-to-contribute/patterns-and-conventions.md)\n",
