            "content": "# Deployment\n\nFactory's platform components deploy to several targets depending on the component type: Vercel for web apps, Firebase for serverless functions and data, AWS for relay/Lambda infrastructure, and S3/GitHub Releases for binary distribution.\n\n## Environments\n\n| Environment | Branch | Purpose |\n|-------------|--------|---------|\n| `preview` | feature branches / PRs to `dev` | Per-PR Vercel preview URLs |\n| `staging` (dev) | `dev` | Integration environment; latest merged code |\n| `preprod` | PRs to `main` | Pre-production validation before production push |\n| `production` | `main` | Live user traffic |\n\nDesktop and daemon/CLI binaries use the same environment names but with slightly different semantics — `staging` uses production-like builds pointing at staging backends.\n\n## Vercel (backend, web, admin)\n\nThree Next.js / Vite applications deploy to Vercel:\n\n| App | Project | Deployed on |\n|-----|---------|-------------|\n| `apps/backend` | `backend` | Every push to `dev`/`main`, every PR |\n| `apps/web` | `web` | Every push to `dev`/`main`, every PR |\n| `apps/admin` | `admin` | Every push to `main`, PRs to `main` |\n\nDeployment is driven by GitHub Actions workflows:\n\n- `.github/workflows/deploy-dev-web.yml` — deploys `apps/web` on PRs and pushes to `dev`.\n- `.github/workflows/deploy-prod.yml` — reusable workflow called by other workflows for `backend` and `admin` on `main`/PRs-to-`main`.\n- `.github/workflows/deploy-prod-app.yml`, `deploy-prod-admin.yml` — callers of the reusable workflow.\n\nFor PR builds, the web app derives its backend URL from the branch name automatically (e.g. a branch `fix/foo-bar` points to `backend-git-fix-foo-bar-factory-ai.vercel.app`).\n\nEnvironment variables are managed in Vercel's project settings and pulled at build time with `vercel pull`. `.env` files are deleted before builds so only Vercel-managed variables are used.\n\n## Firebase (functions, Firestore)\n\n`apps/functions` contains Firebase Cloud Functions. Firebase Hosting is not used for the main web app — only Vercel.\n\nFirestore is the primary datastore. Schema changes (indexes, rules) are maintained via `firestore.indexes.json` and `firestore.rules` at the repo root and deployed with the Firebase CLI.\n\n## AWS infrastructure (relay, Lambda, E2B)\n\nAWS infrastructure is managed with OpenTofu (Terraform-compatible) in `infra/`. Key components:\n\n- **Relay** — a WebSocket relay service (`@factory/relay`) that proxies connections between clients and remote daemon instances. Deployed as Lambda + API Gateway via `.github/workflows/deploy-relay-aws.yml` on pushes to `dev`/`main`.\n- **E2B sandbox templates** — deployed via `.github/workflows/e2b-template-deploy.yml`.\n- **S3 buckets** — used for binary distribution and static asset hosting.\n- **IAM / SSO** — managed via `infra/env/aws/` OpenTofu modules.\n\nThe `infra/` directory is divided into:\n\n- `infra/backend/` — S3 state bucket and DynamoDB lock table\n- `infra/resource-setup/` (modules) — VPC, subnets, IAM, per-environment resources\n- `infra/env/` — environment-specific overrides (aws, gcp, github, snyk, etc.)\n\nOpenTofu is run in CI via `.github/workflows/opentofu.yml`, which plans and applies on PRs / pushes.\n\n## Desktop app distribution\n\nThe Electron desktop app is built and distributed via `.github/workflows/desktop-release.yml`. The workflow:\n\n1. Detects the target environment based on the triggering branch/event.\n2. Builds platform-specific installers (macOS, Windows) using Electron Forge.\n3. Uploads binaries to S3.\n4. Signs macOS builds with an Apple Developer certificate.\n\nThe app uses Squirrel auto-update, polling S3 for new releases.\n\n## CLI and daemon binary distribution\n\nCLI and daemon releases are coordinated by the release automation:\n\n1. `.github/workflows/release-bump-version.yml` — bumps versions in `package.json` files and opens a bump PR.\n2. `.github/workflows/release-cut.yml` — merges into a release branch and opens a PR to `main`.\n3. `.github/workflows/cli-release.yml` — builds the Bun SEA binary and uploads to S3 / GitHub Releases.\n4. `.github/workflows/factoryd-release.yml` — same for the daemon binary.\n5. `.github/workflows/cli-release-npm.yml` — publishes the CLI wrapper to npm.\n\n## CI/CD overview\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    PR[\"PR opened / push\"] --> Checks[\"Lint, typecheck, tests\\n(basic-checks, test, typecheck)\"]\n    Checks --> PreviewDeploy[\"Preview deploy\\n(web, backend on Vercel)\"]\n    Merge[\"Merge to dev\"] --> StagingDeploy[\"Staging deploy\\n(web, backend, relay)\"]\n    StagingDeploy --> DesktopStaging[\"Desktop staging build\"]\n    PRToMain[\"PR to main\"] --> PreprodDeploy[\"Preprod deploy\"]\n    MergeMain[\"Merge to main\"] --> ProdDeploy[\"Production deploy\\n(web, backend, admin)\"]\n    ProdDeploy --> DesktopProd[\"Desktop production build\"]\n    ProdDeploy --> CLIRelease[\"CLI / daemon release\"]\n```\n\n55 workflows live in `.github/workflows/`. Key workflows beyond deployment:\n\n- `pr-conventions.yml` — enforces Conventional Commits title format.\n- `playwright-e2e.yml` / `playwright-e2e-critical.yml` — end-to-end browser tests.\n- `cli-e2e-tests.yml` — TUI-based CLI integration tests.\n- `opentofu.yml` — infrastructure plan/apply.\n- `semantic-diff.yml` — PR diff summaries.\n- `sync-feature-flags.yml` — syncs Statsig flag definitions.\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [System architecture](../overview/architecture.md)\n- [Backend app](../apps/backend.md)\n- [Reference: environment variables](../reference/configuration.md)\n",
