            "content": "# Monitoring overview\n\nFactory uses a layered observability stack: structured logs shipped to **Axiom**, error and exception tracking in **Sentry**, and custom metrics recorded via the `@factory/logging` package.\n\n## What we observe\n\n| Signal | Tool | Where |\n|--------|------|--------|\n| Exceptions and errors | Sentry | Backend, daemon, CLI, web |\n| Structured logs | Axiom (via pino JSON output) | Backend, daemon, CLI |\n| Custom metrics (counters, histograms) | Axiom | Backend, daemon, CLI |\n| Distributed traces (OTLP) | Axiom traces | Backend (opt-in via `FACTORY_OTEL_ENABLED`) |\n| Frontend telemetry | Backend `/api/telemetry/` endpoint | Web / desktop |\n\n## Components\n\n### Sentry\n\nAll major components initialise a Sentry client at startup:\n\n- Backend: `apps/backend/sentry.server.config.ts` + `apps/backend/src/instrumentation.ts`\n- Daemon: `apps/daemon/src/sentry.config.ts`\n- CLI: `apps/cli/src/sentry.config.ts`\n\nSentry captures unhandled exceptions and errors logged via `logException`. It is enabled when `SENTRY_DSN` is present in the environment. See [logging.md](logging.md) for integration details.\n\n### Logging / Axiom\n\nLogs are written as structured JSON using [pino](https://getpino.io). In production they are ingested by Axiom. See [logging.md](logging.md) for how to add log statements and what log levels are available.\n\n### Metrics\n\nCustom metrics are emitted alongside logs as structured JSON with a `[metric:` prefix. Axiom queries extract the metric name and value fields. See [metrics.md](metrics.md) for the metrics API and available metric types.\n\n### OpenTelemetry (backend)\n\nThe backend optionally exports distributed traces to Axiom via OTLP HTTP when `FACTORY_OTEL_ENABLED=true`. Trace context (trace ID, span ID) is attached to log lines so logs and traces can be correlated.\n\n## Sub-pages\n\n- [Logging](logging.md) — log functions, secret scrubbing, Sentry breadcrumbs, dev log locations.\n- [Metrics](metrics.md) — metrics API, counters/histograms/gauges, Axiom.\n",
