            "content": "# Features\n\n**Active contributors**: Arman Bolat, Luke Alvoeiro, theo, Eno Reyes, David Vendrow, Alvin Sng\n\n## Overview\n\nThis section documents the cross-cutting capabilities of the Factory platform — features that span multiple apps and packages rather than belonging to a single deployable unit.\n\nEach page describes the feature from the user's perspective: what it does, how to use it, and how it connects to the underlying implementation. For implementation details, follow the cross-links to the relevant app and package pages.\n\n## Feature pages\n\n| Feature | Description |\n|---|---|\n| [Sessions](./sessions.md) | Creating, resuming, forking, and searching conversation sessions; JSONL on-disk storage; per-session settings |\n| [LLM integration](./llm-integration.md) | Supported LLM providers, streaming protocol, BYOK, model selection, proxy flow through the backend |\n| [Skills](./skills.md) | Reusable prompt-context files that teach Droid workflows; built-in vs user skills; the `/create-skill` command |\n| [MCP integration](./mcp-integration.md) | Model Context Protocol servers that give the agent executable tools; configuration, transport types, OAuth |\n| [Missions](./missions.md) | Long-running autonomous tasks; orchestrator + worker sessions; the `/enter-mission` and `/exit-mission` commands |\n| [Wiki generation](./wiki-generation.md) | The `/wiki` skill, `droid wiki-upload` command, and the wiki viewer in the web app |\n| [Automations](./automations.md) | Scheduled, autonomous Droid runs defined by `HEARTBEAT.md` files; lifecycle management in the web UI |\n| [IDE integrations](./ide-integrations.md) | VS Code and JetBrains plugins that feed file context and diagnostics into the CLI agent |\n| [Feature flags](./feature-flags.md) | Statsig-backed feature gates; how to define flags in `@factory/common`, check them on frontend and backend |\n\n## Architecture context\n\nAll features run on top of the core [system architecture](../overview/architecture.md). The agent loop inside the CLI drives most interactive features; the backend LLM proxy mediates every model call. See [apps/daemon.md](../apps/daemon.md) for how the web and desktop clients participate in sessions, and [apps/backend.md](../apps/backend.md) for the LLM proxy and API endpoints that features rely on.\n",
