            "content": "# LLM integration\n\n**Active contributors**: l30t, Abhay Singhal, Leo Tchourakov, David Vendrow, Stepan, Alvin Sng\n\n## Purpose\n\nDroid communicates with large language models through a proxy architecture. The CLI sends requests to the Factory backend proxy, which authenticates with the upstream provider and streams tokens back. This lets the platform route across providers (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google, AWS Bedrock, etc.) without the client needing individual API keys. BYOK (Bring Your Own Key) users can bypass the proxy and talk directly to Anthropic.\n\n## Supported providers and models\n\nModels are identified by the `ModelID` enum in `packages/common/src/llm/enums.ts`. Each `ModelID` maps to a specific provider:\n\n| Provider family | Example models |\n|---|---|\n| Anthropic (direct, Bedrock, Vertex) | Claude Sonnet 4.6, Claude Opus 4.6, Claude Haiku 4.5 |\n| OpenAI / Azure OpenAI | GPT-5.4, GPT-5.4 Fast, GPT-5.1-Codex |\n| Google (Vertex AI) | Gemini 2.5 Pro, Gemini 2.5 Flash, Gemini 3 Pro |\n| xAI | Grok Code Fast 1 |\n| Fireworks | Open-source models routed through Fireworks |\n| Baseten | Custom hosted models |\n\nThe backend translates `ModelID` values to provider-specific model strings in `apps/backend/src/features/llm/model-ids.ts`, keeping those strings server-side to avoid leaking unreleased model IDs to clients.\n\n## Proxy flow\n\nAll model traffic (except BYOK) goes through the Factory backend:\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant CLI as CLI / daemon\n    participant Proxy as Backend /api/llm/*\n    participant Validate as validateProxyRequest\n    participant Provider as LLM provider\n\n    CLI->>Proxy: POST messages + model ID + session headers\n    Proxy->>Validate: auth, billing pool check, model mapping\n    Validate-->>Proxy: apiProvider, apiProviderModelId\n    Proxy->>Provider: provider-specific request\n    Provider-->>Proxy: SSE token stream\n    Proxy-->>CLI: SSE pass-through\n    Proxy->>Proxy: recordMessageUsage (tokens, model, org)\n```\n\nThree proxy route families cover different provider APIs:\n- `/api/llm/a/v1/messages` — Anthropic-compatible (routes to Anthropic, Vertex, Bedrock, or Fireworks)\n- `/api/llm/o/v1/chat/completions` — OpenAI chat completions\n- `/api/llm/g/v1/` — Google Gemini\n\nThe `x-api-provider` request header tells the proxy which provider to use for the current turn.\n\n## Provider rotation (Anthropic family)\n\nFor Claude models the CLI rotates across available backend providers (`ANTHROPIC`, `VERTEX_ANTHROPIC`, `BEDROCK_ANTHROPIC`) to distribute load and handle rate-limit failures. `getNextAnthropicProvider()` in `apps/cli/src/llm-proxy/utils.ts` implements round-robin rotation with these rules:\n\n- Feature flags (`UseAnthropicBedrock`, `UseAnthropicVertex`) control which providers are in the rotation for a given org.\n- Model-specific flags (e.g., `UseOpus46Bedrock`) override the global routing for newly launched models.\n- If a `lockedProvider` is set in session settings, no rotation occurs.\n- Fireworks-hosted models (`FIREWORKS` API provider) are always pinned and never rotated.\n\n## Streaming protocol\n\nThe CLI consumes token streams using the Anthropic SDK streaming interface for Claude models and the OpenAI SDK for OpenAI/Gemini models. Both are implemented in `apps/cli/src/hooks/createLLMStreamingCore.ts` (the core logic) and wrapped by `apps/cli/src/hooks/useLLMStreaming.ts` (the React hook for TUI use).\n\nChunk processing functions (`processAnthropicChunk`, `processOpenAIChunk`, `processGeminiSSEChunk`) normalize provider-specific delta formats into internal `StreamingResult` objects that the agent loop consumes uniformly.\n\nThinking tokens (extended reasoning, chain-of-thought) are handled through `ThinkingBlock` content blocks in the Anthropic protocol. These are stored in session messages and can optionally be shown in the TUI.\n\n## BYOK (Bring Your Own Key)\n\nUsers on the BYOK plan supply their own Anthropic API key. When the backend detects a BYOK user, it forwards the request directly to Anthropic using the user's key, bypassing Factory's token pools. No model ID translation occurs; the request goes as-is to `api.anthropic.com`.\n\nBYOK is Anthropic-only. Users cannot currently supply their own OpenAI or Gemini keys.\n\n## Model selection\n\nUsers change the active model with `/model` in the TUI, which opens the model selector overlay. Available models are filtered by:\n\n- Feature flags — some models are behind gates (e.g., `Alto0204`, `Glacier0205`, `OlM0305`)\n- Org plan — certain model tiers require the Ultra plan\n- Session type — Mission orchestrator sessions use `MISSION_ORCHESTRATOR_MODEL` by default\n\n`ReasoningEffort` (off / low / medium / high / xhigh / max) controls the thinking budget for models that support extended reasoning (Claude 3.7+ and newer, OpenAI o-series).\n\n## Dynamic config\n\nThe `DEFAULT_MODEL_OVERRIDE` dynamic config in Statsig can push a default model and reasoning effort to all CLI users without a code deploy. The CLI reads this at startup and applies it if the user has not set a personal preference.\n\n## Integration points\n\n| Component | Relationship |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/cli/src/hooks/createLLMStreamingCore.ts` | Core streaming implementation for all providers |\n| `apps/cli/src/hooks/useLLMStreaming.ts` | React hook wrapping streaming core for TUI |\n| `apps/cli/src/llm-proxy/utils.ts` | Provider rotation and proxy header construction |\n| `apps/backend/src/app/api/llm/` | Backend proxy route handlers |\n| `apps/backend/src/features/llm/model-ids.ts` | `ModelID` → provider model string mapping |\n| `packages/common/src/llm/enums.ts` | `ModelID`, `ApiProvider`, `ModelProvider`, `ReasoningEffort` enums |\n| [features/feature-flags.md](./feature-flags.md) | Model routing gates (`UseAnthropicBedrock`, model-specific flags) |\n| [apps/backend.md](../apps/backend.md) | Full backend LLM proxy description |\n",
            "file_path": "/Users/jonathanlucuix-andre/Documents/test-repos/factory-mono/droid-wiki/features/llm-integration.md"
          },
