            "content": "# Skills\n\n**Active contributors**: theo, Arman Bolat, Luke Alvoeiro, Eno Reyes, David Vendrow, Abhay Singhal\n\n## Purpose\n\nA skill is a reusable prompt-context file that teaches Droid a workflow or domain capability. When a skill is invoked, its content is injected into the agent's context at the start of the conversation, shaping how the agent approaches the task. Skills are distinct from MCP tools: skills provide *instructions*, MCP tools provide *executable functions*.\n\nFor implementation details see [apps/cli/skills.md](../apps/cli/skills.md).\n\n## Skill file format\n\nA skill is always a directory containing a `SKILL.md` file with YAML frontmatter:\n\n```markdown\n---\nname: summarize-diff\ndescription: Summarize the staged git diff in 3-5 bullets. Use when the user asks for a summary of pending changes.\nenabled: true\nuserInvocable: true\n---\n\n# Summarize Diff\n\n## Instructions\n\n1. Run `git diff --staged`.\n2. Summarize the changes in 3-5 bullets, focusing on user-visible behavior.\n```\n\nKey frontmatter fields:\n\n| Field | Default | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `name` | (required) | Unique identifier and slash-command name |\n| `description` | (required) | One-to-two sentence summary used for skill discovery |\n| `enabled` | `true` | Whether the skill loads at startup |\n| `userInvocable` | `true` | Whether the skill registers as a `/name` slash command |\n\nThe directory may also contain supporting scripts, schemas, checklists, and a `references.md`.\n\n## Where skills live\n\n| Scope | Path | Sharing |\n|---|---|---|\n| Project | `<repo>/.factory/skills/<skill-name>/SKILL.md` | Committed to git; shared with the team |\n| Personal | `~/.factory/skills/<skill-name>/SKILL.md` | Local to your machine; private |\n\nBoth locations are merged at startup. Project skills take precedence on name conflicts.\n\n## Built-in skills\n\nSkills bundled inside the CLI binary live in `apps/cli/src/skills/builtin/constants.ts` and `apps/cli/src/skills/builtin/index.ts`. They are loaded alongside user skills and are always available regardless of the local `.factory/skills/` directory. Examples include `tuistory` (TUI test automation) and `agent-browser` (browser automation via Playwright).\n\n## Invoking a skill\n\n**Via slash command** — type `/skill-name` in the TUI prompt. The skill's content is prepended to the conversation and the agent runs.\n\n**Via `/skills`** — lists all registered skills with their descriptions. Useful for discovering what's available.\n\n**In exec mode** — skill content can be embedded in the system prompt passed to `droid exec`. There is no slash-command UX in exec mode.\n\n## Creating a skill\n\n`/create-skill <description>` starts a guided skill-creation workflow:\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant U as User\n    participant C as /create-skill\n    participant A as AgentLoop\n    participant FS as File system\n\n    U->>C: /create-skill \"query axiom logs\"\n    C->>C: Build multi-block instruction message\n    C->>A: Run agent with instructions + docs + existing-skills list\n    A->>FS: Search past sessions for evidence\n    A->>U: Propose skill spec (evidence table)\n    A->>FS: Write .factory/skills/<name>/SKILL.md\n    A->>U: Confirm: run /skills to verify\n```\n\nThe creation instructions (in `apps/cli/src/commands/create-skill.ts`) require the agent to:\n- Search past sessions for evidence before writing anything\n- Produce a findings table with quoted citations\n- Consider supporting scripts or schemas alongside `SKILL.md`\n- Never fabricate findings from a single session\n\n## The skills in this repository\n\nThe `~/.factory/skills/` directory for this monorepo is populated with project-specific skills. Each skill is a directory under `.factory/skills/` with its own `SKILL.md`. Notable examples:\n\n- `add-llm-model` — procedure for wiring in a new LLM provider\n- `create-pr` — Factory-specific PR creation checklist\n- `frontend-ui-development` — conventions for building UI using `@factory/core-ui`\n- `wiki` — the wiki generation skill (described in [features/wiki-generation.md](./wiki-generation.md))\n\n## Integration points\n\n| Component | Relationship |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/cli/src/commands/skills/SkillCommandsLoader.ts` | Registers skills as slash commands at startup |\n| `apps/cli/src/commands/create-skill.ts` | `/create-skill` command handler |\n| `apps/cli/src/skills/builtin/` | Built-in skill constants embedded in the binary |\n| `@factory/services/settings` (SettingsManager) | Resolves and validates skills from both personal and project directories |\n| [apps/cli/skills.md](../apps/cli/skills.md) | Implementation deep-dive |\n| [features/mcp-integration.md](./mcp-integration.md) | MCP tools complement skills by providing executable functions |\n",
