            "content": "# Missions\n\n**Active contributors**: theo, David Vendrow, factory-daniel, Alvin Sng, Qingchen Dang, Eno Reyes\n\n## Purpose\n\nA Mission (also called AGI mode or Project Colossus) is a long-running autonomous task where Droid works through a large, multi-step goal without continuous user involvement. The orchestrator session plans the work and breaks it into features, then spawns sequential worker sessions that each execute one feature. The user monitors progress through the MissionControl TUI and can intervene when the agent needs guidance.\n\n## When to use missions\n\nMissions are appropriate when a task:\n- Spans multiple files, packages, or subsystems\n- Would take more turns than a normal conversation can hold\n- Benefits from a planning phase before execution begins\n- Can be decomposed into discrete, independently verifiable units of work\n\nSmaller, focused tasks are better handled in a regular conversation.\n\n## Entering mission mode\n\nIn the TUI, type `/enter-mission`. This:\n\n1. Upgrades the current session's `decompSessionType` to `Orchestrator`\n2. Sets the interaction mode to `AGI`\n3. Switches to a high-reasoning model (`MISSION_ORCHESTRATOR_MODEL`) if the current model is not in the recommended list\n\nThe model selector shows a simplified \"mission model picker\" in orchestrator mode, limiting choices to models with sufficient reasoning capability.\n\n## Exiting mission mode\n\n`/exit-mission` returns to a normal session. If a full mission was started (a `state.json` and `mission.md` were created), exiting creates a fresh session. If the session was upgraded to orchestrator mode but no mission work was done, it downgrades back to a regular session in place.\n\n## Mission on-disk layout\n\nEach mission is stored under `~/.factory/missions/<baseSessionId>/`:\n\n```\n~/.factory/missions/<baseSessionId>/\n├── mission.md          # Mission brief (title + objectives)\n├── state.json          # Machine-managed state file (current phase, feature IDs, worker PIDs)\n├── features.json       # Ordered list of features with status\n├── handoffs.jsonl      # Worker → orchestrator handoff records\n└── progress-log.jsonl  # Timeline of events (worker started/completed, validation results)\n```\n\nThe `state.json` file is updated by `MissionFileService` (`apps/cli/src/services/mission/MissionFileService.ts`) and is never written directly by the LLM.\n\n## Orchestrator and worker sessions\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    O[Orchestrator session] -->|spawns| W1[Worker session: Feature 1]\n    W1 -->|completes; handoff| O\n    O -->|spawns| W2[Worker session: Feature 2]\n    W2 -->|completes; handoff| O\n    O -->|spawns| W3[Worker session: Feature 3]\n    W3 -->|needs input; pauses| O\n    O -->|user resolves; resumes| W3\n    W3 -->|completes| O\n    O -->|all features done| D[Mission complete]\n```\n\nThe orchestrator session holds the `MissionRunner` which manages the worker lifecycle via `apps/cli/src/services/mission/MissionRunner.ts`. Each worker runs in a non-interactive exec session and reports results back through the mission file system.\n\n## Mission states\n\n`MissionState` (from `@factory/common/droid`) tracks the current phase:\n\n| State | Meaning |\n|---|---|\n| `planning` | Orchestrator is decomposing the goal into features |\n| `running` | A worker session is executing a feature |\n| `paused` | Worker requested human input or ran into a blocker |\n| `awaiting_input` | Orchestrator is waiting for user confirmation to proceed |\n| `completed` | All features finished successfully |\n| `failed` | Mission aborted due to unrecoverable error |\n\n## Resuming a mission\n\n`/missions` opens a picker listing all known missions with their state and last-modified time. Selecting a mission resumes the orchestrator session from where it left off. Worker sessions can also be resumed individually from the `/sessions` picker.\n\n## MissionControl TUI\n\nDuring execution, the TUI switches to a mission-specific view that shows:\n- The mission brief and feature list\n- The currently running worker's progress\n- Handoff summaries from completed workers\n- Pause/resume controls\n- Token usage across the orchestrator and all workers\n\nThe frontend mission components in `packages/frontend/src/features/missions/` provide the same view in the web and desktop clients, driven by `MissionNotification` events streamed from the daemon.\n\n## Integration points\n\n| Component | Relationship |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/cli/src/commands/enter-mission.ts` | `/enter-mission` slash command |\n| `apps/cli/src/commands/exit-mission.ts` | `/exit-mission` slash command |\n| `apps/cli/src/commands/missions.ts` | `/missions` picker command |\n| `apps/cli/src/services/mission/MissionRunner.ts` | Worker session lifecycle management |\n| `apps/cli/src/services/mission/MissionFileService.ts` | Reads and writes mission state files |\n| `packages/frontend/src/features/missions/` | Web/desktop mission UI components |\n| `@factory/common/droid` | `MissionState`, `MissionFeature`, and notification types |\n| [features/sessions.md](./sessions.md) | Worker sessions are regular sessions with `decompSessionType = Worker` |\n| [apps/cli/index.md](../apps/cli/index.md) | CLI overview including exec mode that workers use |\n",
