            "content": "# Wiki generation\n\n**Active contributors**: jonathan-factory, Eno Reyes, Andrei Savin, factory-davidgu\n\n## Purpose\n\nDroid can generate a structured documentation wiki for any repository and publish it to the Factory web app for browsing. The workflow has two phases: generating markdown files locally with the `/wiki` skill, then uploading them with `droid wiki-upload`.\n\n## The `/wiki` skill\n\nThe `wiki` skill lives at `.factory/skills/wiki/SKILL.md`. Invoking `/wiki` in the TUI starts the generation workflow, which:\n\n1. **Surveys the repo** — two-pass scan (structural: README, package.json, entry points, CI; deep: feature flags, route definitions, service classes)\n2. **Plans the table of contents** — assigns pages to tiers (critical/normal), decides which lenses to use (apps, features, packages, etc.)\n3. **Delegates to sub-agents** — parallelizes page generation across multiple agent invocations\n4. **Assembles** — audits cross-links, writes `.wiki-meta.json` with the page order for sidebar display\n\nOutput lands in `droid-wiki/` at the repo root (or a temporary directory if `--no-local` is requested).\n\n## Page format\n\nEach page is a markdown file that follows a standard structure:\n\n- Level-1 heading (extracted as the page title by the uploader)\n- **Active contributors** byline (derived from `git log origin/dev`)\n- **Purpose** — 2-3 sentences\n- **Directory layout** (when relevant)\n- **Key abstractions** table\n- **How it works** section with Mermaid diagrams for flows involving 3+ components\n- **Integration points** table\n- **Entry points for modification**\n\n## The `.wiki-meta.json` file\n\nThe wiki root always contains `.wiki-meta.json`. The `pageOrder` array controls the sidebar display order in the web viewer:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"generatedAt\": \"2025-01-15T10:30:00Z\",\n  \"pageCount\": 42,\n  \"pageOrder\": [\n    \"overview/index.md\",\n    \"overview/architecture.md\",\n    \"features/index.md\",\n    \"features/sessions.md\"\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nWithout this file, pages sort alphabetically. The uploader passes the `pageTree` structure derived from `pageOrder` to the API.\n\n## The `droid wiki-upload` command\n\n`apps/cli/src/commands/wiki-upload.ts` implements the upload command:\n\n```bash\ndroid wiki-upload \\\n  --repo-url https://github.com/Factory-AI/factory-mono \\\n  --wiki-dir ./droid-wiki \\\n  [--cleanup]     # delete wiki-dir on success\n  [--session-id <id>]  # associate upload with a session\n```\n\nThe upload process:\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant CLI as droid wiki-upload\n    participant FS as File system\n    participant API as /api/v0/wiki\n\n    CLI->>FS: findMarkdownFiles(wikiDir)\n    CLI->>FS: readPageOrderFromWikiMeta(wikiDir)\n    CLI->>CLI: buildPageTree(files, wikiDir, pageOrder)\n    CLI->>CLI: resolveGitMetadata (commit hash, branch, local changes)\n    CLI->>API: POST CreateWikiRunRequest\n    API-->>CLI: { wikiRunId }\n    CLI->>FS: rmSync(wikiDir) if --cleanup\n```\n\n`buildPageTree` groups files by directory, applies the order from `.wiki-meta.json`, and produces a `PageTreeNode[]` hierarchy that becomes the sidebar. `generatePageId` converts file paths to URL-safe IDs (slashes become `--`).\n\n## Wiki viewer in the web app\n\nThe wiki viewer lives in `packages/frontend/src/features/wiki/`. The index page (`WikiPage`, `packages/frontend/src/features/wiki/pages/Wiki.page.tsx`) lists repositories that have been uploaded, gated by the `Wiki` feature flag. Clicking a repository opens the reader (`WikiReader.page.tsx`), which renders the selected page's markdown and shows the sidebar tree.\n\nWiki runs are fetched via `useQueryWikiRuns` (a React Query hook) from `/api/v0/wiki`. The viewer is available at `/wiki` in the web app.\n\nThe `Wiki` feature flag must be enabled for the organization to see the wiki UI.\n\n## Integration points\n\n| Component | Relationship |\n|---|---|\n| `.factory/skills/wiki/SKILL.md` | The skill that drives wiki generation in the CLI |\n| `apps/cli/src/commands/wiki-upload.ts` | Upload command implementation |\n| `packages/frontend/src/features/wiki/` | Web UI: index page and markdown reader |\n| `packages/common/src/wiki/` | `WikiPage`, `PageTreeNode` types shared between CLI and backend |\n| `packages/common/src/api/v0/wiki/` | `CreateWikiRunRequest` API type |\n| `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts` | `Wiki` feature flag that gates the viewer |\n| [features/feature-flags.md](./feature-flags.md) | How the `Wiki` gate is checked in the frontend |\n| [apps/backend.md](../apps/backend.md) | `/api/v0/wiki` endpoint that stores wiki runs |\n",
