            "content": "# Automations\n\n**Active contributors**: Eno Reyes, shashank-factory, jonathan-factory, factory-jerry, Andrei Savin\n\n## Purpose\n\nAutomations are scheduled, autonomous Droid runs that execute on a cron schedule without user interaction. Each automation is defined by a `HEARTBEAT.md` file that describes what Droid should do. The automation engine runs the agent against those instructions and stores the output in structured files under the automation directory.\n\nThe `Automations` feature flag must be enabled for the organization to use this feature.\n\n## On-disk layout\n\nEach automation is a directory under `.factory/automations/<id>/`:\n\n```\n.factory/automations/<id>/\n├── HEARTBEAT.md        # Automation definition with YAML frontmatter\n├── VISUAL.html         # Latest visual output from execution (optional)\n├── memory/             # Persistent memory files (*.json) the agent reads/writes\n└── reports/            # Execution reports (*.md) generated per run\n```\n\n### HEARTBEAT.md format\n\n```markdown\n---\nname: Daily error digest\ndescription: Summarize production errors from the last 24 hours\nschedule: daily\nmodel: claude-sonnet-4-6\ntags: [monitoring, errors]\npaused: false\n---\n\n# Daily error digest\n\nQuery Axiom for error logs from the past 24 hours and produce\na markdown report grouped by error type.\n```\n\nFrontmatter fields:\n\n| Field | Required | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `name` | yes | Human-readable display name |\n| `description` | no | Optional description |\n| `schedule` | yes | Named cadence (`daily`, `weekly`, `monthly`) or cron expression |\n| `model` | no | Model ID to use; falls back to org default |\n| `tags` | no | Categorization tags |\n| `paused` | no | When `true`, automation won't run on schedule |\n\n## Automation lifecycle\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    A[HEARTBEAT.md created] --> B[Automation discovered]\n    B --> C{Schedule fires}\n    C --> D[CLI exec session created]\n    D --> E[Agent runs HEARTBEAT instructions]\n    E --> F[Report written to reports/]\n    F --> G{Error?}\n    G -- repeated failures --> H[Status: Degraded]\n    G -- success --> I[Status: Active]\n    H --> J[User fixes HEARTBEAT.md]\n    J --> I\n    I --> C\n```\n\nAutomations are discovered by scanning `.factory/automations/` for directories that contain a parseable `HEARTBEAT.md`. Invalid automations (missing file, bad frontmatter, invalid schedule) are shown in the UI with their validation issues so users can fix them.\n\n## Automation statuses\n\n| Status | Meaning |\n|---|---|\n| `active` | Running on schedule |\n| `paused` | Will not run on schedule; can be run manually |\n| `degraded` | Repeated failures; needs attention |\n\n## Web UI\n\nThe automations feature in `packages/frontend/src/features/automations/` provides:\n- **List panel** — shows all automations with status, schedule, and last-run info\n- **Detail panel** — shows the automation config, run history, controls (run now, pause, resume), and the latest visual output\n- **Visual viewer** — renders the `VISUAL.html` output inline\n- **Create modal** — guided flow to scaffold a new automation with a name, schedule, and description\n\nThese components are wired up in `packages/frontend/src/features/automations/pages/` and communicate with the daemon's automation control-plane via React Query hooks in `packages/frontend/src/features/automations/queries/`.\n\n## Control-plane\n\nThe daemon exposes an automation control-plane with JSON-RPC methods for:\n- Listing automations (with valid/invalid separation)\n- Triggering a manual run\n- Pausing and resuming schedules\n- Fetching run history\n- Retrieving visual output\n\nError codes (`AutomationErrorCode`) provide machine-readable failure reasons:\n\n| Code | Meaning |\n|---|---|\n| `AUTOMATION_NOT_FOUND` | No automation with that ID |\n| `RUN_IN_PROGRESS` | Already running; cannot start another |\n| `INVALID_AUTOMATION_CONFIG` | Bad schedule or missing required fields |\n| `EXECUTION_FAILED` | The Droid session exited with an error |\n\n## Integration points\n\n| Component | Relationship |\n|---|---|\n| `packages/common/src/automations/types.ts` | Request/response types for the control-plane |\n| `packages/common/src/automations/enums.ts` | `AutomationStatus`, `AutomationRunStatus`, `AutomationErrorCode` |\n| `packages/droid-core/src/automations/` | Core automation discovery and execution logic |\n| `packages/frontend/src/features/automations/` | Web/desktop UI components |\n| [features/sessions.md](./sessions.md) | Each automation run creates an exec-mode session |\n| [features/feature-flags.md](./feature-flags.md) | `Automations` flag gates the feature |\n| [apps/daemon.md](../apps/daemon.md) | Daemon schedules automation runs and exposes the control-plane |\n",
