            "content": "# IDE integrations\n\n**Active contributors**: Arman Bolat, Alvin Sng, Eno Reyes, Varin Nair, factory-jerry\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe VS Code and JetBrains plugins connect the IDE to the Droid CLI so the agent can see what the developer is looking at — open files, the current cursor selection, and lint diagnostics. This context is automatically injected into conversations without the user needing to paste code.\n\n## Supported IDEs\n\n| IDE | Package | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| VS Code (and forks: Cursor, Windsurf) | `apps/factory-vscode-extension/` | MCP HTTP server inside the extension |\n| JetBrains (IntelliJ, PyCharm, etc.) | `apps/factory-jetbrains-plugin/` | MCP HTTP server inside the plugin |\n\n## Architecture\n\nBoth integrations follow the same pattern: the IDE plugin runs a local MCP HTTP server, and the CLI connects to it as a system MCP client.\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant IDE as VS Code / JetBrains\n    participant Server as IDE MCP server (HTTP)\n    participant CLI as Droid CLI\n    participant Agent as Agent loop\n\n    IDE->>Server: Extension activated\n    Server->>Server: Start HTTP server on dynamic port\n    Server->>IDE: Write lock file (port + workspace info)\n    CLI->>CLI: IdeContextManager reads lock file\n    CLI->>Server: MCP connect (StreamableHTTPClientTransport)\n    Server-->>CLI: Connected\n    IDE->>Server: User changes file / selection\n    Server->>CLI: notifications/activeFile\n    CLI->>Agent: Inject file context into system prompt\n    Agent->>Server: callTool (e.g., open_diff, apply_changes)\n    Server->>IDE: Apply changes in editor\n```\n\n## Lock files\n\nWhen the extension starts, it writes a lock file that tells the CLI where to connect. The CLI's `IdeContextManager` (`apps/cli/src/services/IdeContextManager.ts`) reads lock files from a well-known directory to discover running IDE instances.\n\nPriority order for connection:\n1. `FACTORY_VSCODE_MCP_PORT` environment variable (set when launching the CLI from inside VS Code)\n2. `FACTORY_JETBRAINS_MCP_PORT` environment variable\n3. Lock file scan (for connecting from an external terminal)\n\n## VS Code extension\n\n`apps/factory-vscode-extension/src/extension.ts` activates the extension and starts `IDEServer` (`apps/factory-vscode-extension/src/ide-server.ts`), an MCP server with these managers:\n\n| Manager | File | What it tracks |\n|---|---|---|\n| `OpenFilesManager` | `open-files-manager.ts` | Active file, open file list, cursor selection |\n| `DiagnosticsManager` | `diagnostics-manager.ts` | TypeScript/lint errors per file |\n| `DiffManager` | `diff-manager.ts` | Pending diffs from Droid suggestions |\n\nThe server sends MCP notifications (`notifications/activeFile`, `notifications/openFiles`, `notifications/diagnostics`) to the CLI whenever these change.\n\nTools exposed by the VS Code extension to the agent include diff creation and application, so the agent can propose and preview code changes in the editor before writing them to disk.\n\n## JetBrains plugin\n\n`apps/factory-jetbrains-plugin/` implements the equivalent for IntelliJ-based IDEs. The plugin exposes the same MCP notification protocol as the VS Code extension. The CLI connects to it via `JetBrainsIdeClient` (`apps/cli/src/services/JetBrainsIdeClient.ts`), which shares the same notification schema as `VSCodeIdeClient` but handles JetBrains-specific diagnostics aggregation (the plugin sends both per-file and aggregate diagnostic formats).\n\n## Context injection\n\nWhen a file-change notification arrives, `IdeContextManager` updates its state. The `useIdeContext` hook (`apps/cli/src/hooks/useIdeContext.ts`) reads this state and injects it as a `SYSTEM_REMINDER` block into the conversation. The block includes:\n\n- Current file path and language\n- Selected text (if any)\n- Open file list\n- Active lint diagnostics\n\nThis context is refreshed on every agent turn so the LLM always sees the current state of the editor.\n\n## `/ide` command\n\nThe `/ide` slash command in the TUI shows connection status and lets users:\n- See which IDE instance is connected\n- Disconnect from the current instance\n- Connect to a different instance if multiple IDE lock files are present\n\n## Minimum extension version\n\nThe `MIN_IDE_EXTENSION_VERSION` dynamic Statsig config enforces a minimum plugin version. If the installed extension is too old, the CLI prompts the user to update before connecting.\n\n## Integration points\n\n| Component | Relationship |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/factory-vscode-extension/src/ide-server.ts` | VS Code MCP server implementation |\n| `apps/factory-jetbrains-plugin/src/` | JetBrains plugin |\n| `apps/cli/src/services/VSCodeIdeClient.ts` | CLI MCP client for VS Code |\n| `apps/cli/src/services/JetBrainsIdeClient.ts` | CLI MCP client for JetBrains |\n| `apps/cli/src/services/IdeContextManager.ts` | Singleton that manages connection state and context updates |\n| `apps/cli/src/commands/ide.ts` | `/ide` slash command |\n| [features/mcp-integration.md](./mcp-integration.md) | IDE servers use MCP protocol; the CLI treats them as system MCP servers |\n| [apps/vscode-extension.md](../apps/vscode-extension.md) | Detailed VS Code extension documentation |\n",
