            "content": "# CLI (`apps/cli`)\n\n**Active contributors**: Arman Bolat, Luke Alvoeiro, shashank-factory, theo, Leo Tchourakov, Stepan, Abhay Singhal, David Vendrow\n\n## Purpose\n\n`apps/cli` is the primary distribution point for Droid — the AI software engineering agent. It ships as a Node.js SEA (Single Executable Application) binary named `droid` and supports two fundamentally different operating modes:\n\n1. **Interactive TUI** — a full-screen React/Ink terminal application that renders a chat interface, streams LLM responses, and handles complex keyboard input.\n2. **Exec mode** — a headless, non-interactive command invoked as `droid exec \"prompt\"` that runs a single agent turn and exits with structured output.\n\nBoth modes share the same agent core (`AgentLoop`), session persistence, tool registry, and MCP integration. The mode is selected at startup based on whether arguments are present.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/cli/\n├── src/\n│   ├── index.ts              # Entry point: mode detection, bootstrap, Commander setup\n│   ├── main.tsx              # TUI entry: Ink render() + lifecycle\n│   ├── app.tsx               # Root React component for TUI\n│   ├── commands/             # Commander subcommands (exec, mcp, daemon, search, …)\n│   │   ├── exec.ts           # droid exec command\n│   │   ├── skills/           # Skill slash-command registration\n│   │   ├── mcp/              # droid mcp subcommands\n│   │   └── create-skill.ts   # /create-skill slash command\n│   ├── components/           # Ink/React UI components\n│   ├── hooks/                # React hooks (useAgent, useLLMStreaming, keyboard input, …)\n│   │   └── compaction/       # Conversation compaction logic\n│   ├── core/\n│   │   └── AgentLoop.ts      # Agent turn execution engine\n│   ├── exec/                 # Exec-mode runners\n│   │   ├── renderlessExecRunner.ts        # Standard exec runner\n│   │   ├── streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts  # JSON-RPC streaming runner (daemon mode)\n│   │   └── streamingExecRunner.ts         # Deprecated stream-json runner\n│   ├── mcp/\n│   │   └── McpHub.ts         # Aggregates multiple MCP server connections\n│   ├── services/\n│   │   ├── SessionService.ts # Session lifecycle, persistence, compaction\n│   │   └── mcp/McpService.ts # MCP lifecycle and tool registration\n│   ├── skills/\n│   │   └── builtin/          # Built-in skill constants\n│   └── tools/                # Tool registry, executors\n├── e2e-tests/                # @microsoft/tui-test E2E tests\n├── scripts/                  # Build, bundle, setup scripts\n└── package.json\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| Abstraction | File | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `AgentLoop` | `src/core/AgentLoop.ts` | Drives a single agent turn: calls LLM, executes tools, manages compaction |\n| `SessionService` | `src/services/SessionService.ts` | Creates, loads, forks, and persists sessions as JSONL |\n| `McpHub` | `src/mcp/McpHub.ts` | Aggregates MCP server connections, routes tool calls |\n| `McpService` | `src/services/mcp/McpService.ts` | Session-scoped MCP lifecycle: start/stop, OAuth, tool registration |\n| `useLLMStreaming` | `src/hooks/useLLMStreaming.ts` | React hook wrapping LLM streaming for TUI |\n| `useAgent` | `src/hooks/useAgent.ts` | React hook for full agent state in TUI |\n| `useChatKeyboardInput` | `src/hooks/useChatKeyboardInput.ts` | Keyboard input state machine |\n| `CompactionManager` | `src/hooks/compaction/CompactionManager.ts` | Context-window compaction (summarization) |\n| `SkillCommandsLoader` | `src/commands/skills/SkillCommandsLoader.ts` | Registers skills as slash commands |\n| `createExecCommand` | `src/commands/exec.ts` | Commander `exec` subcommand factory |\n\n## How it works\n\n### Mode detection\n\n`src/index.ts` runs a bootstrap sequence before launching either mode:\n\n```\nprocess start\n  → load .env / .env.local\n  → configureCredentialsStorage (keytar)\n  → initSentry, initTelemetry\n  → loadSystemCertificates\n  → settingsService.initialize()\n  → fetchFeatureFlags (background)\n  → Commander program.parseAsync(argv)\n         ↓ no positional args          ↓ first arg = \"exec\"\n     interactive TUI              exec command\n     (main.tsx)                   (commands/exec.ts)\n```\n\nThe entry point detects the first non-flag argument (`firstNonFlag`). When empty, it routes to the TUI via `main.tsx`. When `exec`, it routes directly to `createExecCommand()` (skipping all other command imports for ~200 ms startup savings).\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    A[process.argv] --> B{firstNonFlag?}\n    B -- none --> C[main.tsx / Ink TUI]\n    B -- exec --> D[commands/exec.ts]\n    B -- mcp --> E[commands/mcp/mcp.ts]\n    B -- daemon --> F[commands/daemon.ts]\n    B -- search/update/… --> G[other commands]\n    C --> H[AgentLoop via useAgent]\n    D --> I[AgentLoop via renderlessExecRunner]\n```\n\n### Agent execution\n\nBoth modes ultimately drive the same `AgentLoop`:\n\n1. **User message** is added to `SessionService` (persisted to JSONL).\n2. `AgentLoop` calls `createLLMStreamingCore` → sends messages to the Factory LLM proxy.\n3. Streamed response events (text deltas, tool use) are emitted via `agentEventBus`.\n4. Tool calls are dispatched through `ToolExecutor` → registered executor (file, shell, MCP, …).\n5. Tool results are appended as messages; the loop continues until the model stops.\n6. When the context window nears its limit, `CompactionManager` summarizes old messages and truncates history.\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant U as User\n    participant S as SessionService\n    participant A as AgentLoop\n    participant L as LLM proxy\n    participant T as ToolExecutor\n\n    U->>S: addUserMessage()\n    S->>A: run(prompt, history)\n    A->>L: stream messages\n    L-->>A: text delta / tool_use\n    A->>T: executeTool(name, args)\n    T-->>A: tool_result\n    A->>L: append tool_result, continue\n    L-->>A: stop_reason = end_turn\n    A->>S: persistAssistantMessage()\n```\n\n## Integration points\n\n| System | How CLI integrates |\n|---|---|\n| **factoryd daemon** | TUI connects via JSON-RPC WebSocket (`stream-jsonrpc` exec mode); daemon manages session lifecycle for web/desktop clients — see [apps/daemon.md](../daemon.md) |\n| **LLM proxy** (`apps/backend`) | All LLM calls go through the Factory API proxy; auth via `FACTORY_API_KEY` or WorkOS session token |\n| **MCP servers** | `McpHub` manages stdio and HTTP MCP server processes; tools auto-registered into TUI tool registry |\n| **@factory/droid-core** | Tool definitions and LLM streaming primitives — see [packages/droid-core.md](../../packages/droid-core.md) |\n| **@factory/common** | Shared types: `FactoryDroidMessage`, `SessionTag`, `AutonomyMode`, protocol schemas |\n| **Statsig feature flags** | Fetched at startup, control incremental rendering, MCP behaviours, etc. — see [docs/feature-flags.md](../../docs/feature-flags.md) |\n\n## Entry points for modification\n\n| Goal | Start here |\n|---|---|\n| Add a new slash command | Register a `SlashCommand` in `src/commands/` and add to the `commandRegistry` |\n| Add a new CLI subcommand | Create a Commander `Command` factory in `src/commands/` and register in `src/index.ts` |\n| Change agent behaviour | `src/core/AgentLoop.ts` — tool execution loop, compaction triggers |\n| Add a new tool | `src/tools/tui.ts` — register executor factory; `@factory/droid-core/tools/definitions` for schema |\n| Change session storage format | `src/services/SessionService.ts`, `src/services/sessionJsonl.ts` |\n| Modify keyboard shortcuts | `src/hooks/useChatKeyboardInput.ts` |\n| Change TUI layout | `src/app.tsx`, `src/components/` |\n| Add exec output format | `src/commands/exec.ts` → `OutputFormat` enum, `printSuccessOutput()` |\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [overview/architecture.md](../../overview/architecture.md) — System architecture with CLI→daemon→backend→LLM flow\n- [overview/glossary.md](../../overview/glossary.md) — Droid, Mission, Skill, MCP, ACP, CDE\n- [apps/daemon.md](../daemon.md) — factoryd daemon: session lifecycle, WebSocket JSON-RPC server\n- [features/sessions.md](../../features/sessions.md) — Session lifecycle from the user perspective\n- [features/mcp-integration.md](../../features/mcp-integration.md) — MCP integration across CLI and other components\n- [features/missions.md](../../features/missions.md) — Mission/AGI mode feature\n- [how-to-contribute/patterns-and-conventions.md](../../how-to-contribute/patterns-and-conventions.md) — CLI hook patterns, useAgent, useLLMStreaming\n- [packages/droid-core.md](../../packages/droid-core.md) — AI agent core library: tool definitions, LLM streaming\n",
