            "content": "# TUI rendering\n\n**Active contributors**: Arman Bolat, Luke Alvoeiro, theo, Leo Tchourakov, Abhay Singhal\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe interactive TUI is the primary user interface for Droid. It renders a full-screen chat application in the terminal using [Ink](https://github.com/vadimdemedes/ink) — a React renderer for terminal output. All chat history, streaming responses, tool call results, and status indicators are rendered as React components. Keyboard input is managed by a custom hook that handles multi-line editing, history navigation, file path suggestions, and clipboard operations.\n\n## How Ink works in this context\n\nInk renders a React component tree to terminal cells (rows × columns). On each render, it diffs the virtual tree against the previous output and writes only the changed lines. The CLI passes `{ incrementalRendering: true }` to Ink's `render()` when a feature flag is enabled, which further reduces flicker by rewriting only changed lines rather than the full screen.\n\nThe render call in `src/main.tsx`:\n\n```typescript\nconst app = render(\n  <KeypressProvider>\n    <App initialPrompt={initialPrompt} resumeSessionId={resumeSessionId} />\n  </KeypressProvider>,\n  {\n    exitOnCtrlC: false,     // handled manually to avoid interrupting subprocess shells\n    patchConsole: false,    // console.* redirected to log file by src/utils/patch-console.ts\n    incrementalRendering,   // feature-flag controlled\n  }\n);\n```\n\n`app.waitUntilExit()` blocks until the component tree unmounts (user quits), then `main.tsx` calls `displayResumeCommandIfNeeded()` and exits.\n\n## Component hierarchy\n\n```\nKeypressProvider           (raw keypress event bus)\n└── App (app.tsx)          (root: session init, mode routing)\n    ├── Header             (directory, model, session ID, autonomy level)\n    ├── ConversationView   (scrollable message history)\n    │   ├── AssistantMessage   (streamed text + thinking blocks)\n    │   ├── ToolCallMessage    (tool name, args, result)\n    │   └── UserMessage        (user input display)\n    ├── StatusBar          (working state: idle / thinking / calling tool / …)\n    ├── ChatInput          (text input area + suggestions + bash mode)\n    │   └── useChatKeyboardInput (keyboard state machine)\n    └── Overlays           (MCP manager, skill creator, settings panel, …)\n```\n\n`src/app.tsx` (~162 KB) contains the root `App` component. It is large because it co-locates the agent lifecycle hooks (`useAgent`, `useLLMStreaming`) with the top-level UI structure, keeping state shared across many child components available without prop-drilling through context.\n\n## Rendering model\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    A[terminal keypresses] --> B[KeypressProvider]\n    B --> C[useChatKeyboardInput]\n    C --> D[input state: text, cursor, suggestions]\n    D --> E[ChatInput component]\n    F[useAgent / useLLMStreaming] --> G[message array state]\n    G --> H[ConversationView]\n    H --> I[Ink render → terminal cells]\n    J[agentEventBus] --> F\n```\n\nReact state drives all rendering. The agent emits events on `agentEventBus` (in `src/events/AgentEventBus.ts`); hooks subscribe to those events and call React state setters, triggering re-renders.\n\n## Keyboard input\n\n`src/hooks/useChatKeyboardInput.ts` implements a custom multi-line text editor as a React hook. It does not use any text-input Ink component; instead it subscribes to raw keypresses from `KeypressProvider` and manages `input` / `cursorPosition` state manually. Key capabilities:\n\n| Binding | Effect |\n|---|---|\n| `Enter` | Submit message |\n| `Shift+Enter` / `\\` + `Enter` | Insert newline |\n| `↑` / `↓` | Navigate history (single-line) or move cursor (multi-line) |\n| `Ctrl+A` / `Ctrl+E` | Start / end of line |\n| `Ctrl+W` / `Option+Backspace` | Delete word before cursor |\n| `Option+D` / `Ctrl+Delete` | Delete word after cursor |\n| `Ctrl+U` | Delete to line start |\n| `Ctrl+K` | Delete to line end |\n| `Option+←` / `Option+→` | Jump word left / right |\n| `Ctrl+V` / `Cmd+V` | Paste from clipboard (text or image) |\n| `Tab` | Cycle reasoning level |\n| `Shift+Tab` | Cycle interaction mode (Auto → Spec → AGI) |\n| `Ctrl+N` | Cycle available models |\n| `Ctrl+L` | Cycle autonomy level |\n| `?` (empty input) | Toggle help hints |\n| `!` (empty input) | Toggle bash mode |\n| `ESC` (double) | Clear input |\n\n**Clipboard handling**: pasted text longer than 400 characters or more than 8 lines is shown as a `[preview... N lines]` placeholder in the input field. The full content is stored in a `pastedBlocks` map and expanded back to full text immediately before submitting to the agent.\n\n**Kitty protocol**: the CLI detects and enables the [Kitty keyboard protocol](https://sw.kovidgoyal.net/kitty/keyboard-protocol/) at startup. This provides unambiguous CSI-u escape sequences for keys like `Shift+Tab`, `ESC`, and modifier+arrow combinations that are otherwise indistinguishable in traditional terminal encoding.\n\n## KeypressProvider\n\n`src/contexts/KeypressProvider.tsx` wraps the raw Node.js keypress events and exposes them as a React context. It deduplicates rapid keypress events and emits them as `KeyEvent` objects. Consumers call `useKeypressProvider()` to subscribe. `useChatKeyboardInput` is the primary consumer.\n\n## Logging in TUI mode\n\nAll `console.*` calls are intercepted by `src/utils/patch-console.ts` (imported first in `src/index.ts`) and redirected to `~/.factory/logs/droid-log-<timestamp>.log`. This prevents log output from corrupting the Ink render.\n\n## E2E tests\n\nThe TUI is tested with `@microsoft/tui-test` (Microsoft's terminal UI testing framework). Tests live in `apps/cli/e2e-tests/`. Each test spawns the CLI binary in an isolated workspace under `/tmp/droid-test-{pid}-{timestamp}`, interacts with the terminal via the test API, and asserts on rendered text. Run with:\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli && npm run test:e2e\n```\n\n## Integration points\n\n- **`src/hooks/useAgent.ts`** — agent state hook consumed by `App`; connects TUI to `AgentLoop` and `SessionService`\n- **`src/hooks/useLLMStreaming.ts`** — streaming state hook; surfaces text deltas, thinking blocks, and tool calls\n- **`src/app.tsx`** — root component; contains the top-level `useAgent`/`useLLMStreaming` calls\n- **`src/services/SessionService.ts`** — session is created or loaded before first render; see [session-management.md](./session-management.md)\n- **MCP** — started in background during `main.tsx`; tool list updates trigger re-renders; see [mcp.md](./mcp.md)\n\n## Entry points for modification\n\n| Goal | File |\n|---|---|\n| Add or change a keyboard shortcut | `src/hooks/useChatKeyboardInput.ts` |\n| Change the input area appearance | `src/components/chat/` |\n| Add a new message type to conversation view | `src/components/` + wire up in `App`/`ConversationView` |\n| Add an overlay (modal) | `src/app.tsx` — overlay state + conditional render |\n| Change the header layout | `src/components/Header.tsx` (or equivalent) |\n| Change Ink render options | `src/main.tsx` — the `render()` call |\n| Add E2E test coverage | `apps/cli/e2e-tests/` |\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [apps/cli/index.md](./index.md) — CLI overview and architecture\n- [apps/cli/exec-mode.md](./exec-mode.md) — Non-interactive exec mode\n- [how-to-contribute/patterns-and-conventions.md](../../how-to-contribute/patterns-and-conventions.md) — Hook patterns\n",
