            "content": "# Exec mode\n\n**Active contributors**: Arman Bolat, Luke Alvoeiro, shashank-factory, Abhay Singhal, David Vendrow\n\n## Purpose\n\nExec mode (`droid exec`) is the non-interactive variant of Droid. It accepts a prompt (from an argument, a file, or stdin), runs the agent to completion, and emits structured output to stdout. It is designed for scripting, CI/CD pipelines, sub-agent spawning (Mission workers), and integration with external orchestration systems.\n\n## Command structure\n\n```\ndroid exec [options] [prompt]\n```\n\n**Prompt sources** (priority order):\n1. `--file <path>` — read from a file\n2. Piped stdin (auto-detected when stdin is not a TTY)\n3. Positional argument\n\n**Key options**:\n\n| Option | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `--auto <low\\|medium\\|high>` | Autonomy level controlling which tools are permitted |\n| `--skip-permissions-unsafe` | Bypass all permission checks (isolated environments only) |\n| `-s, --session-id <id>` | Continue an existing session (loads history, no replay) |\n| `-m, --model <id>` | Model to use (default: `DEFAULT_MODEL_OPTION`) |\n| `-r, --reasoning-effort <level>` | Reasoning effort per model |\n| `-o, --output-format <format>` | `text` (default), `json`, `stream-json`, `debug` |\n| `--input-format <format>` | `stream-json` (multi-turn stdin) or `stream-jsonrpc` (daemon mode) |\n| `--mission` | Run in mission/AGI orchestrator mode |\n| `--list-tools` | Print available tools and exit |\n| `--enabled-tools` / `--disabled-tools` | Override tool allow/block list |\n| `-w, --worktree [name]` | Create a git worktree and run inside it |\n\n## Autonomy levels\n\nExec mode enforces a tiered permission system. Without flags the agent runs **read-only**.\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    A[no flags] -->|read-only| B[inspect, diff, log commands]\n    C[--auto low] -->|file ops| D[touch, mkdir, mv, cp]\n    E[--auto medium] -->|dev ops| F[npm install, git commit, build]\n    G[--auto high] -->|prod ops| H[git push, deploy, migrations]\n    I[--skip-permissions-unsafe] -->|unrestricted| J[all tools allowed]\n```\n\n## Output formats\n\nThe `--output-format` flag controls what is written to stdout:\n\n| Format | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `text` | Plain text final answer from the agent |\n| `json` | Single JSON object (`ExecSummary`) on exit |\n| `stream-json` | JSONL event stream (one event per line) as the agent runs |\n| `debug` | Same as `stream-json` with additional diagnostic events |\n\n### `stream-json` event types\n\n```jsonc\n{ \"type\": \"system\", \"subtype\": \"init\", \"cwd\": \"...\", \"session_id\": \"...\", \"tools\": [...], \"model\": \"...\" }\n{ \"type\": \"message\", \"role\": \"user\"|\"assistant\", \"id\": \"...\", \"text\": \"...\", \"session_id\": \"...\" }\n{ \"type\": \"tool_call\", \"id\": \"...\", \"toolId\": \"...\", \"parameters\": {...}, \"session_id\": \"...\" }\n{ \"type\": \"tool_result\", \"id\": \"...\", \"toolId\": \"...\", \"value\": \"...\", \"isError\": false, \"session_id\": \"...\" }\n{ \"type\": \"error\", \"source\": \"cli\"|\"agent_loop\", \"message\": \"...\", \"session_id\": \"...\" }\n{ \"type\": \"completion\", \"finalText\": \"...\", \"numTurns\": 3, \"durationMs\": 4200, \"session_id\": \"...\", \"usage\": {...} }\n```\n\n## Streaming input modes\n\n### `--input-format stream-json` (multi-turn, deprecated)\n\nKeeps a single process alive and reads newline-delimited user messages from stdin. Each message is an `Anthropic.MessageParam` with `role: \"user\"`. The session persists across all messages. Stdin close triggers graceful shutdown. This mode is deprecated in favor of `stream-jsonrpc`.\n\n### `--input-format stream-jsonrpc` (daemon/web client mode)\n\nUsed when factoryd spawns a CLI child process to serve a web or desktop client session. The runner (`src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts`) speaks JSON-RPC 2.0 over stdin/stdout, implementing the full [ACP (Agent Communication Protocol)](../../overview/glossary.md). It handles session initialization, message exchange, tool calls, MCP configuration, and skill listing — all via RPC methods.\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant D as factoryd daemon\n    participant C as CLI (stream-jsonrpc)\n    participant A as AgentLoop\n\n    D->>C: stdin: {\"method\":\"initialize\",\"params\":{...}}\n    C-->>D: stdout: {\"result\":{\"sessionId\":\"...\"}}\n    D->>C: stdin: {\"method\":\"addUserMessage\",\"params\":{\"content\":\"fix the bug\"}}\n    C->>A: run turn\n    A-->>C: agentEventBus events\n    C-->>D: stdout: notifications (text delta, tool call, completion)\n    D->>C: stdin EOF / kill signal\n    C->>C: graceful shutdown\n```\n\n## Runners\n\n`src/exec/` contains several runner implementations:\n\n| File | Used when |\n|---|---|\n| `renderlessExecRunner.ts` | Standard `droid exec \"prompt\"` — runs `AgentLoop` directly |\n| `streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` | `--input-format stream-jsonrpc` (daemon child mode) |\n| `streamingExecRunner.ts` | `--input-format stream-json` (deprecated multi-turn) |\n| `acpChildRunner.ts` | `--output-format acp` (ACP single-session child) |\n| `acpDaemonRunner.ts` | `--output-format acp-daemon` (ACP multi-session daemon) |\n\n`renderlessExecRunner.ts` is the main exec path. It:\n1. Verifies auth token.\n2. Creates or loads a session via `SessionController`.\n3. Adds the user message.\n4. Runs `AgentLoop.run()`.\n5. Collects final text and emits a `completion` event.\n\n## Mission mode\n\n`--mission` upgrades the session to an orchestrator role:\n\n1. Ensures `factoryd` is running (starts it if needed).\n2. Calls `sessionService.upgradeToOrchestratorSession()`.\n3. Sets `DroidInteractionMode.AGI`.\n4. Prepends the orchestrator system prompt to `EXEC_SYSTEM_PROMPT`.\n5. Uses `MISSION_ORCHESTRATOR_MODEL` and `MISSION_ORCHESTRATOR_REASONING_EFFORT` by default.\n\nWorker sessions are spawned by the orchestrator via the `Task` tool, which calls back into `factoryd` — which spawns new `droid exec --input-format stream-jsonrpc` child processes.\n\nSee [features/missions.md](../../features/missions.md) for the full mission architecture.\n\n## Worktrees\n\n`--worktree [name]` creates a git worktree (or reuses an existing one) before running the agent:\n\n```bash\ndroid exec --worktree feature-branch \"implement the OAuth flow\"\n```\n\nThe worktree is created at a temp path, `process.chdir()` is called, and the agent runs in that directory. If the worktree was newly created, it is deleted on exit via the shutdown coordinator hook.\n\n## Tool selection\n\n`src/commands/resolveToolSelection.ts` computes the allowed tool set from:\n- The base set for the selected model\n- `--enabled-tools` additions\n- `--disabled-tools` removals\n- MCP tools (added after `getMcpService().start()`)\n\n`--list-tools` prints the resolved catalog grouped by category (Read / Edit / Execute / Other / MCP) and exits.\n\n## Session continuation\n\n`--session-id <id>` loads an existing session's full conversation history before the new prompt. The history is replayed silently (not echoed to stdout) to give the agent context.\n\n## Error handling and exit codes\n\n- Exit code `0` — successful completion\n- Exit code `1` — agent error, authentication failure, or invalid options\n\nFor `json` and `stream-json` formats, errors are emitted as structured events rather than printed to stderr.\n\n## Integration points\n\n- **`SessionService`** — session creation/loading; see [session-management.md](./session-management.md)\n- **`McpService`** — started before prompt resolution so MCP tools are available; see [mcp.md](./mcp.md)\n- **`AgentLoop`** — core execution engine; see [apps/cli/index.md](./index.md)\n- **factoryd** — spawns CLI in `stream-jsonrpc` mode; see [apps/daemon.md](../daemon.md)\n\n## Entry points for modification\n\n| Goal | File |\n|---|---|\n| Add a new output format | `src/commands/exec.ts` — `OutputFormat` enum + `printSuccessOutput()` |\n| Add a new exec flag | `src/commands/exec.ts` — `.option()` + `ExecCommandOptions` type |\n| Change agent behaviour in exec | `src/exec/renderlessExecRunner.ts` |\n| Change JSON-RPC protocol handling | `src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` |\n| Change tool resolution logic | `src/commands/resolveToolSelection.ts` |\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [apps/cli/index.md](./index.md) — CLI overview\n- [apps/cli/tui-rendering.md](./tui-rendering.md) — Interactive TUI\n- [apps/cli/session-management.md](./session-management.md) — Session lifecycle\n- [apps/daemon.md](../daemon.md) — factoryd, which spawns exec in stream-jsonrpc mode\n- [features/missions.md](../../features/missions.md) — Mission orchestration\n",
