            "content": "# Session management\n\n**Active contributors**: Arman Bolat, Luke Alvoeiro, shashank-factory, Leo Tchourakov, Abhay Singhal\n\n## Purpose\n\n`src/services/SessionService.ts` is the single source of truth for session state in the CLI. It handles creation, loading, forking, compaction, and on-disk persistence of conversation sessions. A session is the unit of continuity: it stores the full message history, settings (model, autonomy level, interaction mode), token usage, and metadata.\n\nSee [features/sessions.md](../../features/sessions.md) for the user-facing description of sessions.\n\n## On-disk layout\n\nSessions are stored as [JSONL](https://jsonlines.org/) (newline-delimited JSON) files:\n\n```\n~/.factory/sessions/\n├── <session-id>.jsonl          # global / project-agnostic sessions\n├── -<sanitized-cwd>/           # project-specific directory (hashed from cwd)\n│   ├── <session-id>.jsonl      # session messages\n│   └── <session-id>.settings.json  # session settings overlay\n└── .favorites                  # set of favorited session IDs\n```\n\nEach `.jsonl` file has:\n- **Line 1**: `SessionSummaryEvent` — session metadata (id, title, owner, cwd, tags, …)\n- **Subsequent lines**: `DroidMessageEvent` — individual conversation messages\n\nAttachments (PDFs) are stored separately:\n```\n~/.factory/sessions/<session-id>/attachments/\n```\n\nThe sessions directory is created with restricted permissions (`chmod 700`) to protect conversation history.\n\n## Session lifecycle\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    A[CLI start] --> B{resume flag?}\n    B -- no --> C[createNewSession]\n    B -- yes --> D[loadSession]\n    C --> E[createSessionWithId]\n    D --> E\n    E --> F[current session active]\n    F --> G[addUserMessage]\n    G --> H[AgentLoop runs]\n    H --> I[persistAssistantMessages]\n    I --> J{context limit?}\n    J -- no --> G\n    J -- yes --> K[CompactionManager.compact]\n    K --> I\n    F --> L{/fork or rewind}\n    L --> M[forkSession]\n    M --> E\n    F --> N[user quits / shutdown]\n    N --> O[SessionEnd hooks]\n    O --> P[session persisted to disk]\n```\n\n### Creation\n\n`createNewSession()` generates a UUID session ID, writes the first `SessionSummaryEvent` line to the JSONL file, and optionally creates the session in the Factory API (cloud sync). A fresh `system_info` context block is injected on the first user message if the session is new (not resumed).\n\n### Loading (resume)\n\n`loadSession(sessionId)` searches for the `.jsonl` file across:\n1. The current project directory (`-<sanitized-cwd>/`)\n2. The global sessions directory\n3. All project directories (when `searchAllProjects: true`)\n\nIt reads the JSONL file line-by-line, reconstructing the message array. PDF attachment data is loaded back into memory from the attachments directory. The resulting `DroidSession` object is returned.\n\nResume is triggered by `--resume [sessionId]` in TUI mode or `--session-id <id>` in exec mode.\n\n### Forking\n\n`forkSession(sourceSessionId, targetMessageId, newTitle)` creates a new session that is a copy of an existing one truncated at a specific message. This powers the **rewind** feature — when the user asks Droid to rewind and try a different approach, the current session is forked at the divergence point.\n\nThe fork:\n1. Loads all messages from the source session up to `targetMessageId`.\n2. Creates a new session with the truncated history.\n3. Links the new session's `parentSessionId` to the source.\n\n### Compaction\n\nWhen the conversation approaches the model's context limit, `CompactionManager` (`src/hooks/compaction/CompactionManager.ts`) summarizes older messages:\n\n1. Messages beyond a token threshold (`COMPACTION_TOKEN_LIMIT`) are passed to a `Summarizer` which generates a compact summary via the LLM.\n2. The full history is replaced with: `[summary block] + [recent messages]`.\n3. The new compact history is persisted to the JSONL file (overwriting older entries).\n4. A `CompactionSummaryKind` enum tracks whether this was a full compaction or a provider-switch migration.\n\nToken counting uses a character-based approximation (4 chars ≈ 1 token) to avoid the latency of exact tokenization.\n\n## Settings per session\n\nEach session has a `SessionSettings` object maintained in memory and persisted to `<session-id>.settings.json`:\n\n| Setting | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `model` | Active model ID (e.g., `claude-sonnet-4-20250514`) |\n| `reasoningEffort` | Reasoning budget for the model |\n| `interactionMode` | Auto / Spec / AGI |\n| `autonomyLevel` | Off / Low / Medium / High |\n| `autonomyMode` | Derived from interaction mode + autonomy level |\n| `specModeModel` / `specModeReasoningEffort` | Separate model config for Spec mode |\n\nSettings changes (model switch, autonomy toggle) are saved asynchronously and optionally synced to the Factory API for cloud session continuity.\n\n## Interaction modes and autonomy\n\n`SessionService` is the authoritative store for autonomy:\n\n| Mode | Meaning |\n|---|---|\n| `Auto` + `Off` | Read-only (default TUI) |\n| `Auto` + `Low/Medium/High` | Auto-run with tiered permissions |\n| `Spec` | Plan-first mode: agent proposes, user approves |\n| `AGI` (Mission) | Orchestrator mode: spawns worker sessions |\n\nOrganization-level policies can cap the maximum `AutonomyLevel` via `SettingsManager`. The service clamps any requested level to the org maximum.\n\n## Token usage tracking\n\nThe service accumulates `TokenUsage` counters (input, output, cache_read, cache_creation, thinking tokens) across all messages in the session. These are periodically flushed to the JSONL file and exposed for exec-mode `ExecSummary` output.\n\n## Session search\n\n`getAllSessions()` and `getAllNonEmptySessions()` scan the sessions directory recursively, reading the first JSONL line (summary event) of each file without loading the full message history. Results are sorted by `modifiedTime` descending.\n\nA background `warmSearchCache()` call at startup pre-builds an index of session IDs and titles for faster search in the TUI session picker.\n\n## Hooks: session start and end\n\n`HookService` fires `SessionStart` events after session creation (allowing external tools to inject context) and `SessionEnd` events on shutdown (allowing cleanup or final syncs). `ensureSessionEndHookRegistered()` in `src/index.ts` registers a process exit hook to guarantee the `SessionEnd` fires even on SIGTERM.\n\n## Integration points\n\n| Component | Relationship |\n|---|---|\n| `AgentLoop` | Reads session history; calls `addMessage()` to persist each turn |\n| `SessionController` | Thin wrapper over `SessionService` used by exec-mode runners |\n| `CompactionManager` | Called by `AgentLoop` when token budget is exceeded |\n| Factory API | Cloud sync: session creation, settings changes, status updates (`droid-status` endpoint) |\n| `MissionExecutionWakeLockService` | Acquires system wake lock during mission execution |\n\n## Entry points for modification\n\n| Goal | File |\n|---|---|\n| Change session persistence format | `src/services/SessionService.ts`, `src/services/sessionJsonl.ts` |\n| Change compaction strategy | `src/hooks/compaction/CompactionManager.ts`, `Summarizer.ts` |\n| Change how sessions are scoped per project | `src/services/SessionService.ts` → `getSessionsDirectory()`, `sanitizePathToDirectoryName()` |\n| Add a new session setting | `src/services/SessionService.ts` + `@factory/common/session/settings` |\n| Add a session lifecycle hook | `src/services/HookService.ts` |\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [features/sessions.md](../../features/sessions.md) — Session feature from the user perspective\n- [apps/cli/index.md](./index.md) — CLI overview\n- [apps/cli/exec-mode.md](./exec-mode.md) — How exec mode uses sessions\n- [apps/daemon.md](../daemon.md) — Daemon's own session lifecycle\n",
