            "content": "# MCP integration\n\n**Active contributors**: Arman Bolat, Luke Alvoeiro, Leo Tchourakov, Varin Nair, Eno Reyes\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe CLI integrates with [Model Context Protocol (MCP)](https://modelcontextprotocol.io/) servers to give the agent access to external tools and resources — file access in remote environments, database queries, API clients, browser automation, and more. The MCP layer consists of two main classes:\n\n- **`McpHub`** (`src/mcp/McpHub.ts`) — low-level aggregator that owns connections to individual MCP server processes\n- **`McpService`** (`src/services/mcp/McpService.ts`) — session-scoped orchestrator that manages the full lifecycle: startup, tool registration, OAuth, settings-driven reload, and event emission\n\nSee [features/mcp-integration.md](../../features/mcp-integration.md) for the cross-cutting feature description and configuration reference.\n\n## Server configuration\n\nMCP servers are configured in the `mcpServers` map in `~/.factory/settings.json` (personal) or `<repo>/.factory/settings.json` (project). Each entry specifies the server name, transport type, and connection parameters.\n\nTwo transport types are supported:\n\n| Type | Use case | Required fields |\n|---|---|---|\n| `stdio` (default) | Local processes (npx packages, local scripts) | `command`, `args[]`, optional `env{}` |\n| `http` | Remote servers, SaaS APIs | `url`, optional `headers{}`, optional `oauth{}` |\n\nAdditional per-server fields:\n\n| Field | Default | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `disabled` | `false` | Prevent the server from starting without removing the config |\n| `disabledTools` | `[]` | Block specific tools from this server |\n\n```jsonc\n// .factory/settings.json\n{\n  \"mcpServers\": {\n    \"my-db\": {\n      \"type\": \"stdio\",\n      \"command\": \"npx\",\n      \"args\": [\"-y\", \"@my-org/mcp-db-server\"],\n      \"env\": { \"DB_URL\": \"postgres://...\" }\n    },\n    \"github\": {\n      \"type\": \"http\",\n      \"url\": \"https://api.github.com/mcp\",\n      \"headers\": { \"Authorization\": \"Bearer ghp_...\" }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n`droid mcp add <name> <url-or-command>` writes to the settings file and triggers a live reload.\n\n## Architecture\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    S[McpService] --> H[McpHub]\n    H --> P1[stdio process: npx @my-org/mcp-server]\n    H --> P2[stdio process: uvx mcp-server-git]\n    H --> P3[HTTP: https://api.example.com/mcp]\n    H --> P4[system: CLI MCP server]\n    H -->|tools list| R[TUI Tool Registry]\n    R --> A[AgentLoop / ToolExecutor]\n    A -->|callTool| H\n    H -->|MCP callTool| P1\n```\n\n`McpHub` separates `systemMcpConfigs` (built-in servers, such as the internal CLI MCP server for VSCode integration) from `userMcpConfigs` (user-defined). Both sets are started together; system servers are never stopped by config reloads.\n\n## Startup flow\n\n`getMcpService().start()` is called early in both TUI (`src/main.tsx`) and exec mode (`src/commands/exec.ts`). The startup sequence:\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant CLI as CLI startup\n    participant MS as McpService\n    participant MH as McpHub\n    participant TR as TUI Tool Registry\n\n    CLI->>MS: start()\n    MS->>MS: load settings (user + system configs)\n    MS->>MH: new McpHub({systemMcpConfigs, userMcpConfigs})\n    MS->>MH: reloadServers()\n    MH->>MH: start HTTP servers sequentially (OAuth conflict prevention)\n    MH->>MH: start stdio servers in parallel\n    MH-->>MS: McpReloadResult\n    MS->>MH: listAllTools()\n    MS->>TR: register each tool as McpToolExecutor\n    MS-->>CLI: start() resolves\n```\n\nHTTP servers are started sequentially because OAuth callback servers cannot share the same port.\n\n## Client types\n\n### Stdio client (`src/mcp/clients/stdio.ts`)\n\nSpawns a child process using `StdioClientTransport` from the MCP SDK. The process inherits the current environment merged with any `env` overrides from the config. Stderr is silenced. Log-level notifications from the server are forwarded to the Factory logging layer.\n\n### HTTP client (`src/mcp/clients/http.ts`)\n\nConnects to a remote MCP endpoint over HTTP. If the server requires OAuth, `McpService` creates a `TuiOAuthProvider` that:\n1. Opens the authorization URL in the user's browser.\n2. Starts a local callback server (`OAuthCallbackServer`) to receive the authorization code.\n3. Exchanges the code for tokens via `OAuthStorage` (persisted to `~/.factory/mcp-oauth/`).\n\n## Tool registration\n\nAfter connecting to each server, `McpService` calls `listAllTools()` on `McpHub`, then for each tool:\n\n1. Creates a `FactoryTool` descriptor with the MCP tool's name (prefixed as `{serverName}_{toolName}`), description, and input schema.\n2. Wraps it in a `McpToolExecutor` that calls `McpHub.callTool()` when invoked.\n3. Registers the tool + executor in the TUI tool registry (`getTUIToolRegistry().register()`).\n4. Tracks registered tool IDs by server name in `registeredToolsByServer` for cleanup on reload.\n\nThe tool's `llmId` in the agent's tool list uses the prefixed name so the LLM can identify which server provides it.\n\n## Live reload\n\n`McpService` watches the settings file for changes. When the `mcpServers` config changes:\n1. `McpHub.reloadServers()` is called with the new config.\n2. Servers whose config is unchanged are left running (cheap equality check via `_.isEqual`).\n3. Removed or changed servers are stopped (SIGTERM → SIGKILL grace period).\n4. New servers are started.\n5. The updated tool list is broadcast to all ACP/JSON-RPC clients via `McpHub.notifyAll()`.\n\nDuring targeted operations (add/remove/enable/disable from the TUI MCP manager), file watching is temporarily disabled to suppress spurious reloads.\n\n## Resource subscriptions\n\n`McpHub` supports MCP resource subscriptions. A client (ACP session) can subscribe to a named resource on a server. When the server notifies of an update (`ResourceUpdated`), `McpHub` fetches the new contents and forwards a `ResourceChange` notification to all subscribed clients. This enables live context injection (e.g., a file watcher server pushing updated file content into the agent's context).\n\n## CLI commands\n\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `droid mcp add <name> <url-or-command>` | Add an MCP server to settings |\n| `droid mcp remove <name>` | Remove an MCP server from settings |\n| `/mcp` (TUI slash command) | Open the interactive MCP manager overlay |\n\nThe interactive MCP manager overlay (TUI only) shows connection status, lists tools per server, and allows enabling/disabling individual tools.\n\n## Error handling\n\n- Server startup failures are reported as `McpServiceEventType.SERVER_STARTED` events with `success: false`.\n- Individual tool call failures propagate as tool result errors (the agent sees the error message and can retry or skip).\n- After a startup failure the server can be retried via `McpHub.retryServer(name)`.\n- HTTP servers that fail OAuth are logged with the auth outcome; the server remains registered but non-functional until re-authenticated.\n\n## Integration points\n\n| Component | Relationship |\n|---|---|\n| `TUI tool registry` | MCP tools are registered here; `AgentLoop`/`ToolExecutor` dispatch calls through it |\n| `streamingJsonRpcExecRunner` | Handles `toggleMcpServer`, `addMcpServer`, `removeMcpServer`, `authenticateMcpServer` JSON-RPC methods from daemon clients |\n| `SettingsManager` (`@factory/services/settings`) | Source of truth for `mcpServers` config |\n| `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk` | Official MCP TypeScript SDK used for all transport and protocol logic |\n\n## Entry points for modification\n\n| Goal | File |\n|---|---|\n| Change server startup/connection logic | `src/mcp/clients/stdio.ts`, `src/mcp/clients/http.ts` |\n| Change tool naming / registration | `src/services/mcp/McpService.ts` → `createMcpTool()` |\n| Change OAuth flow | `src/services/mcp/oauth/TuiOAuthProvider.ts`, `OAuthCallbackServer.ts` |\n| Add MCP notification handling | `src/mcp/McpHub.ts` — `client.setNotificationHandler()` |\n| Change tool executor behaviour | `src/tools/executors/client/mcp/McpToolExecutor.ts` |\n| Add CLI commands for MCP | `src/commands/mcp/` |\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [features/mcp-integration.md](../../features/mcp-integration.md) — MCP integration feature description and configuration reference\n- [apps/cli/index.md](./index.md) — CLI overview\n- [apps/daemon.md](../daemon.md) — Daemon MCP proxy for web/desktop clients\n- [overview/glossary.md](../../overview/glossary.md) — MCP definition\n",
