            "content": "# @factory/droid-core — AI agent core\n\n**Active contributors:** Luke Alvoeiro, l30t, Alvin Sng, factory-sherry, Varin Nair, factory-daniel, Stepan, theo\n\n## Purpose\n\n`@factory/droid-core` is the runtime library that powers the Droid AI agent. It defines every tool the agent can call, the registry that binds tools to executors, the provider-agnostic LLM streaming interface, message and fragment types used during a conversation, and prompt-building utilities. It runs in both the CLI/daemon (Bun, Node) and the browser-side tool execution paths.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/droid-core/src/\n├── api/           # HTTP helpers for agent readiness and droid API calls\n├── automations/   # Automation trigger definitions\n├── core/          # Core constants and enums (session identity, etc.)\n├── droids/        # Droid configuration computation\n├── feature-flags/ # Feature flag constants reused inside droid-core\n├── llms/          # LLM provider integrations and default model selection\n│   ├── errors/    # Typed LLM error classes\n│   └── provider/  # Anthropic, OpenAI, Google provider implementations\n├── machine-connection/ # Machine connection type defaults\n├── messages/      # Message utility functions\n├── prompts/       # System prompt construction (agent-readiness, readiness-fix)\n├── streaming/     # Data stream schema, enums, metrics recorder\n└── tools/         # Tool framework\n    ├── create-tool.ts     # createTool() factory function\n    ├── enums.ts           # Toolkit, ToolUIGroupId, DraftToolFeedbackType enums\n    ├── registry.ts        # ToolRegistry class\n    ├── types.ts           # FactoryTool, ToolExecutor, ToolImplementation interfaces\n    ├── definitions/       # All built-in tool implementations\n    │   ├── cli/           # Read, LS, Execute, Edit, MultiEdit, Create, GrepSearch, …\n    │   ├── file-tools/    # applyPatch, editFile, createFile (non-CLI variants)\n    │   ├── mission/       # proposeMission, startMissionRun, endFeatureRun, …\n    │   ├── slack/         # slackPostMessage\n    │   ├── todo/          # todoWrite\n    │   └── web/           # webSearch, fetchUrl\n    ├── legacy/            # Legacy tool wrappers\n    └── utils/             # apply-patch-core, truncate, line-slice, large-output, …\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| Abstraction | File | Description |\n|-------------|------|-------------|\n| `FactoryTool` | `tools/types.ts` | Shape of a single tool: `id`, `llmId`, `description`, `inputSchema`, `outputSchemas`, `isToolEnabled`, `executionLocation`, etc. |\n| `ToolExecutor<TDeps>` | `tools/types.ts` | Interface with an `execute(deps, params)` async generator that yields `DraftToolFeedback` |\n| `ToolImplementation<TDeps>` | `tools/types.ts` | Pairs a `FactoryTool` with a lazy `executorFactory` |\n| `ToolRegistry<TDeps>` | `tools/registry.ts` | Map-backed registry; `register()`, `getExecutor()`, `getTool()`, `getAllTools()`, `getToolByLlmId()` |\n| `createTool()` | `tools/create-tool.ts` | Factory that converts a Zod input schema → JSON Schema and fills defaults for `isMcpTool: false` |\n| `DraftToolFeedback` | `tools/types.ts` | `DraftToolResult` or `DraftToolUpdate` yielded during tool execution |\n| `IsToolEnabledParams` | `tools/types.ts` | Context passed to the dynamic `isToolEnabled` predicate: feature flags, integrations, model provider, machine connection type, etc. |\n| `LanguageModelV1` | `llms/types.ts` | Provider-agnostic LLM interface; one method: `doStream(options) → LanguageModelStreamResultV1` |\n| `LanguageModelV1CallOptions` | `llms/types.ts` | Inputs to `doStream`: model, system prompt, messages, tools, abort signal, Langfuse tracer |\n| `LanguageModelV1StreamPart` | `llms/types.ts` | Union of all possible stream parts (text delta, tool call, thinking delta, finish step, …) |\n| `DataStreamPartKey` | `streaming/enums.ts` | Enum of all data stream part types used in the wire format |\n| `LanguageModelFinishReason` | `streaming/enums.ts` | Why the model stopped: `stop`, `tool-calls`, `length`, `error`, `canceled`, etc. |\n| `DataStreamEncodedKey` | `streaming/enums.ts` | Compact single-character keys for the streaming wire encoding |\n| `LLMToolSpec` | `tools/types.ts` | Minimal tool spec sent to the LLM (name, description, input_schema) |\n| `Toolkit` | `tools/enums.ts` | Groups tools by capability: `Base`, `WebSearch`, `CodeSearch`, `Terminal`, `Slack` |\n| `ToolUIGroupId` | `tools/enums.ts` | UI groupings: `ViewFile`, `EditFile`, `GlobTool`, `GrepTool`, `WebSearch`, etc. |\n\n## How it works\n\n### Tool lifecycle\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    def[\"Tool definition\\n(createTool)\"] --> reg[\"ToolRegistry\\n.register()\"]\n    reg --> exec[\"ToolRegistry\\n.getExecutor(toolId)\"]\n    exec --> run[\"ToolExecutor\\n.execute(deps, params)\"]\n    run --> fb[\"DraftToolFeedback\\nyield Update | Result\"]\n```\n\n1. Each built-in tool calls `createTool({ id, llmId, inputSchema, ... })` which converts the Zod schema to JSON Schema (via `zod-to-json-schema`) and returns a `FactoryTool`.\n2. The calling app (CLI or daemon) creates a `ToolRegistry` instance and calls `registry.register({ tool, executorFactory })` for each tool it wants to enable.\n3. The agent loop resolves the executor lazily via `registry.getExecutor(toolId)` and calls `executor.execute(dependencies, params)`, which is an async generator.\n4. The generator yields zero or more `DraftToolUpdate` objects (interim progress) before finally yielding a `DraftToolResult`.\n5. The `isToolEnabled` predicate on each tool is evaluated with current session state to decide which tools appear in the LLM's tool list.\n\n### LLM provider abstraction\n\nEach provider (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google) implements the `LanguageModelV1` interface in `packages/droid-core/src/llms/provider/`. The interface exposes a single `doStream()` method that returns a `ReadableStream<LanguageModelV1StreamPart>`. This keeps the agent loop provider-agnostic — it streams parts regardless of which model is in use.\n\nProvider-specific concerns (chunk schemas, stop reasons, JSON schema sanitization, error mapping, prompt caching) live in subdirectories:\n- `provider/anthropic/` — chunk schema, stop reason mapping, prompt caching\n- `provider/openai/` — finish reason, error handling, tool name sanitization\n- `provider/google/` — schema conversion, error mapper, finish reason\n\n### Streaming protocol\n\nThe data stream uses a compact encoded format (`DataStreamEncodedKey`) where each part is prefixed with a single hex character. Parts include:\n- `0` (text), `3` (tool_call), `4` (tool_result), `5` (tool_call_streaming_start), `6` (tool_call_delta)\n- `7` (finish_message), `8` (finish_step), `9` (tool_update)\n- `b` (fragment_text_delta), `c` (thinking_text_delta), `d` (redacted_thinking)\n\nThe full schema is in `packages/droid-core/src/streaming/schema.ts`.\n\n### Prompt building\n\n`packages/droid-core/src/prompts/agent-readiness.ts` builds the system prompt for the agent-readiness assessment flow. `readiness-fix.ts` handles fix-mode prompt construction. Both export typed functions rather than raw strings.\n\n### Tool definitions (built-in set)\n\n| Group | Tools |\n|-------|-------|\n| **CLI** | `Read`, `LS`, `Execute`, `Edit`, `MultiEdit`, `Create`, `GrepSearch`, `GlobSearch`, `ApplyPatch`, `TaskCli`, `GenerateDroid`, `Skill`, `AskUser`, `ExitSpecMode` |\n| **File tools** | `applyPatch`, `editFile`, `editFileAnthropic`, `createFile`, `createFileAnthropic` |\n| **Web** | `webSearch` (Exa / You backends), `fetchUrl` |\n| **Search** | `globSearch`, `grepSearch`, `viewFile`, `viewFolder` |\n| **Mission** | `proposeMission`, `startMissionRun`, `endFeatureRun`, `dismissHandoffItems` |\n| **Slack** | `slackPostMessage` |\n| **Todo** | `todoWrite` |\n| **Readiness** | `storeAgentReadinessReportRemote` |\n| **Shell** | `shell` |\n\n## Integration points\n\n- `apps/cli` is the primary consumer; it creates a `ToolRegistry`, registers all CLI tools, and drives the agent loop. See [apps/cli/index.md](../apps/cli/index.md).\n- `apps/daemon` uses `@factory/daemon-core` which consumes `@factory/droid-core` for server-side tool execution.\n- The backend LLM proxy consumes provider implementations for streaming completions to the daemon.\n- See [features/llm-integration.md](../features/llm-integration.md) for the end-to-end LLM call path.\n\n## Entry points for modification\n\n- Adding a new tool → create a file in `packages/droid-core/src/tools/definitions/<group>/`, call `createTool()`, export from the group's `index.ts`, and add to `packages/droid-core/src/tools/definitions/index.ts`.\n- Adding a new LLM provider → implement `LanguageModelV1` in `packages/droid-core/src/llms/provider/<provider>/` and add it to the provider index.\n- Updating the streaming schema → edit `packages/droid-core/src/streaming/schema.ts` and `enums.ts`, then update any consumers that pattern-match on stream part types.\n- Modifying tool availability logic → update the `isToolEnabled` function on the relevant `FactoryTool` definition.\n",
