            "content": "# @factory/common — shared types and API contracts\n\n**Active contributors:** factory-sherry, factory-octavian, Luke Alvoeiro, l30t, Abhay Singhal, David Vendrow, Arman Bolat, Alvin Sng\n\n## Purpose\n\n`@factory/common` is the canonical source of truth for all shared TypeScript types, enums, Zod schemas, and API contracts in the monorepo. Every layer — CLI, daemon, backend, web, desktop — imports from this package to stay in sync on data shapes. It has no runtime dependencies beyond `zod` and imports from no other `@factory/*` package.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/common/src/\n├── agent/           # FirestoreAgentConfig and agent-level types\n├── agentReadiness/  # Readiness assessment types and enums\n├── api/\n│   ├── agent-readiness/\n│   ├── analytics/\n│   ├── backend/     # Backend HTTP API request/response types and Zod schemas\n│   ├── daemon/      # Daemon JSON-RPC heartbeat types\n│   ├── shared/      # Shared API utilities\n│   └── v0/          # Versioned public API: sessions, messages, git-ai, computers, organization, wiki\n├── automations/     # Automation types and enums\n├── billing/         # Billing plan types\n├── cli/             # CLI-specific types\n├── daemon/          # Daemon configuration and types\n├── desktop/         # Desktop-specific types\n├── documents/       # Document types\n├── droid/           # Droid protocol: JSON-RPC methods, MCP types, tool confirmation, mission decomposition\n├── events/          # Analytics event types\n├── feature-flags/   # FactoryFeatureFlags constants, dynamic config types\n├── images/          # Image types\n├── integrations/    # Integration type and delegation enums\n├── llm/             # ModelID enum, ReasoningEffort, ModelProvider, LLMModel types\n├── memory/          # Memory types\n├── node/            # Node infrastructure types\n├── organization/    # Org and workspace types\n├── policy/          # Security policy types\n├── relay/           # Relay enums, schemas, types\n├── repositories/    # Repository types\n├── security/        # Security constants\n├── session/         # Session types, message types, context, fragments, tools, JSONL events\n├── sessionV2/       # Next-generation session types\n├── settings/        # Settings types and enums\n├── shared/          # Cross-cutting enums (DroidMode, ClientType, etc.)\n├── tags/            # Session tag schema\n├── terminal/        # Terminal types\n├── timeline/        # Timeline event types\n├── tools/           # Tool execution enums and schemas\n├── ui/              # UI state types\n├── updater/         # Updater types\n├── usage/           # Token usage types\n├── wiki/            # Wiki types\n└── workspaces/      # Workspace types\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| Domain | Export path | Description |\n|--------|-------------|-------------|\n| **LLM types** | `@factory/common/llm` | `ModelID`, `ReasoningEffort`, `ModelProvider`, `ApiProvider`, `LLMModel`, `BillingPool` |\n| **Session types** | `@factory/common/session` | `FirestoreSession`, `SessionPrivacyLevel`, `DroidExecutionStatus`, `AssemblyMessageRole`, message types, fragment types, JSONL event types |\n| **Droid protocol** | `@factory/common/droid` | JSON-RPC method enums (`DroidClientMethod`, `DroidServerMethod`), `FactoryTool` confirmation types, MCP types, mission decomposition schemas |\n| **Feature flags** | `@factory/common/feature-flags` | `FactoryFeatureFlags` constant map, `DynamicConfigKey` types |\n| **API — backend** | `@factory/common/api/backend` | HTTP API request/response types and Zod schemas for backend routes |\n| **API — daemon** | `@factory/common/api/daemon` | `DaemonHeartbeatRequest`/`Response` |\n| **API — v0** | `@factory/common/api/v0/sessions` etc. | Versioned public API shapes: sessions, messages, git-ai, computers, wiki |\n| **Settings** | `@factory/common/settings` | User and org settings shapes |\n| **Integrations** | `@factory/common/integrations` | `IntegrationType` enum and delegation enums |\n| **Automations** | `@factory/common/automations` | Automation types |\n| **Relay** | `@factory/common/relay` | Relay connection enums and schemas |\n| **Organization** | `@factory/common/organization` | Org and workspace types |\n| **Shared** | `@factory/common/shared` | `DroidMode`, `ClientType`, `ToolExecutionLocation` and other cross-cutting enums |\n| **Tools** | `@factory/common/tools` | `ToolExecutionErrorType`, `ToolCallConfirmationStatus`, `GenericToolExecutionOutput` |\n| **Wiki** | `@factory/common/wiki` | Wiki types |\n| **Updater** | `@factory/common/updater` | Auto-updater types |\n\n## How it works\n\n### Export paths\n\n`@factory/common` uses named export paths rather than a single barrel. Each domain subdirectory exposes an `index.ts` that is mapped in `packages/common/package.json`'s `\"exports\"` field. For example:\n\n```ts\nimport { ModelID, ReasoningEffort } from '@factory/common/llm';\nimport { FirestoreSession, DroidExecutionStatus } from '@factory/common/session';\nimport { FactoryFeatureFlags } from '@factory/common/feature-flags';\n```\n\n### LLM model identifiers\n\n`ModelID` in `packages/common/src/llm/enums.ts` is the single authoritative enum of all supported model identifiers across Anthropic (Claude Sonnet/Opus/Haiku), OpenAI (GPT-5 family), and Google (Gemini 2.5/3 family). Model IDs are provider-independent strings; the provider and API endpoint are resolved by `@factory/utils/llm` or `@factory/models`.\n\n`ReasoningEffort` controls how much thinking a model does: `none`, `dynamic`, `off`, `minimal`, `low`, `medium`, `high`, `xhigh`, `max`.\n\n### Session types\n\nThe session domain (`packages/common/src/session/`) is the largest subdirectory. It defines:\n\n- `FirestoreSession` / `FirestoreSessionWithId` — Firestore document shape for sessions\n- `AssemblyMessageRole` — `user`, `assistant`, `tool`\n- `MessageContentType` — the variants of content within a message\n- `FactoryMessage` (union of `FactoryUserMessage`, `FactoryAssistantMessage`, `FactoryToolMessage`) — the canonical in-memory message type\n- Fragment types — `CodeFragment`, `DocumentFragment`, `HTMLFragment`, `SVGFragment`, `MermaidFragment`, with `FragmentWithSlug`\n- Context types — `FactoryContext`, `SearchedFile`, `SemanticSummary`\n- JSONL session event types — `DroidMessageEvent`, `SessionSummaryEvent`, `CompactionStateEvent`, `TodoStateEvent` (used by CLI/daemon for local session persistence)\n\n### Droid protocol types\n\n`packages/common/src/droid/` contains all JSON-RPC protocol types between the CLI/web client and the daemon, and between the daemon and the droid process:\n\n- `DroidClientMethod` / `DroidServerMethod` enums — method names for JSON-RPC calls\n- `InitializeSessionRequest`, `AddUserMessageRequest`, `InterruptSessionRequest`, etc.\n- Tool confirmation types — `ToolConfirmationDetails` union for all tool types that require user confirmation\n- MCP types — `StdioMCPServer`, `SseMCPServer`, `HttpMCPServer`, `McpServerStatus`, `McpAuthOutcome`\n- Mission decomposition — `MissionSnapshot`, `Handoff`, `WorkerHandoff`, `ProgressLogEntry`, `MissionFeature`\n\n### Feature flags\n\n`FactoryFeatureFlags` in `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts` is a typed constant object keyed by flag name. The `@factory/services/feature-flags` package resolves these flags against Statsig at runtime.\n\n## Integration points\n\n- Every app and package imports from `@factory/common` for shared types; it is the lowest-level `@factory/*` package.\n- Adding a new API endpoint requires types in `packages/common/src/api/<service>/types.ts` before implementing in `apps/backend`. See [how-to-contribute/patterns-and-conventions.md](../how-to-contribute/patterns-and-conventions.md).\n- Session types are used by `apps/daemon`, `apps/cli`, and `packages/frontend` to synchronize message and context state.\n- See [features/sessions.md](../features/sessions.md) for the full session lifecycle.\n\n## Entry points for modification\n\n- Adding a new LLM model → add a value to `ModelID` in `packages/common/src/llm/enums.ts`.\n- Adding a new feature flag → add a key to `FactoryFeatureFlags` in `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts`.\n- Adding a new API endpoint shape → create `packages/common/src/api/<service>/types.ts`, add the export path to `packages/common/package.json`, then implement in the relevant app.\n- Adding session message content → extend the appropriate union types in `packages/common/src/session/messages/types.ts`.\n- Adding a new droid JSON-RPC method → add a value to `DroidClientMethod` or `DroidServerMethod` in `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts` and add the request/response types in `packages/common/src/droid/types.ts`.\n",
