            "content": "# @factory/frontend — shared React feature modules\n\n**Active contributors:** Andrei Savin, Alvin Sng, factory-sherry, factory-octavian, Luke Alvoeiro, Nikita Lilichenko, Ricky S, jonathan-factory\n\n## Purpose\n\n`@factory/frontend` is the platform-agnostic React library shared between `apps/web` and `apps/desktop`. It owns the application shell, routing, authentication context, and all feature modules. Both the web app and the Electron desktop app mount the `RootApp` component from this package and pass in their platform-specific `AuthContextValue` and router instance.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/frontend/src/\n├── api/           # API client layer (React Query hooks and fetch utilities)\n├── app/           # App-level routing constants and provider config\n├── auth/          # AuthContext, WorkOS auth flow, auth pages\n├── errors/        # Error boundary components\n├── features/      # All 23 feature modules (see below)\n├── hooks/         # Shared hooks (useQueryParams, useIsDesktop, etc.)\n├── layouts/       # Main layout shell\n├── router/        # TanStack Router setup and route definitions\n│   ├── RootApp.tsx          # Top-level React entry point\n│   ├── initRouter.ts        # Creates a router instance for a given platform\n│   └── createAppRouter.ts   # Defines all routes (~50 routes)\n├── services/      # Platform services (telemetry, session utilities, console log collector)\n├── types/         # Shared frontend types\n├── utils/         # Environment helpers, other utilities\n└── views/         # Shared view components (LoadingView, etc.)\n```\n\n### Feature modules (`packages/frontend/src/features/`)\n\n| Module | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `analytics` | Activity dashboard, agent readiness, productivity, token usage, tools and user dashboards |\n| `attribution` | Signup attribution tracking |\n| `auth` | Auth feature components (separate from the auth/ directory) |\n| `automations` | Automation list, detail, visual viewer, controls; TanStack Query hooks |\n| `banner` | App-wide announcement banners |\n| `debug` | Debug page for internal tooling |\n| `e2e` | E2E test login page |\n| `error` | Not-found and other error pages |\n| `feature-flags` | Statsig feature flag context and hooks |\n| `ga-analytics` | Google Analytics script injection |\n| `health` | Health check page |\n| `home` | Home page (redirect logic) |\n| `missions` | Mission-mode session UI |\n| `onboarding` | Onboarding flow with step pages |\n| `referral` | Referral program page |\n| `sessions` | Session list, session detail, session atoms (Jotai), hooks, modules, providers, queries, mutations |\n| `settings` | General, billing, API keys, organization, integrations, computer, enterprise controls, usage, voucher, cloud template settings pages |\n| `support` | Support settings page |\n| `terminal` | Embedded xterm.js terminal feature |\n| `utility` | Login, logout, close, McpOAuthCallback pages |\n| `wiki` | Wiki reader and wiki page views |\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| Abstraction | Location | Description |\n|-------------|----------|-------------|\n| `RootApp` | `router/RootApp.tsx` | Top-level component; mounts Sentry, OTEL, GA, `AuthContextProvider`, `AppProvider`, `RouterProvider` |\n| `initRouter()` | `router/initRouter.ts` | Creates a TanStack Router instance with the platform-specific layout and home page component |\n| `createAppRouter()` | `router/createAppRouter.ts` | Defines all ~50 routes (authenticated and public) |\n| `AuthContextProvider` | `auth/AuthContext.provider.tsx` | React context providing `isAuthenticated`, `user`, and auth actions |\n| `AppProvider` | `router/App.provider.tsx` | Wraps TanStack Query's `QueryClientProvider`, theme, and toast providers |\n| `DaemonClient` (via `@factory/daemon-client`) | consumed in `features/sessions/services/` | WebSocket JSON-RPC client to `factoryd`; provides session init, messaging, interrupt, and settings methods |\n\n## How it works\n\n### Application shell and routing\n\n`RootApp` is initialized once per platform. `apps/web` calls `initRouter({ layout: MainLayout, homePage: SessionsPage })` and passes the result as the `router` prop. `apps/desktop` does the same with an Electron-specific layout.\n\nAll routes are defined in `packages/frontend/src/router/createAppRouter.ts` using TanStack Router's `createRoute` API. Protected routes are nested under an `_authenticated` layout route that redirects unauthenticated users to the home page. Notable routes:\n\n- `/sessions` → `SessionsPage` (session list)\n- `/sessions/:sessionId` → `SessionDetailPage` (full session view)\n- `/automations` → `AutomationsPage`\n- `/settings/*` → settings pages\n- `/wiki/*` → wiki pages\n- `/analytics/*` → analytics dashboards\n\n### Authentication\n\n`AuthContextProvider` wraps the entire app and exposes a `useAuthContext()` hook. WorkOS is the identity provider. The desktop app provides its auth implementation via Electron IPC; the web app uses browser-based redirects. The `AuthContextValue` interface (`apps/desktop` and `apps/web` each supply a concrete value) is exported from `packages/frontend/src/index.ts`.\n\n### Daemon client integration\n\nFeature modules in `features/sessions/` communicate with the daemon through `@factory/daemon-client`'s `DaemonClient`. This client manages a WebSocket connection to `factoryd` and exposes typed JSON-RPC methods (`initializeSession`, `addUserMessage`, `interruptSession`, `loadSession`, `updateSessionSettings`, MCP config methods, etc.). Session state is managed via Jotai atoms in `features/sessions/atoms/` and TanStack Query in `features/sessions/queries/`.\n\n### State management\n\n- **Global state**: TanStack Query (`@tanstack/react-query`) for server state and cache\n- **Local/UI state**: Jotai (`jotai`) atoms for session-level UI state\n- **Routing**: TanStack Router (`@tanstack/react-router`)\n- **Forms**: controlled inputs via `@factory/core-ui` primitives\n\n### Public API surface\n\n`packages/frontend/src/index.ts` exports a minimal surface for platform-specific integration:\n\n- `RootApp`, `LoadingView`, `initRouter`\n- Auth types (`AuthContextValue`, `WorkOSUser`, `ElectronAPI`, etc.)\n- Automations feature: all views, queries, hooks, and types needed by the desktop app's automation panel\n\n## Integration points\n\n- `apps/web` mounts `RootApp` with browser auth and Vite env config.\n- `apps/desktop` mounts `RootApp` with Electron IPC auth and injects the Electron API.\n- `@factory/daemon-client` provides the WebSocket transport; see [packages/other-packages.md](./other-packages.md).\n- `@factory/core-ui` provides all UI primitives; see [packages/core-ui.md](./core-ui.md).\n- `@factory/component-library` provides chat rendering, diff viewer, and Mermaid diagrams used inside `features/sessions/`.\n- See [features/sessions.md](../features/sessions.md) for the full session feature architecture.\n- See [apps/web.md](../apps/web.md) and [apps/desktop.md](../apps/desktop.md) for consumer-specific configurations.\n\n## Entry points for modification\n\n- Adding a new page/route → create a page component in `features/<feature>/pages/`, add a route in `packages/frontend/src/router/createAppRouter.ts`, and add the route constant to `packages/frontend/src/app/routing/constants.ts`.\n- Adding a new feature module → create `packages/frontend/src/features/<name>/` with `pages/`, `components/`, `hooks/`, `queries/`, `mutations/` as needed, then wire the route.\n- Adding a new settings page → add to `features/settings/pages/` and add a route under the `/settings` parent in `createAppRouter.ts`.\n- Exposing a feature for desktop integration → add exports to `packages/frontend/src/index.ts`.\n",
