            "content": "# Other packages\n\nThis page gives a brief overview of the smaller packages in `packages/` that are not covered by the dedicated pages for `@factory/common`, `@factory/core-ui`, `@factory/droid-core`, and `@factory/frontend`.\n\n---\n\n## @factory/services\n\n**Active contributors:** Alvin Sng, Arman Bolat, Nikita Lilichenko, l30t, factory-sherry\n\n**Purpose**: Adapters for external services. Consumed by the backend, daemon, and CLI — never directly by frontend UI.\n\n**Export paths:**\n- `@factory/services/feature-flags` — Statsig feature flag client wrapper\n- `@factory/services/settings` — Settings persistence helpers\n- `@factory/services/plugins` — Plugin registry for droid capabilities\n- `@factory/services/session-search` — Local session search indexing\n- `@factory/services/firebase/*` — Firebase Admin SDK and Firestore helpers\n- `@factory/services/aws/*` — AWS S3, SQS, Secrets Manager clients\n- `@factory/services/anthropic` — Anthropic SDK wrapper\n- `@factory/services/openai` — OpenAI SDK wrapper\n- `@factory/services/workos/*` — WorkOS auth utilities\n- `@factory/services/stripe/*` — Stripe billing helpers\n- `@factory/services/orb/*` — Orb billing helpers\n- `@factory/services/slack/*` — Slack API helpers\n- `@factory/services/gcp/*` — GCP PubSub and Storage clients\n- `@factory/services/utils/encryption` — AES encryption utilities\n\n**Key dependencies:** `firebase-admin`, `@aws-sdk/*`, `@google-cloud/*`, `stripe`, `jose`, `chokidar`, `simple-git`.\n\n---\n\n## @factory/models\n\n**Active contributors:** Alvin Sng, Nikita Lilichenko, factory-sherry, Luke Alvoeiro, David Vendrow\n\n**Purpose**: Firestore document schema types and Firestore document models for all collections. Used by the backend and daemon to read/write Firestore. Not imported by frontend UI.\n\n**Directory:** `packages/models/src/` contains subdirectories per collection: `organization/`, `session/`, `sessionV2/`, `repositories/`, `integrations/`, `memory/`, `factoryApiKeys/`, `workspace/`, `referrals/`, `promotions/`, `agent/`, `events/`, `cardFingerprints/`, `deletedOrganization/`.\n\n---\n\n## @factory/daemon-core\n\n**Active contributors:** factory-jerry, factory-sherry, shashank-factory, Luke Alvoeiro, factory-octavian\n\n**Purpose**: The core runtime logic of the `factoryd` daemon process. Handles session lifecycle management, relay connections, terminal (xterm headless), automations, code-server integration, and the server-side JSON-RPC request handler.\n\n**Export paths:**\n- `@factory/daemon-core` — main index (session manager, request handler, server setup)\n- `@factory/daemon-core/automations` — automation scheduler\n\n**Key dependencies:** `bun-pty` (pseudoterminal), `@xterm/headless`, `@xterm/addon-serialize`, `jose`, `@factory/droid-sdk`, `@factory/runtime`.\n\n**Directory:** `packages/daemon-core/src/` contains `droid/`, `relay/`, `server/`, `terminal/`, `automations/`, `services/`, `utils/`, `code-server/`.\n\n---\n\n## @factory/daemon-client\n\n**Active contributors:** factory-sherry, shashank-factory, Ricky S, factory-jerry, Luke Alvoeiro\n\n**Purpose**: The WebSocket JSON-RPC client used by `apps/web` and `apps/desktop` (via `@factory/frontend`) to communicate with the `factoryd` daemon. Exposes a fully typed `DaemonClient` class that mirrors every daemon method.\n\n**Key files:**\n- `packages/daemon-client/src/DaemonClient.ts` — ~1 500 line typed client with methods for session management, MCP config, terminal, file browsing, session search, automations, and more\n- `packages/daemon-client/src/WebSocketConnection.ts` — reconnecting WebSocket transport\n- `packages/daemon-client/src/errors.ts` — typed client errors\n\n**Imported by:** `@factory/frontend` (indirectly), `apps/web`, `apps/desktop`.\n\n---\n\n## @factory/runtime\n\n**Active contributors:** factory-davidgu, factory-jerry, Alvin Sng, Abhay Singhal\n\n**Purpose**: Authentication utilities for Node/Bun runtimes. Handles WorkOS access token storage, refresh, and verification using `jose` (JWT). Optionally integrates with OS keychain via `keytar`.\n\n**Export path:** `@factory/runtime/auth`\n\n**Key dependencies:** `jose`, `atomically`, `keytar` (optional), `@factory/services`, `@factory/environment`.\n\n**Used by:** `apps/cli`, `apps/daemon`, `@factory/daemon-core`.\n\n---\n\n## @factory/logging\n\n**Active contributors:** Alvin Sng, factory-sherry, l30t, theo, factory-octavian\n\n**Purpose**: Structured logging, metrics counters, Sentry error reporting, and OpenTelemetry tracing for all runtime environments (browser and Node/Bun).\n\n**Export paths:**\n- `@factory/logging` — main logger (`log`, `createLogger`), `setSentryAdapter`\n- `@factory/logging/node` — Node-specific logger (Pino-based)\n- `@factory/logging/errors` — typed error classes\n- `@factory/logging/sentry` — Sentry adapter setup\n- `@factory/logging/metrics/*` — metrics counters\n- `@factory/logging/tracing` — OpenTelemetry tracing helpers\n- `@factory/logging/outcome-recorder` — records task outcome metrics\n\n**Key dependencies:** `pino`, `@opentelemetry/api`, `@opentelemetry/core`.\n\n---\n\n## @factory/updater\n\n**Active contributors:** factory-sherry, shashank-factory, factory-jerry, Alvin Sng, Leo Tchourakov\n\n**Purpose**: Semver-based auto-update logic shared between `apps/cli` and `apps/daemon`. Checks a remote config URL for a newer version, downloads it, and reports the outcome.\n\n**Exports:** `Updater` class, `UpdateOutcome` enum, `UpdaterConfig` / `UpdaterState` / `UpdateInfo` types.\n\n**Key dependencies:** `semver`.\n\n---\n\n## @factory/environment\n\n**Active contributors:** factory-jerry, factory-davidgu, factory-sherry, Arman Bolat, Alvin Sng\n\n**Purpose**: Typed environment variable resolution with a provider-injection pattern (useful for testing). Avoids direct `process.env` access across the codebase (enforced by the `no-direct-process-env` lint rule).\n\n**Exports:** `createEnvironment()`, `requireEnv()`, `resolveEnv()`, `parseBooleanEnv()`, `getEnvironment()`, `setEnvironmentProvider()`, `FactoryEnv` / `DeploymentEnv` enums, `EnvironmentVariable` constants.\n\n**Used by:** almost every `@factory/*` package and all apps. See [how-to-contribute/patterns-and-conventions.md](../how-to-contribute/patterns-and-conventions.md) for the migration guide from raw `process.env`.\n\n---\n\n## @factory/utils\n\n**Active contributors:** Alvin Sng, Nikita Lilichenko, factory-sherry, Luke Alvoeiro, David Vendrow\n\n**Purpose**: Pure utility functions with no side effects, organized by domain.\n\n**Export paths:**\n- `@factory/utils/format` — string formatting helpers\n- `@factory/utils/time` — date/time utilities\n- `@factory/utils/promise` — async helpers\n- `@factory/utils/text` — text manipulation, PDF extraction (`unpdf`)\n- `@factory/utils/llm` — `getLLMModel()`, model registry, default model resolution\n- `@factory/utils/models` — model capability helpers\n- `@factory/utils/shell` — shell command parsing\n- `@factory/utils/fuzzy` — fuzzy search via `fuse.js`\n- `@factory/utils/messages` — message utility functions\n- `@factory/utils/security` — secret scrubbing, CSP config\n- `@factory/utils/mcp` — MCP server utilities\n- `@factory/utils/skills` — Droid skill helpers\n- `@factory/utils/session` — session utility functions\n- `@factory/utils/api` — `apiFetch` and API config\n- `@factory/utils/billing`, `./usage`, `./stats`, `./autonomy` — various business logic helpers\n\n---\n\n## @factory/mcp\n\n**Status**: Empty placeholder. MCP tooling lives in `@factory/utils/mcp`.\n\n---\n\n## @factory/signal-core\n\n**Active contributors:** Abhay Singhal, factory-jerry\n\n**Purpose**: Signal definitions, Zod schemas, and registry for the analytics batch pipeline and Admin UI. Defines which events and facets are tracked.\n\n**Export paths:**\n- `@factory/signal-core/enums` — signal type enums\n- `@factory/signal-core/constants` — signal constants\n- `@factory/signal-core/types` — signal types\n- `@factory/signal-core/schema` — Zod schemas\n- `@factory/signal-core/signals/registry` — signal registry\n- `@factory/signal-core/signals/facets` — facet definitions\n\n**Peer dependency:** `@google-cloud/bigquery` (optional; used only in the pipeline worker).\n\n---\n\n## @factory/test-utils\n\n**Active contributors:** Ricky S, factory-jerry\n\n**Purpose**: Shared test mocks and helpers for browser and Node test environments.\n\n**Export paths:**\n- `@factory/test-utils/browser-mocks` — mock implementations for browser globals\n- `@factory/test-utils/node-mocks` — mock implementations for Node APIs\n- `@factory/test-utils/mocks` — general mocks\n\n**Used by:** packages that run Vitest browser-environment tests.\n\n---\n\n## @factory/droid-sdk\n\n**Active contributors:** factory-sherry, Luke Alvoeiro, factory-jerry, factory-octavian, Ricky S\n\n**Purpose**: TypeScript SDK for driving droid exec processes programmatically. Intended for use by external tooling, CI workers, and integration tests that need to launch and communicate with a Droid session without a full daemon setup.\n\n**Exports:** `DroidClient`, `ProcessTransport`, `DroidProcessManager`, `DroidProcessMode`, error classes (`ConnectionError`, `ProcessExitError`, `SessionNotFoundError`, `TimeoutError`).\n\n**Key files:**\n- `packages/droid-sdk/src/client.ts` — `DroidClient`: manages a session lifecycle over a transport\n- `packages/droid-sdk/src/process-transport.ts` — `ProcessTransport`: spawns a droid process and communicates via stdin/stdout JSON-RPC\n- `packages/droid-sdk/src/DroidProcessManager.ts` — manages multiple concurrent droid processes\n\nSee [apps/cli/index.md](../apps/cli/index.md) for how the CLI consumes this SDK.\n\n---\n\n## @factory/eslint-config\n\n**Purpose**: Shared ESLint configuration for all packages and apps. Enforces conventions such as:\n- No raw `<div>`, `<button>`, `<input>` in TSX (use `@factory/core-ui` instead)\n- Enums in `enums.ts`, types in `types.ts`\n- API types in `@factory/common/src/api/<service>/types.ts`\n- Absolute imports only\n- No `require()` calls\n- No direct `process.env` access (use `@factory/environment`)\n\nDev-only dependency; not included in production bundles.\n\n---\n\n## @factory/component-library\n\n**Active contributors:** Andrei Savin, Ricky S, Luke Alvoeiro, factory-sherry, Nikita Lilichenko\n\n**Purpose**: Reusable layout-focused React components that sit above `@factory/core-ui` primitives. Contains the chat UI rendering pipeline and diff viewer used in session views.\n\n**Key exports:**\n- `MessageMarkdownDisplay` — renders assistant/user markdown messages\n- `SyntaxHighlightedCode` — syntax-highlighted code blocks (`highlight.js`)\n- `MermaidDiagram` — renders Mermaid diagrams via `beautiful-mermaid`\n- `DiffViewer`, `DiffLine`, `DiffSkipBlock` — unified diff rendering\n- `DiffViewerPanel`, `SemanticDiffView` — full-featured diff panel\n- `DiffCommentForm`, `DiffCommentDisplay` — inline diff comments\n\n**Key dependencies:** `beautiful-mermaid`, `react-markdown`, `remark-gfm`, `highlight.js`, `gitdiff-parser`, `diff`, `recharts`, `typewriter-effect`, `ansi-to-react`.\n\n**Used by:** `apps/web`, `apps/desktop` via `@factory/frontend`.\n\n---\n\n## @factory/ui\n\n**Status**: Empty placeholder.\n",
