            "content": "# Development workflow\n\nThis page covers the full cycle from setting up a dev environment to landing a PR.\n\n## Environment setup\n\nSee [Getting started](../overview/getting-started.md) for the install steps. In brief:\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/Factory-AI/factory-mono.git\ncd factory-mono\nnpm install       # also runs postinstall → npm run setup\n```\n\nRequired tools:\n- **Node.js 18.x** — use `.nvmrc` with `nvm use`\n- **npm 11+** — `packageManager: \"npm@11.2.0\"` is pinned in `package.json`\n- **Bun 1.3.10** — required for CLI and daemon\n\n## Branch naming\n\nBranch from `dev`, not `main`:\n\n```bash\ngit checkout dev\ngit pull origin dev\ngit checkout -b alice/FAC-1234-short-description\n```\n\nBranch name constraints (enforced by the pre-push hook and CI):\n- ≤ 32 characters\n- Letters, numbers, hyphens, and slashes only\n- Conventional format: `<handle>/<ticket>-description`\n\nExamples: `alice/FAC-1234-add-webhook`, `bob/FAC-5678-fix-sidebar-scroll`\n\n## Starting the dev servers\n\nDo **not** run `npm run dev` at the root — it is intentionally disabled and will exit with an error.\n\n| Command | What it starts |\n|---|---|\n| `npm run dev:web` | backend (3000), web (3002), admin (3001), storybook, daemon — works over SSH |\n| `npm run dev:desktop` | same as `dev:web` plus the Electron desktop app — local only |\n\nDev server output is streamed to both the console and log files:\n\n| App | Log file |\n|---|---|\n| backend | `/tmp/factory-dev-backend.log` |\n| admin | `/tmp/factory-dev-admin.log` |\n| daemon | `/tmp/factory-dev-daemon.log` |\n| desktop | `/tmp/factory-dev-desktop.log` |\n\nStream a log live: `tail -f /tmp/factory-dev-backend.log`\n\n## Making changes\n\n### Web and backend\n\nStart `npm run dev:web`, then edit files. Vite (web) and Next.js (backend, admin) both hot-reload on save — no rebuild needed between changes.\n\n### CLI and daemon\n\nThe CLI runs on Bun and does **not** hot-reload. After changing CLI or daemon code, rebuild before testing:\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli && npm run setup\n```\n\nThis installs a `droid-dev` binary (connects to hosted dev API) and a `droid-localhost` binary (connects to local backend). To run against local backend, ensure `npm run dev:web` is also running:\n\n```bash\ndroid-dev        # against hosted dev API\ndroid-localhost  # against local backend at localhost:3000\n```\n\nAfter changing `packages/common` (shared types, schemas, enums), rebuild the CLI as well since it reads from those packages at build time.\n\n### Shared packages\n\nChanges to `packages/*` are picked up automatically by web and backend (they import source directly via TypeScript path aliases). The CLI and daemon require a rebuild as described above.\n\n## Running checks locally\n\n### Correct filter syntax\n\n**Always use `--` before `--filter`** when running npm scripts that call Turborepo. Without `--`, npm consumes the flag silently and Turborepo runs every workspace — a full `test` or `typecheck` run consumes ~9 GB of RAM.\n\n```bash\n# Correct\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/frontend\nnpm run typecheck -- --filter=@factory/droid-core\nnpm run build -- --filter=apps/web\n\n# Wrong — npm eats --filter, turbo runs everything\nnpm run test --filter=@factory/frontend\n```\n\nMultiple filters are additive:\n\n```bash\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/common --filter=@factory/daemon-core\n```\n\n### Common local checks\n\n```bash\nnpm run fix                              # lint + format (preferred, runs prettier + ESLint)\nnpm run typecheck -- --filter=<package>  # TypeScript checking\nnpm run test -- --filter=<package>       # run tests for one package\nnpm run knip                             # detect unused exports\n```\n\nFor the full project (e.g., before opening a PR):\n\n```bash\nnpm run fix\nnpm run typecheck\n```\n\nRun a single test file without going through Turborepo:\n\n```bash\n# Jest (CLI, backend, most packages)\ncd apps/cli && npx jest src/path/to/file.test.ts\n\n# Vitest (frontend packages)\ncd packages/frontend && npx vitest run src/path/to/file.test.ts\n```\n\n## Testing changes by app\n\n### Web (`apps/web`)\n\n1. Start `npm run dev:web`\n2. Open `http://localhost:3002`\n3. Interact with the UI; Vite hot-reloads on save\n\nFor E2E: see [testing — Playwright](./testing.md#playwright-web-e2e).\n\n### Backend (`apps/backend`)\n\n1. Start `npm run dev:web`\n2. Backend listens at `http://localhost:3000`\n3. Test API endpoints with `curl` or a tool like Postman\n\nTail the log for runtime errors:\n```bash\ntail -f /tmp/factory-dev-backend.log\n```\n\n### CLI (`apps/cli`)\n\n1. Rebuild after every code change: `cd apps/cli && npm run setup`\n2. Run `droid-dev` or `droid-localhost` to test interactively\n3. Run unit tests: `cd apps/cli && npx jest src/...`\n4. Run TUI E2E tests: `cd apps/cli && npx tui-test e2e-tests/`\n\nSee [apps/cli](../apps/cli/index.md) for CLI-specific development details.\n\n### Daemon (`apps/daemon`)\n\nDaemon code changes require rebuilding the CLI (which bundles the daemon):\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli && npm run setup\n# Then restart: kill the running daemon and run droid-dev\n```\n\nCheck daemon logs:\n```bash\ntail -f ~/.factory-dev/logs/factoryd.log\n```\n\n## Opening a PR\n\n1. Push your branch: `git push -u origin <branch-name>`\n2. Open a PR targeting `dev` (not `main`)\n3. Fill in the PR template (description, related issue, risk, how tested)\n4. CI runs automatically: lint, typecheck, tests, PR conventions check\n\nPR title must follow Conventional Commits format — see [index](./index.md#pr-conventions).\n\n## Merge\n\nSquash-merge is the default. After CI passes and you have at least one approval, merge. The Linear ticket closes automatically if the description includes `Closes FAC-*`.\n\nDo not merge to `main` directly — all changes flow through `dev` first.\n",
