            "content": "# Testing\n\nThis page covers unit tests, E2E tests, and how to run them.\n\n## Frameworks by app/package\n\n| Target | Framework | Config |\n|---|---|---|\n| `apps/cli` | Jest (via ts-jest, ESM preset) | `apps/cli/jest.config.cjs` |\n| `apps/backend` | Jest | `apps/backend/jest.config.*` |\n| `apps/daemon` | Jest | `apps/daemon/jest.config.*` |\n| `packages/frontend` | Vitest | `packages/frontend/vite.config.*` |\n| Other packages | Jest | per-package `jest.config.*` |\n| CLI E2E | `@microsoft/tui-test` | `apps/cli/tui-test.config.ts` |\n| Web E2E | Playwright | `apps/web/playwright.config.ts` |\n\n## Running tests\n\n### Targeted runs (preferred)\n\nAlways use `--` before `--filter` to pass the flag through npm to Turborepo. Without it, npm silently discards `--filter` and Turborepo runs every workspace — consuming ~9 GB of RAM.\n\n```bash\n# Run tests for a single package\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/frontend\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/common --filter=@factory/daemon-core\n\n# Run all tests (warning: resource-intensive)\nnpm run test\n```\n\n### Single file\n\n```bash\n# Jest packages (CLI, backend, most packages)\ncd apps/cli && npx jest src/path/to/file.test.ts\n\n# Vitest packages (frontend)\ncd packages/frontend && npx vitest run src/path/to/file.test.ts\n```\n\n### CLI E2E tests (TUI)\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli && npx tui-test e2e-tests/\n```\n\nThe TUI test config (`tui-test.config.ts`) uses Bash on macOS/Linux and PowerShell on Windows. Timeout is 120 s locally, 240 s in CI.\n\n### Web E2E tests (Playwright)\n\n```bash\ncd apps/web\n\n# Install browsers (first time only)\nnpm run e2e:install\n\n# Run all E2E tests\nnpm run e2e\n\n# Interactive UI mode\nnpm run e2e:ui\n\n# Run a specific test by name pattern\nnpm run e2e -- --grep \"test name pattern\"\n```\n\nPlaywright tests live in `apps/web/e2e/`. The config runs against `http://localhost:3002` and requires the dev server to be up. See `docs/playwright-e2e-testing.md` for auth setup and selector patterns.\n\n## Unit test patterns\n\n### jsdom environment for frontend tests\n\nAny test that uses React hooks, DOM APIs, or browser globals needs the jsdom environment declared at the top of the file:\n\n```typescript\n/**\n * @jest-environment jsdom\n */\n\nimport { renderHook } from '@testing-library/react';\nimport { useMyHook } from './useMyHook';\n```\n\nOmitting this causes `ReferenceError: document is not defined`. This applies to React hook tests, atom tests, component tests, and any test using `@testing-library/react`.\n\n### Mocking with `jest.requireActual`\n\nAlways use static top-level `jest.mock()` with `...jest.requireActual()` to preserve real behavior for unrelated functions. Never use bare auto-mocking or `jest.doMock`.\n\n```typescript\nimport { fetchTeamId, fetchTickets } from './linearApi';\n\njest.mock('./linearApi', () => ({\n  ...jest.requireActual('./linearApi'),\n  fetchTeamId: jest.fn(),\n  fetchTickets: jest.fn(),\n}));\n\nbeforeEach(() => {\n  jest.resetAllMocks();\n});\n\nit('maps tickets correctly', async () => {\n  (fetchTeamId as jest.Mock).mockResolvedValue({ id: 'team-123' });\n  (fetchTickets as jest.Mock).mockResolvedValue([{ title: 'Task', date: '2025-01-01' }]);\n\n  const result = await getItems('org-123');\n\n  expect(result).toEqual([{ name: 'Task', dueDate: new Date('2025-01-01') }]);\n});\n```\n\nKey rules:\n- Call `jest.resetAllMocks()` in `beforeEach` — reapplies default stubs every test\n- Set per-test behavior with `mockResolvedValue` / `mockImplementation` inside each `it`\n- Declare shared variables in the `describe` scope and initialize in `beforeEach` to avoid duplication\n\n### Singleton and cache testing\n\nFor modules with cached instances, use module isolation instead of exported reset functions:\n\n```typescript\n// Good: module isolation\nbeforeEach(() => {\n  jest.resetModules();\n});\n\nit('creates a fresh instance', async () => {\n  const { getService } = await import('./service');\n  // fresh module each time\n});\n\n// Bad: exported reset function (pollutes production API)\nimport { resetInstance } from './service';\nbeforeEach(() => resetInstance());\n```\n\n### What to mock vs. what to run real\n\n**Mock:** HTTP clients, database/ORM calls, filesystem access, external APIs, anything non-deterministic.\n\n**Run real:** pure helpers, formatters, lodash-like utilities, logging calls.\n\nNever mock or assert on `@factory/logging` — it couples tests to implementation details rather than behavior.\n\n### Avoid conditional expects\n\nPut `expect()` at the top level of `it()` blocks, not inside conditionals:\n\n```typescript\n// Bad — may silently pass if condition is never true\nit('handles response', async () => {\n  const result = await someApiCall();\n  if (result.success) {\n    expect(result.data).toBeDefined();\n  }\n});\n\n// Good\nit('throws on invalid input', async () => {\n  await expect(riskyOperation('invalid')).rejects.toThrow();\n});\n```\n\n### Fixtures\n\nUse factory functions with an `overrides` parameter for test data:\n\n```typescript\n// fixtures.ts\nexport const subscriptionFixture = (overrides: Partial<Subscription> = {}): Subscription => ({\n  id: 'sub_123',\n  organizationId: 'org_123',\n  status: 'active',\n  plan: 'standard',\n  ...overrides,\n});\n\n// In tests\nconst sub = subscriptionFixture({ status: 'past_due' });\n```\n\nUse global search for `fixtures.ts` to find existing fixtures before creating new ones.\n\n## Coverage\n\nThe CLI has a coverage threshold of 25% line coverage (`apps/cli/jest.config.cjs`). Coverage reports are generated in `coverage/` under each package:\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli && npx jest --coverage\n```\n\nCoverage excludes constants, enums, index files, and entry points by convention.\n\n## CI test runs\n\nOn every PR:\n- `test.yml` runs all tests except `backend` and `@factory/cli` (those have dedicated workflows)\n- `test-cli.yml` runs CLI-specific tests\n- `test-backend.yml` runs backend tests\n- `cli-e2e-tests.yml` runs the TUI E2E suite\n- `playwright-e2e.yml` and `playwright-e2e-critical.yml` run Playwright tests\n\n## Related\n\n- [apps/cli](../apps/cli/index.md) — CLI development and TUI testing details\n- [Patterns and conventions](./patterns-and-conventions.md) — module-level conventions\n- `docs/unit-tests.md` — full unit test specification\n- `docs/playwright-e2e-testing.md` — Playwright setup and auth patterns\n",
