            "content": "# Debugging\n\nThis page covers log locations, common errors, and a troubleshooting runbook for CLI, daemon, backend, and web.\n\n## Architecture overview\n\n```\nWeb frontend (DaemonSessionController.ts)\n    ↓ WebSocket JSON-RPC\nDaemon (droid-request-handler.ts)\n    ↓ stdin/stdout JSON-RPC\nCLI (streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.tsx)\n```\n\nUnderstanding which layer an issue lives in determines where to look.\n\n## Log file locations\n\n### Dev server logs (streamed to disk)\n\nWhen `npm run dev:web` or `npm run dev:desktop` is running, each app writes to:\n\n| App | Log file |\n|---|---|\n| backend | `/tmp/factory-dev-backend.log` |\n| admin | `/tmp/factory-dev-admin.log` |\n| daemon | `/tmp/factory-dev-daemon.log` |\n| desktop | `/tmp/factory-dev-desktop.log` |\n\nStream a log live:\n```bash\ntail -f /tmp/factory-dev-backend.log\n```\n\nSearch for errors:\n```bash\ngrep -i error /tmp/factory-dev-backend.log\n```\n\n### CLI and daemon session logs\n\n| Environment | Directory | Key files |\n|---|---|---|\n| Development | `~/.factory-dev/logs/` | `factoryd.log`, `droid-log-single.log`, `console.log` |\n| Production | `~/.factory/logs/` | Same files |\n\n**Important:** dev logs go to `~/.factory-dev/`, not `~/.factory/`. Checking the wrong directory is a common source of confusion.\n\nWatch all session logs at once:\n```bash\ntail -f ~/.factory-dev/logs/*.log\n```\n\nTrace a specific message through the stack:\n```bash\n# 1. Check whether CLI emitted it\ngrep \"your-feature\" ~/.factory-dev/logs/droid-log-single.log\n\n# 2. Check whether daemon received or forwarded it\ngrep \"your-feature\" ~/.factory-dev/logs/factoryd.log\n```\n\n## Quick debug checklist\n\nWhen something isn't working after a CLI or daemon change:\n\n- [ ] Rebuilt CLI: `cd apps/cli && npm run setup`\n- [ ] Restarted daemon process (kill and relaunch)\n- [ ] Started a **new** session (existing sessions don't pick up new builds)\n- [ ] Checking the right log directory (`~/.factory-dev/` for dev builds)\n- [ ] Schema/enum changes are in `@factory/common` (not just in the CLI)\n- [ ] Frontend handler exists for the notification type\n\n## Common issues\n\n### Changes not appearing after edit\n\nThe CLI does not hot-reload. Every code change requires a rebuild:\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli && npm run setup\n```\n\nThen kill the daemon and start a new session.\n\n### Schema mismatches (notification not received by frontend)\n\nIf the CLI sends a notification but the frontend never receives it:\n\n1. Notification type is in `SessionNotificationType` enum in `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts`\n2. Schema is defined in `packages/common/src/droid/schemas/cli.ts`\n3. A handler exists in `packages/frontend/src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts`\n\n### Timing issues (notifications dropped on startup)\n\nNotifications sent before the session is registered with the daemon are silently dropped. Always emit notifications after session initialization completes, not during startup.\n\n### Dev vs. prod confusion\n\nIf you're seeing stale behavior and aren't sure which build is running:\n\n1. Run `which droid-dev` and confirm it points to a recently built binary\n2. Check `~/.factory-dev/logs/` rather than `~/.factory/logs/`\n3. Confirm the daemon you restarted is the dev daemon, not a production install\n\n## Adding debug logging\n\nUse `@factory/logging` for all log calls. Never use `console.log` in production code — the CLI patches `console.*` to redirect to the logging system.\n\n```typescript\nimport { logInfo, logWarn, logException } from '@factory/logging';\n\nlogInfo('[Feature] Event received', { count: items.length });\nlogWarn('[Feature] Retrying after timeout', { attempt });\n```\n\nLog context before risky calls, not after. If you call `logException`, handle the error locally and don't rethrow. See [Patterns and conventions](./patterns-and-conventions.md) for the full error-handling rules.\n\n## Backend debugging\n\nBackend runs at `http://localhost:3000`. Tail the log for runtime errors:\n\n```bash\ntail -f /tmp/factory-dev-backend.log\n```\n\nFor Next.js API routes, check the terminal output for stack traces on 500 errors. The backend uses Sentry in production — see [how-to-monitor/logging.md](../how-to-monitor/logging.md) for Sentry setup.\n\n## Frontend debugging\n\nThe web app runs at `http://localhost:3002`. Browser DevTools is the primary tool.\n\nFor WebSocket communication between frontend and daemon, open the Network tab and filter by WS. The JSON-RPC messages between `DaemonSessionController.ts` and the daemon are visible there.\n\n## CLI debugging\n\n### Using droid-dev directly\n\nThe `droid-dev` wrapper runs CLI source via Bun — changes are immediately reflected without rebuilding (for Bun-executed code). For compiled output, still run `npm run setup`.\n\n### Enabling verbose output\n\nMost CLI commands accept a `--debug` flag or environment variable. Check the specific command's source for supported flags.\n\n### TUI rendering issues\n\nIf the terminal UI renders incorrectly, try:\n\n```bash\n# Resize terminal and restart\ndroid-dev\n\n# Or run in a wider terminal\nCOLUMNS=120 LINES=50 droid-dev\n```\n\n## Key files for cross-layer debugging\n\n| Layer | Key files |\n|---|---|\n| Protocol (shared) | `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts`, `packages/common/src/droid/schemas/` |\n| CLI | `apps/cli/src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.tsx` |\n| Daemon | `apps/daemon/src/server/handlers/droid-request-handler.ts` |\n| Frontend | `packages/frontend/src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` |\n\n## Related\n\n- `docs/debugging-daemon.md` — source of truth for CLI/daemon/frontend debugging\n- [how-to-monitor/logging.md](../how-to-monitor/logging.md) — logging infrastructure and Sentry\n- [apps/cli](../apps/cli/index.md) — CLI development details\n",
