            "content": "# Tooling\n\nThis page covers the build system, package manager, linting, formatting, type checking, and pre-commit hooks.\n\n## Build system — Turborepo\n\nThe repo uses [Turborepo](https://turbo.build) (`turbo.json`) for task orchestration across workspaces. All top-level `npm run` scripts delegate to `turbo run <task>`.\n\nKey Turborepo behaviors:\n- **Caching** — build outputs are cached by input hashes. `build` is cached; `typecheck`, `lint`, `fix`, `test` are not (set `\"cache\": false` in `turbo.json`).\n- **Concurrency** — `fix` and `lint` run with `--concurrency 2`; `build` runs all tasks in dependency order.\n- **`--continue`** — most top-level scripts pass `--continue` so failures in one workspace don't abort others.\n\n### Filtering (important)\n\n**Always use `--` before `--filter`** when running npm scripts. Without `--`, npm absorbs the flag and turbo runs all workspaces.\n\n```bash\n# Correct — filter is passed through to turbo\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/frontend\nnpm run build -- --filter=apps/web\nnpm run typecheck -- --filter=@factory/droid-core\n\n# Wrong — npm eats --filter, all workspaces run\nnpm run test --filter=@factory/frontend\n```\n\nMultiple filters stack:\n```bash\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/common --filter=@factory/daemon-core\n```\n\n### Direct turbo invocation\n\nFor advanced filtering you can invoke turbo directly:\n```bash\nnpm exec turbo -- run test --filter=apps/cli --no-cache\n```\n\n## Package manager — npm workspaces\n\nThe repo uses npm workspaces with npm 11. Workspaces are declared in the root `package.json`:\n\n```\napps/*\npackages/*\ninternal/apps/*\ninternal/packages/*\ninternal/web\n```\n\nDependencies are hoisted to the root `node_modules` by default. To install a dependency in a specific workspace:\n\n```bash\nnpm install <package> --workspace=apps/cli\n```\n\nBun (`bun.lock` exists at the root) is used for CLI and daemon bundling, but npm is the primary package manager for the monorepo.\n\n## Linting — ESLint\n\nESLint is configured via `@factory/eslint-config` (`packages/eslint-config/`). Each workspace extends one of the preset configurations:\n\n| Preset | Target |\n|---|---|\n| `@factory/eslint-config/factory-package` | Shared packages in `packages/*` |\n| `@factory/eslint-config/frontend` | Frontend packages |\n| `@factory/eslint-config/vite-app` | Vite apps (e.g., `apps/web`) |\n| `@factory/eslint-config/backend` | Non-Next.js apps |\n| `@factory/eslint-config/factory-next` | Next.js apps (backend, admin) |\n\nEach preset automatically registers the `factory` ESLint plugin — you don't need to add it separately.\n\nKey rules enforced:\n- Enums in `enums.ts`, types in `types.ts`\n- Absolute imports only (`@factory/...`, `@/...`) — no `../../utils`\n- No `require()` — ES6 `import` only\n- No raw `<div>`, `<button>`, `<input>` in UI code — use `@factory/core-ui` components\n- No hardcoded colors — use `colors.semantics`\n- No direct `process.env` access — use the typed `@factory/environment` system\n\nRun lint:\n```bash\nnpm run lint                          # lint only, all workspaces\nnpm run lint -- --filter=apps/web     # lint one workspace\n```\n\nRun lint + autofix:\n```bash\nnpm run fix                           # preferred; lint + format together\n```\n\n## Formatting — Prettier\n\nPrettier is configured at the root. It runs automatically as part of `npm run fix` and via the pre-commit hook (runs only on staged files).\n\nRun manually:\n```bash\nnpm run format    # prettier --write . (all files)\nnpm run fix       # turbo fix (runs prettier + ESLint per workspace)\n```\n\n## Type checking — TypeScript\n\nEach workspace has its own `tsconfig.json`. Type checking runs via:\n\n```bash\nnpm run typecheck                          # all workspaces\nnpm run typecheck -- --filter=<workspace>  # one workspace\n```\n\nTypeScript is configured with strict settings. `tsconfig.json` at the root extends base settings used across the monorepo.\n\n## Unused exports — Knip\n\n[Knip](https://knip.dev) detects unused exports, files, and dependencies:\n\n```bash\nnpm run knip\n```\n\nCI runs Knip via the `knip.yml` workflow. Unused exports fail the check. This is especially relevant when adding test-only helper functions (e.g., reset functions for singletons) — use module isolation patterns instead. See [testing — singleton testing](./testing.md#singleton-and-cache-testing).\n\nKnip configuration is at `knip.json` in the repo root.\n\n## Stylelint\n\nCSS-in-JS and styled-components are linted by stylelint:\n\n```bash\nnpm run stylelint    # runs stylelint on all *.{js,jsx,ts,tsx,css} files\n```\n\nStylelint also runs in the pre-commit hook on staged files.\n\n## Pre-commit hooks — Husky\n\nHusky manages two git hooks:\n\n### `pre-commit` (`.husky/pre-commit`)\n\nRuns automatically on `git commit`. For each staged file (excluding symlinks):\n\n1. Runs Prettier (`npm exec prettier -- $files --write --ignore-unknown`)\n2. Runs stylelint (`npm exec stylelint -- $files --fix`)\n3. Stages any files modified by the formatters\n\nIf you have **unstaged changes in the same files you're staging**, the hook exits with an error to prevent accidental overwrites. Stage everything or stash unstaged changes first.\n\n### `pre-push` (`.husky/pre-push`)\n\nRuns automatically on `git push`. Validates the branch name:\n\n- Must be ≤ 32 characters\n- Letters, numbers, hyphens, and slashes only\n- `main`, `dev`, and `HEAD` are exempt\n\nViolating this will block the push. Rename the branch and retry.\n\n## CI workflows\n\n| Workflow | Trigger | What it checks |\n|---|---|---|\n| `eslint.yml` | PR | `npm run lint` across all workspaces |\n| `format.yml` | PR | Prettier formatting |\n| `typecheck.yml` | PR | TypeScript across all workspaces |\n| `test.yml` | PR | Tests (excluding `backend` and `@factory/cli`) |\n| `test-cli.yml` | PR | CLI unit tests |\n| `knip.yml` | PR | Unused exports |\n| `pr-conventions.yml` | PR open/edit | Title format, branch name, Linear ticket |\n\n## Related\n\n- [Development workflow](./development-workflow.md) — how to run checks locally\n- [Testing](./testing.md) — test frameworks and patterns\n- `packages/eslint-config/README.md` — ESLint config presets and contributing rules\n",
