            "content": "# Lore\n\nThe history and evolution of the Factory monorepo, reconstructed from git history.\n\n> Hedging note: sections derived from commit message patterns are labeled \"appears to have been\" or \"likely\" where the exact intent is inferred rather than documented.\n\n---\n\n## Eras\n\n### Era 1 — Bootstrapping (September–October 2024)\n\nThe earliest commit in the repo is dated **September 30, 2024**, with the message \"Initial commit from Create Next App.\" Within the same day, commits add styled-components, design-system color variables, the Inter font, auth scaffolding, a Redux store, basic Flex/Box components, and a Firebase connection. The first PR merged into the repo was a prettier config.\n\nCommit messages in the first weeks reference `Factory-AI/factory-assembly` as the originating repo (\"Merge branch 'dev' of https://github.com/Factory-AI/factory-assembly into dev\"), suggesting the monorepo was spun up as a fresh Next.js app and early code was migrated in from a pre-existing repository called `factory-assembly`.\n\n**Key events:**\n- **Sept 30, 2024** — Initial Next.js/React commit; Firebase connected same day\n- **Oct 1, 2024** — `Box` component created, `useDisclosure` hook migrated, prettier added, sessions/blueprints pages scaffolded\n- **Oct 2024** — 319 commits; the fastest-growing month relative to codebase size\n\n---\n\n### Era 2 — Assembly Matures (November 2024–January 2025)\n\nThe product at this point appears to have been called \"Assembly.\" Development focused on the web application: local file sync (LFS), codebase/repo indexing, session management, fragment editing, and workflow support. The team migrated to Next.js 15 in late December.\n\n**Key events:**\n- **Dec 27, 2024** — Migrate to Next.js 15\n- **Dec 2024** — 427 commits; heaviest month in the first year\n- **Jan 2025** — Stripe chat billing removed; Prometheus metrics added\n- **Jan 2025** — 375 commits\n\n---\n\n### Era 3 — Rebrand and Structural Shifts (February–May 2025)\n\nSeveral significant renamings happened in rapid succession, signaling a product identity shift:\n\n- **Feb 10, 2025** — \"Renamed tasks to threads\"\n- **Feb 24, 2025** — \"Rename Assembly to Factory in all user/LLM-facing content\" — the product officially became \"Factory\" in the UI and prompts\n- **Apr 24, 2025** — MCP (Model Context Protocol integration layer) renamed to \"bridge\"\n\nThe team also cleaned up the frontend: the Workflows tab was removed (May 2025) and the legacy dashboard was deleted.\n\n**Key events:**\n- **Feb 2025** — Brand rename; 405 commits\n- **Mar–Apr 2025** — 378 and 315 commits respectively\n- **May 2025** — 481 commits, the highest yet; agent loop unit tests added\n\n---\n\n### Era 4 — The CLI Revolution (June–September 2025)\n\nThis era appears to have been when Factory shifted from being primarily a web product to being primarily a terminal-based agent tool. Several foundational packages were created, and a brand-new CLI app was bootstrapped.\n\n- **June 13, 2025** — `packages/logging` and `packages/errors` created\n- **June 25, 2025** — `apps/bridge` migrated from a standalone external repo into the monorepo\n- **July 10, 2025** — `packages/droid-core` initialized (\"Droid Core Package Init\")\n- **July 21, 2025** — `apps/factory-cli` initialized, using [Ink](https://github.com/vadimdemedes/ink) (React for terminal UIs)\n- **August 14, 2025** — `@factory/common` package created to centralize shared types\n- **September 2025** — 741 commits, the all-time peak month\n\n**Key events:**\n- **Jul 2025** — 527 commits; CLI scaffolded with auth, model selection\n- **Aug 2025** — 637 commits; `@factory/common` consolidates shared types/enums\n- **Sept 2025** — 741 commits; CLI rapidly gains features (exec mode, spec mode, MCP, droid co-authoring)\n\n---\n\n### Era 5 — Platform Expansion (October 2025)\n\nOctober 2025 appears to have been a month of significant architectural additions. Multiple new foundations were laid simultaneously:\n\n- **Oct 9, 2025** — `apps/web` initialized (\"Init Assembly V3 app\"), a brand-new Vite+React web app replacing the older Next.js front end\n- **Oct 10, 2025** — `apps/daemon` scaffolded in the monorepo\n- **Oct 15, 2025** — HCv3 (Hypercode v3, the legacy code intelligence integration) fully removed from `apps/factory-app`\n- **Oct 22, 2025** — React Compiler adopted for `apps/web`; `useMemo` and `useCallback` banned by lint rule\n- **Oct 27, 2025** — `packages/core-ui` established as the mandatory design system\n\n**Key events:**\n- **Oct 2025** — 610 commits; three new major foundations (web app, daemon, core-ui) added in same month\n- HCv3 removal appears to have been a years-long legacy finally cleaned up at this point\n\n---\n\n### Era 6 — Consolidation and Cleanup (November–December 2025)\n\nThe team appears to have shifted focus toward consolidation: removing dead code, unifying environments, and deleting apps that had been superseded.\n\n- **Nov 14, 2025** — \"remove deprecated headless mode and unused chat infrastructure\"\n- **Dec 23, 2025** — `apps/bridge` deleted (\"nuke apps/bridge\") — the bridge was no longer needed as a separate binary\n- **Jan 4, 2026** — Deprecated headless mode and legacy message API removed\n\n**Key events:**\n- **Nov 2025** — 548 commits\n- **Dec 2025** — 501 commits; bridge deleted\n- Several dead backend routes removed in preparation for the rename\n\n---\n\n### Era 7 — Modern Monorepo (January 2026–present)\n\nA cluster of structural renames in January 2026 reflect the current naming scheme:\n\n- **Jan 7, 2026** — `apps/factory-app` renamed to `apps/backend`\n- **Jan 12, 2026** — `apps/factory-cli` renamed to `apps/cli`\n- **Jan 27, 2026** — `packages/daemon-core` extracted from `apps/daemon` to hold shareable daemon logic\n- **Feb 26, 2026** — `apps/signal` migrated from an external repo into the monorepo with a shared `packages/signal-core` package\n- **Mar 11, 2026** — Desktop and E2B computer sandboxes migrated onto the droid daemon\n\nDevelopment continues at ~18 commits/day.\n\n---\n\n## Longest-Standing Features\n\n### Backend API Routing\n\nThe backend API structure (`apps/backend/src/app/api/...`) traces its earliest additions to **October 1, 2024** (the Firebase session endpoint). The Next.js App Router layout with `route.ts` files has been present since the first days and has grown to 12 directory levels deep for the most nested OAuth routes.\n\n### Design System Colors\n\nThe first design-system colors were committed **September 30, 2024** as CSS variables (`add design system colors as global css variables`). The system has since been formalized into `packages/core-ui` (October 2025) with token-based semantics, but the practice of centralizing colors predates every other architectural decision in the repo.\n\n### Firebase Integration\n\nFirebase was added **October 1, 2024** (\"miraculously firebase has worked on the first try\") and remains the primary datastore. Firebase Admin, Firestore rules, and storage rules are still present in the repo root today.\n\n---\n\n## Deprecated and Removed Features\n\n| Feature | Removed | Notes |\n|---------|---------|-------|\n| Stripe chat billing | January 2025 | \"Remove stripe chat usage and plan management\" |\n| HCv3 (Hypercode v3) integration | October 2025 | Legacy code intelligence, fully removed in `refactor(factory-app): complete rip out of HCv3` |\n| `apps/bridge` (standalone Bridge binary) | December 2025 | \"nuke apps/bridge\"; bridge functionality moved into daemon/CLI |\n| Headless mode | January 2026 | \"remove deprecated headless mode and unused chat infrastructure\" |\n| Legacy message API | January 2026 | `chore(factory-cli,factory-app,droid-core): remove legacy message api calls` |\n| Workflows tab / dashboard | May 2025 | \"Remove threads from the frontend and cleanup deprecated dashboard\" |\n| Assembly branding | February 2025 | \"Rename Assembly to Factory in all user/LLM-facing content\" |\n\n---\n\n## Major Rewrites\n\n### Next.js 15 Migration (December 27, 2024)\n\nThe backend app migrated from Next.js 14 to Next.js 15 in a single commit in late December 2024. Some routes deleted during the migration were re-added the following day (\"Reintroduce routes that were deleted during NextJS 15 migration\").\n\n### New Web App — Assembly V3 (October 2025)\n\nThe Vite+React `apps/web` initialized in October 2025 appears to be a ground-up replacement for the web-facing UI that had previously been served by `apps/factory-app`. The old app was renamed to `apps/backend` in January 2026, making its purely backend role explicit.\n\n### daemon-core Extraction (January 27, 2026)\n\n`packages/daemon-core` was extracted from `apps/daemon` to separate the daemon's reusable logic from its runtime harness. The commit message: \"Migrate daemon functionality into a daemon-core package.\"\n\n---\n\n## Growth Trajectory\n\n| Date | Event |\n|------|-------|\n| Sep 30, 2024 | Repo initialized; first commit |\n| Oct 2024 | Sessions, auth, Firebase, basic design system |\n| Dec 2024 | Next.js 15; local file sync; peak early month (427 commits) |\n| Feb 2025 | Renamed Assembly → Factory |\n| Jun 2025 | Bridge and logging packages migrate in |\n| Jul 2025 | `apps/factory-cli` (terminal CLI) scaffolded |\n| Aug 2025 | `@factory/common` package created |\n| Sep 2025 | 741 commits — all-time peak month |\n| Oct 2025 | `apps/web`, `apps/daemon`, `packages/core-ui` all added |\n| Dec 2025 | `apps/bridge` deleted |\n| Jan 2026 | `factory-app` → `backend`, `factory-cli` → `cli` |\n| Feb 2026 | `apps/signal` migrated in |\n| Mar 2026 | Desktop/E2B onto droid daemon; ongoing at ~18 commits/day |\n",
