 your current directory take precedence over those further up the hierarchy.\n## Project Instructions:\n% cat /Users/jonathanlucuix-andre/Documents/test-repos/factory-mono/CLAUDE.md\n<coding_guidelines>\n# CLAUDE.md\n\nThis file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.\n\n**Read `AGENTS.md` first** - it contains essential commands, conventions, and architecture overview.\n\n## Build & Test Commands\n\n```bash\nnpm run fix                              # Lint + format (preferred)\nnpm run test                             # Run all tests\nnpm run typecheck                        # TypeScript checking\nnpm run build                            # Build all packages\nnpm run dev                              # Start all apps in dev mode\n```\n\nTarget specific workspaces with `--filter`:\n```bash\nnpm run test --filter=@factory/frontend\nnpm run build --filter=apps/web\n```\n\nRun a single test file:\n```bash\ncd apps/backend && npx jest path/to/file.test.ts\ncd packages/frontend && npx vitest run path/to/file.test.ts\n```\n\n## Monorepo Structure\n\nnpm workspaces + Turborepo. Node 18.x (`.nvmrc`).\n\n| App | Stack | Port |\n|-----|-------|------|\n| `apps/web` | Vite + React | 3002 |\n| `apps/backend` | Next.js 15 | 3000 |\n| `apps/admin` | Next.js 15 | 3001 |\n| `apps/desktop` | Electron | - |\n| `apps/daemon` | Bun | - |\n| `apps/cli` | Bun | - |\n\n**Key packages**: `@factory/core-ui` (mandatory UI), `@factory/common` (shared types), `@factory/frontend` (React features), `@factory/droid-core` (AI agent)\n\n## Testing Patterns\n\n**Frontend tests need jsdom** - add at file top:\n```ts\n/** @jest-environment jsdom */\n```\n\n**Mocking pattern** - top-level with `requireActual`:\n```ts\njest.mock('./module', () => ({\n  ...jest.requireActual('./module'),\n  functionToMock: jest.fn(),\n}));\n\nbeforeEach(() => jest.resetAllMocks());\n```\n\n**Singleton testing** - use module isolation instead of reset functions:\n```ts\nbeforeEach(() => jest.resetModules());\nit('test', async () => {\n  const { getService } = await import('./service');\n});\n```\n\n## Architecture: Daemon/CLI/Frontend\n\n```\nFrontend (DaemonSessionController.ts)\n    ↓ WebSocket JSON-RPC\nDaemon (droid-request-handler.ts)\n    ↓ stdin/stdout JSON-RPC\nCLI (streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.tsx)\n```\n\nAfter modifying CLI/daemon code:\n1. `cd apps/cli && npm run setup`\n2. Restart daemon\n3. Start new session\n\nLogs: `~/.factory-dev/logs/` (dev) or `~/.factory/logs/` (prod)\n\n## File Organization Rules\n\nESLint enforces:\n- Enums in `enums.ts`, types in `types.ts`\n- API types in `packages/common/src/api/{service}/types.ts`\n- Absolute imports (`@factory/...`, `@/...`)\n- No `require()` - use ES6 imports\n\n## PR Conventions\n\nTitle: `type(scope): description` (e.g., `feat(cli): add new command`)\n- Types: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`\n- Scope: workspace name or `monorepo`\n- Include Linear ticket in description (e.g., `Closes FAC-1234`)\n</coding_guidelines>\n\n% cat /Users/jonathanlucuix-andre/Documents/test-repos/factory-mono/AGENTS.md\n<coding_guidelines>\n# Agents Guidelines for Factory Monorepo\n\n## Critical Requirements\n\n- **packages/frontend work**: Follow [`docs/ui-development.md`](./docs/ui-development.md) - always use `@factory/core-ui` components\n- **API endpoints**: Define types in `@factory/common/src/api/{service}/types.ts` - see [`docs/examples/api-type-conventions.md`](./docs/examples/api-type-conventions.md)\n\n---\n\n## Reference Docs (check when relevant)\n\n- [`/docs/examples/`](./docs/examples/) - End-to-end implementation patterns\n- [`/memories/`](./memories/) - Session context and notes from previous work\n- [`docs/frontend.md`](./docs/frontend.md) - Frontend architecture\n- [`docs/feature-flags.md`](./docs/feature-flags.md) - Statsig feature flags\n- [`docs/error-handling.md`](./docs/error-handling.md) - Error patterns\n- [`docs/unit-tests.md`](./docs/unit-tests.md) - Testing conventions\n- [`docs/playwright-e2e-testing.md`](./docs/playwright-e2e-testing.md) - Playwright E2E testing for apps/web\n\n---\n\n## Commands\n\n```bash\nnpm run fix        # Lint + format (preferred over npm run lint)\nnpm run test       # Run all tests\nnpm run typecheck  # TypeScript checking\nnpm run knip       # Detect unused exports\nnpm run build      # Build all packages\nnpm run dev:web    # Start backend, web, storybook, admin, daemon (works over SSH)\nnpm run dev:desktop # Start backend, web, storybook, admin, desktop (local only)\nnpm run clean      # Clear all caches\n```\n\n**Do NOT use `npm run dev`** at the root — it is intentionally disabled. Use `dev:web` or `dev:desktop` above.\n\nFor CLI dev, run `droid-dev` (hosted) or `droid-localhost` (local API) separately after `cd apps/cli && npm run setup`.\n\n**Dev server logs:** When running `dev:web` or `dev:desktop`, each app streams its output to both console and a log file on disk. You can inspect logs at any time:\n\n| App     | Log file                       |\n| ------- | ------------------------------ |\n| backend | `/tmp/factory-dev-backend.log` |\n| admin   | `/tmp/factory-dev-admin.log`   |\n| desktop | `/tmp/factory-dev-desktop.log` |\n| daemon  | `/tmp/factory-dev-daemon.log`  |\n\nUse `tail -f /tmp/factory-dev-backend.log` to live-stream, or `cat` / `grep` the file to search for errors.\n\n**Filtering to specific packages (IMPORTANT):** You **must** use `--` before `--filter`, otherwise npm eats the flag and turbo runs ALL packages. A full unfiltered `npm run test` consumes ~9 GB of RAM.\n\n```bash\n# CORRECT - filter is passed through to turbo:\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/common --filter=@factory/daemon-core\n\n# WRONG - npm eats --filter, turbo runs everything:\nnpm run test --filter=@factory/common --filter=@factory/daemon-core\n```\n\nThis applies to all turbo-based scripts: `test`, `typecheck`, `lint`, `fix`, `build`.\n\n---\n\n## Testing Requirements\n\n- Do **not**