            "content": "# Architecture\n\nFactory is a distributed system connecting a local terminal experience to cloud-managed AI sessions. At its heart, the CLI communicates with a daemon via WebSocket JSON-RPC. The daemon runs agent sessions that call LLMs and execute tools on the host machine. A web/desktop frontend provides an alternative interface to the same daemon.\n\n## High-level component diagram\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TB\n    subgraph \"User interfaces\"\n        CLI[\"apps/cli<br/>Droid CLI (Ink TUI / exec)\"]\n        Web[\"apps/web<br/>Web app (Vite + React)\"]\n        Desktop[\"apps/desktop<br/>Electron desktop\"]\n        VSCode[\"apps/factory-vscode-extension<br/>VS Code extension\"]\n    end\n\n    subgraph \"Backend services\"\n        Daemon[\"apps/daemon<br/>factoryd (Bun, WebSocket JSON-RPC)\"]\n        Backend[\"apps/backend<br/>Next.js API\"]\n        Functions[\"apps/functions<br/>Firebase Cloud Functions\"]\n    end\n\n    subgraph \"Shared packages\"\n        DroidCore[\"@factory/droid-core<br/>Tool definitions, LLM streaming\"]\n        Common[\"@factory/common<br/>Types, API contracts\"]\n        Frontend[\"@factory/frontend<br/>Shared React features\"]\n        CoreUI[\"@factory/core-ui<br/>Design system\"]\n    end\n\n    subgraph \"External services\"\n        LLMs[\"LLM providers<br/>(Anthropic, OpenAI, Gemini)\"]\n        WorkOS[\"WorkOS<br/>(Auth)\"]\n        Orb[\"Orb<br/>(Billing)\"]\n        Statsig[\"Statsig<br/>(Feature flags)\"]\n        E2B[\"E2B<br/>(Cloud sandboxes)\"]\n        Firebase[\"Firebase / Firestore\"]\n        MCP[\"MCP servers<br/>(external tools)\"]\n    end\n\n    CLI -->|\"WebSocket JSON-RPC\"| Daemon\n    Web -->|\"WebSocket JSON-RPC\"| Daemon\n    Desktop -->|\"WebSocket JSON-RPC\"| Daemon\n    VSCode -->|\"JSON-RPC\"| CLI\n\n    Daemon -->|\"imports\"| DroidCore\n    CLI -->|\"imports\"| DroidCore\n    CLI -->|\"imports\"| Common\n\n    Backend -->|\"LLM proxy\"| LLMs\n    CLI -->|\"REST API\"| Backend\n    Daemon -->|\"REST API\"| Backend\n\n    Backend -->|\"auth\"| WorkOS\n    Backend -->|\"billing\"| Orb\n    Backend -->|\"feature flags\"| Statsig\n    Backend -->|\"data\"| Firebase\n    Backend -->|\"sandboxes\"| E2B\n\n    Daemon -->|\"tool calls via MCP\"| MCP\n    CLI -->|\"MCP hub\"| MCP\n\n    Web -->|\"imports\"| Frontend\n    Desktop -->|\"imports\"| Frontend\n    Frontend -->|\"imports\"| CoreUI\n```\n\n## Request flow: interactive CLI session\n\nWhen a user types a message in the Droid CLI:\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant User\n    participant CLI as apps/cli<br/>(Ink TUI)\n    participant Agent as AgentLoop<br/>(CLI core)\n    participant Daemon as apps/daemon<br/>(factoryd)\n    participant Backend as apps/backend<br/>(LLM proxy)\n    participant LLM as LLM provider\n\n    User->>CLI: types message, presses Enter\n    CLI->>Agent: useAgent hook enqueues message\n    Agent->>Agent: useLLMStreaming builds conversation\n    Agent->>Backend: POST /api/llm/stream (via LLM proxy)\n    Backend->>LLM: streaming request\n    LLM-->>Backend: token stream\n    Backend-->>Agent: SSE / streaming response\n    Agent->>CLI: appendAssistantText (real-time render)\n    Agent->>CLI: addToolCall (tool invocation)\n    CLI->>Daemon: execute tool via JSON-RPC\n    Daemon-->>CLI: tool result\n    Agent->>Backend: continue conversation with tool result\n    Backend->>LLM: follow-up\n    LLM-->>Agent: final response\n    Agent->>CLI: finalizeAssistantMessage\n    CLI->>User: displays full response\n```\n\n## Daemon architecture\n\nThe daemon (`factoryd`) is the session lifecycle manager. It runs as a background process, either bundled with the desktop app or deployed on an E2B cloud sandbox.\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    WS[\"WebSocket server<br/>(port 37643 / 41723)\"]\n    Handler[\"droid-request-handler\"]\n    Sessions[\"Session manager\"]\n    PTY[\"PTY manager<br/>(terminal sessions)\"]\n    DroidCore[\"@factory/droid-core<br/>Tools + streaming\"]\n\n    WS -->|\"JSON-RPC request\"| Handler\n    Handler --> Sessions\n    Handler --> PTY\n    Sessions -->|\"uses\"| DroidCore\n```\n\n## LLM proxy flow\n\nThe backend (`apps/backend`) acts as an LLM proxy, translating requests to provider-specific formats and streaming tokens back to the CLI:\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    CLI -->|\"POST /api/llm/stream\"| Proxy[\"LLM proxy<br/>(apps/backend)\"]\n    Proxy -->|\"Anthropic SDK\"| Anthropic\n    Proxy -->|\"OpenAI SDK\"| OpenAI\n    Proxy -->|\"Google GenAI SDK\"| Gemini\n    Proxy -->|\"SSE stream\"| CLI\n```\n\n## Package dependency map\n\nThe monorepo packages form a dependency hierarchy. Higher-level packages import lower-level ones:\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    CLI[\"apps/cli\"] --> DroidCore[\"@factory/droid-core\"]\n    CLI --> Services[\"@factory/services\"]\n    CLI --> Common[\"@factory/common\"]\n    CLI --> Runtime[\"@factory/runtime\"]\n    CLI --> Logging[\"@factory/logging\"]\n\n    Daemon[\"apps/daemon\"] --> DaemonCore[\"@factory/daemon-core\"]\n    Daemon --> DroidCore\n\n    Web[\"apps/web\"] --> Frontend[\"@factory/frontend\"]\n    Desktop[\"apps/desktop\"] --> Frontend\n\n    Frontend --> CoreUI[\"@factory/core-ui\"]\n    Frontend --> Common\n    Frontend --> DaemonClient[\"@factory/daemon-client\"]\n\n    DroidCore --> Common\n    Services --> Common\n    DaemonClient --> Common\n```\n\n## Language breakdown\n\nThe codebase is almost entirely TypeScript, with Python used in infrastructure tooling and Terraform/HCL for IaC.\n\n```mermaid\nxychart-beta horizontal\n    title \"Source files by language\"\n    x-axis [\"TypeScript\", \"HCL (Terraform)\", \"Python\", \"JavaScript\", \"CSS/Styles\", \"Other\"]\n    y-axis \"Files\" 0 --> 4500\n    bar [3996, 180, 45, 60, 90, 30]\n```\n\n## Key architectural decisions\n\n- **Bun runtime for CLI and daemon** — Bun provides fast startup, native TypeScript execution, and bundling for single-executable distribution. See [patterns and conventions](../how-to-contribute/patterns-and-conventions.md).\n- **Ink (React) for the TUI** — The CLI renders a terminal UI using Ink, bringing React component model and hooks to the terminal. This allows the same reactive programming model across CLI and web.\n- **JSON-RPC 2.0 for daemon communication** — The CLI and web frontends communicate with the daemon over a JSON-RPC protocol. This provides a clear contract and enables multiple clients (CLI, web, desktop) to share a single daemon.\n- **LLM proxy in the backend** — Routing LLM calls through the backend lets Factory apply rate limiting, billing, and logging centrally, rather than in each client.\n- **Turborepo for monorepo builds** — Turborepo provides task caching and parallel execution across workspaces. See [tooling](../how-to-contribute/tooling.md).\n",
