            "content": "# Getting started\n\nThis guide covers how to install dependencies, build the repo, run the dev servers, and run tests.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- **Node.js 18.x** — check `.nvmrc` at the repo root. Use `nvm use` if you have nvm installed.\n- **npm 11+** — the repo uses `packageManager: \"npm@11.2.0\"` in `package.json`.\n- **Bun 1.3.10** — required for CLI and daemon development. Install from [bun.sh](https://bun.sh).\n- **Git** — standard.\n\nOptional tools for specific workflows:\n- **OpenTofu** — for infrastructure changes in `infra/`\n- **Firebase CLI** — `npm install -g firebase-tools` for Cloud Functions work\n- **Playwright** — installed automatically via npm, needed for E2E tests\n\n## Install dependencies\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/Factory-AI/factory-mono.git\ncd factory-mono\nnpm install\n```\n\nThe `postinstall` hook runs `npm run setup` which builds necessary packages in dependency order.\n\n## Running the dev servers\n\nDo **not** run `npm run dev` at the repo root — it is intentionally disabled.\n\n| Command | What it starts |\n|---|---|\n| `npm run dev:web` | backend, web, storybook, admin, daemon |\n| `npm run dev:desktop` | backend, web, storybook, admin, desktop (requires local display) |\n\nLogs from each app are streamed to files:\n\n| App | Log file |\n|---|---|\n| backend | `/tmp/factory-dev-backend.log` |\n| admin | `/tmp/factory-dev-admin.log` |\n| daemon | `/tmp/factory-dev-daemon.log` |\n| desktop | `/tmp/factory-dev-desktop.log` |\n\nUse `tail -f /tmp/factory-dev-backend.log` to stream logs live.\n\n## Port map\n\n| App | Port |\n|---|---|\n| backend | 3000 |\n| web | 3002 |\n| admin | 3001 |\n| daemon (dev) | 41723 |\n| daemon (prod) | 37643 |\n\n## Running the CLI in dev mode\n\nFor CLI development, set up and run `droid-dev` after starting the dev servers:\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli\nnpm run setup    # builds the CLI and installs 'droid-dev' globally\ndroid-dev        # connects to local backend\n```\n\nAfter modifying CLI or daemon code, rebuild before testing:\n```bash\ncd apps/cli && npm run setup\n```\n\n## Build\n\n```bash\nnpm run build                         # build all packages\nnpm run build -- --filter=apps/web    # build only the web app\n```\n\n## Testing\n\nRun all tests (warning: consumes significant RAM):\n```bash\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/frontend\n```\n\nAlways use `--` before `--filter` — without it, npm eats the flag and Turborepo runs tests for every workspace.\n\nRun a single test file:\n```bash\n# In apps/backend:\ncd apps/backend && npx jest path/to/file.test.ts\n\n# In packages/frontend:\ncd packages/frontend && npx vitest run path/to/file.test.ts\n```\n\nCLI E2E tests:\n```bash\ncd apps/cli && npx tui-test e2e-tests/\n```\n\nFrontend E2E tests (Playwright):\n```bash\ncd packages/frontend && npm run test:e2e\n```\n\n## Lint, format, and type-check\n\n```bash\nnpm run fix          # lint + format (preferred)\nnpm run lint         # lint only\nnpm run typecheck    # TypeScript checking\nnpm run knip         # detect unused exports\n```\n\nSame filtering rules apply:\n```bash\nnpm run typecheck -- --filter=@factory/droid-core\n```\n\n## Environment variables\n\nEach app has its own `.env` file. Copy `.env.example` in `apps/backend` for a starting template. The key env files:\n\n- `apps/cli/.env` — CLI configuration\n- `apps/backend/.env` — backend API keys (WorkOS, Firebase, Stripe, etc.)\n- `apps/daemon/.env` — daemon configuration\n\nSensitive secrets (API keys, credentials) are never committed. Use `.env.local` files (git-ignored) for local overrides.\n\nSee [configuration reference](../reference/configuration.md) for a full variable list.\n\n## Infrastructure\n\nInfrastructure changes in `infra/` use OpenTofu (not Terraform):\n\n```bash\ncd infra\ntofu init\ntofu validate\ntofu fmt\n```\n\n## Storybook\n\nView and develop UI components interactively:\n\n```bash\nnpm run storybook\n# Opens at http://localhost:6006\n```\n",
