            "content": "# Complexity hotspots\n\nThis page lists the largest and most structurally complex source files in factory-mono. Size alone is not complexity, but very large files almost always have multiple overlapping responsibilities and are the first place reviewers encounter friction.\n\nMeasurements were taken with `wc -l` across all `.ts` and `.tsx` files, excluding `node_modules`, `dist`, `.next`, and `coverage` directories.\n\n## Top 15 largest source files\n\n| Rank | File | Lines | Type | Notes |\n|------|------|------:|------|-------|\n| 1 | `packages/daemon-core/src/server/handlers/droid-request-handler.test.ts` | 12,410 | Test | Integration test suite for the daemon request handler |\n| 2 | `apps/cli/src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.test.ts` | 5,457 | Test | E2E tests for exec mode streaming |\n| 3 | `apps/cli/src/services/SessionService.test.ts` | 5,449 | Test | Session service unit tests |\n| 4 | `packages/daemon-core/src/server/handlers/droid-request-handler.ts` | **5,106** | **Source** | Monolithic daemon JSON-RPC handler |\n| 5 | `apps/cli/src/app.tsx` | **4,575** | **Source** | Top-level Ink TUI root component |\n| 6 | `packages/services/src/settings/SettingsManager.test.ts` | 3,890 | Test | Settings manager tests |\n| 7 | `packages/frontend/src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.test.ts` | 3,791 | Test | Frontend↔daemon bridge tests |\n| 8 | `packages/droid-sdk/src/client.test.ts` | 3,723 | Test | Droid SDK client tests |\n| 9 | `apps/cli/src/services/SessionService.ts` | **3,622** | **Source** | CLI session lifecycle manager |\n| 10 | `apps/cli/src/skills/builtin/constants.ts` | **3,528** | **Source** | Built-in skill prompt constants |\n| 11 | `apps/cli/src/hooks/useLLMStreaming.test.ts` | 3,490 | Test | LLM streaming hook tests |\n| 12 | `packages/services/src/settings/FactorySettingsFolder.test.ts` | 3,049 | Test | Settings folder tests |\n| 13 | `apps/cli/src/models/converters.test.ts` | 2,936 | Test | Message converter tests |\n| 14 | `apps/cli/src/services/SettingsService.test.ts` | 2,730 | Test | Settings service tests |\n| 15 | `apps/cli/src/core/AgentLoop.ts` | **2,676** | **Source** | Agent execution loop |\n\nProduction source files with over 2,000 lines (excluding test files):\n\n| File | Lines | Responsibility |\n|------|------:|---------------|\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/server/handlers/droid-request-handler.ts` | 5,106 | All daemon↔CLI request dispatch |\n| `apps/cli/src/app.tsx` | 4,575 | TUI root: routing, panels, state wiring |\n| `apps/cli/src/services/SessionService.ts` | 3,622 | Session create/load/resume |\n| `apps/cli/src/skills/builtin/constants.ts` | 3,528 | Built-in skill definitions (prompt strings) |\n| `apps/cli/src/core/AgentLoop.ts` | 2,676 | Core agent turn loop |\n| `packages/frontend/src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` | 2,570 | Frontend WebSocket↔daemon bridge |\n| `apps/cli/src/hooks/useChatKeyboardInput.ts` | 2,270 | Keyboard input state machine |\n| `apps/cli/src/hooks/createLLMStreamingCore.ts` | 2,053 | LLM streaming primitive |\n| `apps/cli/src/services/ConversationStateManager.ts` | 2,000 | Conversation history tracking |\n\n## Notable files in depth\n\n### `droid-request-handler.ts` (5,106 lines)\n\nHandles every JSON-RPC method the CLI sends to the daemon. It contains initialization, session loading, message dispatching, tool confirmation logic, MCP orchestration, and mission-worker lifecycle — all in one file. This is the single highest-risk file for regressions.\n\n**Refactor approach**: Extract per-domain handler modules (e.g., `session-handler.ts`, `tool-confirmation-handler.ts`, `mission-handler.ts`) and route into them from a thin dispatcher. CODEOWNERS for this file overlap with `apps/cli/src/hooks/` — coordinate with `@factory-arman` / `@stepan-factory`.\n\n### `app.tsx` (4,575 lines)\n\nThe Ink TUI root component mixes view routing (which screen is shown), global keyboard handling, auth state, session init, and all the wiring between hooks. It is imported by both interactive and exec modes.\n\n**Refactor approach**: Separate routing concerns into a `<Router>` component; move individual panels into `apps/cli/src/screens/`; extract global keyboard logic into `useChatKeyboardInput` (already exists at 2,270 lines — needs its own split).\n\n### `SessionService.ts` (3,622 lines)\n\nManages the full session lifecycle in the CLI: creating, loading, resuming, delegating, and tearing down sessions. It couples Firestore reads, daemon RPC calls, and local state.\n\n**Refactor approach**: Split into `LocalSessionService` (local-mode session ops) and `RemoteSessionService` (workspace-based session ops), with a shared interface. The existing test file (5,449 lines) should be split in parallel.\n\n### `skills/builtin/constants.ts` (3,528 lines)\n\nA single constants file containing all built-in skill prompt strings. These are large text blobs that inflate the line count significantly.\n\n**Refactor approach**: Move each skill's constants into its own directory (e.g., `skills/builtin/<skill-name>/constants.ts`). This is a mechanical rename that reduces cognitive overhead without changing logic.\n\n### `AgentLoop.ts` (2,676 lines)\n\nCore agent turn execution: builds prompts, invokes LLM, processes streaming chunks, executes tools, and loops. This is the heart of how Droid thinks and acts.\n\n**Refactor approach**: Extract prompt-building into `prompt.ts`, chunk processing into the existing `chunkProcessing` module, and tool-result handling into `tool-loop.ts`. Keep the loop itself thin.\n\n### `DaemonSessionController.ts` (2,570 lines)\n\nFrontend-side WebSocket manager that translates daemon JSON-RPC events into Redux actions. Handles reconnection, auth, and session sync.\n\n**Refactor approach**: Extract the reconnection logic and auth flow into separate classes; keep the event-to-Redux mapping as the single responsibility of the controller.\n\n## Large test files\n\nThe largest test files (>3,000 lines) are not failing tests but symptoms of monolithic source files. As the source files are split, the test files should follow, grouping tests by the extracted module they exercise.\n\nFor very large test files, running the full suite is slow. Use `npx vitest run path/to/specific.test.ts` or `npx jest path/to/specific.test.ts` to target a subset during development.\n\n## Related\n\n- [TODOs and FIXMEs](./todos-and-fixmes.md) — inline debt markers\n- [CLI core](../apps/cli.md) — architecture overview for the CLI\n",
