            "content": "# Configuration\n\nFactory apps are configured through environment variables. Sensitive secrets must never be committed to source control. Each app reads a `.env` file at startup; `.env.development` (checked in, no secrets) provides defaults for local development, and `.env.development.local` (git-ignored) overrides with real keys.\n\nThe `@factory/environment` package (`packages/environment/`) provides a typed wrapper around raw `process.env` access. All CLI and daemon code must use `getEnvironment()` from this package rather than `process.env` directly.\n\n---\n\n## CLI (`apps/cli`)\n\nThe CLI reads its environment at startup via `packages/environment`. The file `apps/cli/.env.development` ships the following safe defaults:\n\n```\nFACTORY_ENV=development\nFACTORY_DEPLOYMENT_ENV=development\nFACTORY_API_BASE_URL=https://dev.api.factory.ai\nFACTORY_APP_BASE_URL=https://dev.app.factory.ai\nFACTORY_DOWNLOADS_BUCKET=dev-downloads.factory.ai\nFACTORY_DOWNLOADS_PREFIX=\nFACTORY_OTEL_ENABLED=true\n```\n\n### Core variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Description |\n|----------|----------|-------------|\n| `FACTORY_ENV` | Yes | Runtime environment: `development` or `production` |\n| `FACTORY_DEPLOYMENT_ENV` | Yes | Deployment tier: `development`, `staging`, or `production` |\n| `FACTORY_API_BASE_URL` | Yes | Base URL for the Factory backend API |\n| `FACTORY_APP_BASE_URL` | Yes | Base URL for the web app (used for OAuth redirects) |\n| `FACTORY_DOWNLOADS_BUCKET` | Yes | S3-compatible bucket for binary downloads |\n| `FACTORY_DOWNLOADS_PREFIX` | No | Path prefix within the downloads bucket |\n| `FACTORY_OTEL_ENABLED` | No | Enable OpenTelemetry tracing (`true`/`false`) |\n\n### Auth\n\n| Variable | Required | Description |\n|----------|----------|-------------|\n| `FACTORY_API_KEY` | No | API key auth; alternative to interactive WorkOS login |\n| `FACTORY_WORKOS_BASE_URL` | No | Override WorkOS API base URL (for E2E testing with mock servers) |\n| `FACTORY_DISABLE_KEYRING` | No | Disable OS keychain for credential storage |\n\n### Logging and runtime\n\n| Variable | Required | Description |\n|----------|----------|-------------|\n| `FACTORY_LOG_FILE` | No | Path to write CLI log output |\n| `FACTORY_RUNTIME_SETTINGS_PATH` | No | Override default settings directory |\n| `FACTORY_DROID_AUTO_UPDATE_ENABLED` | No | Toggle auto-update (`true`/`false`) |\n| `MISSION_WORKER_INACTIVITY_TIMEOUT_MS` | No | Timeout for idle mission workers |\n\n---\n\n## Daemon (`apps/daemon`)\n\nThe daemon shares core `FACTORY_*` variables with the CLI. Additional daemon-specific variables:\n\n| Variable | Required | Description |\n|----------|----------|-------------|\n| `FACTORYD_VERSION` | No | Daemon version string (set by build) |\n| `FACTORYD_DISABLE_AUTO_UPDATE` | No | Disable daemon self-update |\n| `REMOTE_MACHINE_ID` | No | ID of the remote machine when running as a remote daemon |\n| `FACTORY_MACHINE_TYPE` | No | Machine type identifier |\n| `ROLLBACK_ENABLED` | No | Enable rollback to previous daemon version on error |\n| `FACTORY_RELAY_PORT` | No | Port for the relay server (default: system-assigned) |\n| `FACTORY_RELAY_HOST` | No | Host for relay connections |\n| `FACTORY_RELAY_DEBUG` | No | Enable relay debug logging |\n\n---\n\n## Desktop (`apps/desktop`)\n\nThe desktop app uses Vite and reads `VITE_*` prefixed variables. `apps/desktop/.env.development` ships:\n\n```\nVITE_BACKEND_API_HOST=https://dev.api.factory.ai\nVITE_WORKOS_CLIENT_ID=client_01HNM7927XNSKCJ4982Z5J3FFZ\nVITE_VERCEL_ENV=development\nVITE_DAEMON_PORT=41723\nFACTORY_ENV=development\nFACTORY_OTEL_ENABLED=true\n```\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `VITE_BACKEND_API_HOST` | Backend API base URL for the Electron renderer |\n| `VITE_WORKOS_CLIENT_ID` | WorkOS OAuth client ID for authentication |\n| `VITE_DAEMON_PORT` | Port the local daemon listens on (default: 41723) |\n| `VITE_VERCEL_ENV` | Deployment environment signal (`development`/`preview`/`production`) |\n\n---\n\n## Backend (`apps/backend`)\n\nThe backend is a Next.js 15 application deployed on Vercel. Configuration is read from `apps/backend/src/env/constants.ts` which maps every `process.env` variable to a typed `env` object. Set these in `.env.local` for local development or in the Vercel project settings for deployed environments.\n\n### Firebase\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY` | Firebase web API key |\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN` | Firebase auth domain |\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID` | Firestore project ID |\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET` | Firebase storage bucket |\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID` | FCM sender ID |\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_APP_ID` | Firebase app ID |\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_MEASUREMENT_ID` | Analytics measurement ID |\n\n### Authentication (WorkOS)\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_WORKOS_CLIENT_ID` | WorkOS OAuth client ID (public, safe for browser) |\n| `WORKOS_API_KEY` | WorkOS server-side API key (secret — never expose) |\n\n### AWS\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID` | AWS access key (optional if using SSO) |\n| `AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY` | AWS secret key (optional if using SSO) |\n| `AWS_DROID_EXECUTE_QUEUE_URL` | SQS queue for droid execution jobs |\n| `AWS_ORG_EVENTS_QUEUE_URL` | SQS queue for org-level events |\n| `AWS_PLAN_INDEX_QUEUE_URL` | SQS queue for plan indexing |\n\n### LLM proxy / GCP\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `PROXY_FUNCTION_URL` | GCP Cloud Function URL for LLM proxying |\n| `GCP_VERTEX_ANTHROPIC_REGION` | Vertex AI region for Anthropic models |\n| `GCP_VERTEX_ANTHROPIC_REGION_OPUS_41` | Vertex AI region override for Opus 4.1 |\n\n### Billing (Orb)\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_ORB_TEAM_TIER_PLAN_ID` | Orb plan ID for Team tier |\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_ORB_TEAM_ANNUAL_TIER_PLAN_ID` | Orb plan ID for Team Annual tier |\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_ORB_MAX_TIER_PLAN_ID` | Orb plan ID for Max tier |\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_ORB_ULTRA_TIER_PLAN_ID` | Orb plan ID for Ultra tier |\n| `ORB_EXTRA_USAGE_ITEM_ID` | Orb item ID for overage charges |\n\n### Feature flags (Statsig)\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_STATSIG_SDK_KEY` | Statsig client SDK key |\n\nSee [Feature flags](../features/feature-flags.md) for details on how flags are consumed.\n\n### Error monitoring (Sentry)\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_CLIENT_ID` | Sentry DSN for the backend/web app |\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_REPLAY_UNMASK` | Set `true` to unmask session replays |\n\n### Integrations\n\n| Service | Key variables |\n|---------|--------------|\n| GitHub | `GITHUB_APP_ID`, `GITHUB_APP_ID_INTERNAL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID` |\n| GitLab | `NEXT_PUBLIC_GITLAB_CLIENT_ID`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_GITLAB_PERSONAL_CLIENT_ID`, `GITLAB_WEBHOOK_URL` |\n| Slack | `NEXT_PUBLIC_SLACK_CLIENT_ID` |\n| Linear | `NEXT_PUBLIC_LINEAR_CLIENT_ID` |\n| Jira | `NEXT_PUBLIC_JIRA_CLIENT_ID`, `JIRA_WEBHOOK_URL` |\n| Notion | `NEXT_PUBLIC_NOTION_CLIENT_ID` |\n| Confluence | `NEXT_PUBLIC_CONFLUENCE_CLIENT_ID` |\n| PagerDuty | `NEXT_PUBLIC_PAGERDUTY_CLIENT_ID` |\n\n### Other services\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `LOOPS_API_KEY` | Loops transactional email API key |\n| `SENDGRID_INVITE_USER_TEMPLATE_ID` | SendGrid template for user invites |\n| `VOYAGE_API_KEY` | Voyage AI embedding API key |\n| `WEAVIATE_URL` | Weaviate vector DB endpoint |\n| `WEAVIATE_API_KEY` | Weaviate API key |\n| `TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID` | Twilio account SID (phone verification) |\n| `TWILIO_VERIFY_SERVICE_SID` | Twilio Verify service SID |\n\n---\n\n## Setting up a local `.env.local`\n\n1. Copy `.env.example` to `.env.local` in the relevant app directory.\n2. Fill in the required values. Firebase, WorkOS, and Statsig keys are available in 1Password under \"Factory dev environment\".\n3. For AWS, prefer SSO: run `aws configure sso` and set `AWS_PROFILE` instead of hardcoding `AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID`.\n4. LLM requests are routed through the backend proxy — the CLI does not need a direct Anthropic/OpenAI API key in normal operation.\n\n## Related\n\n- [Overview: getting started](../overview/getting-started.md)\n- [Feature flags](../features/feature-flags.md)\n",
