            "content": "# Data models\n\nFactory uses Firestore as its primary database. This page documents the core data models — their TypeScript types, where they live in the codebase, and how they relate to each other.\n\nAll canonical type definitions are in `packages/common/src/` and `packages/models/src/`. These packages are imported by the backend, CLI, daemon, and frontend.\n\n---\n\n## Session\n\nA session represents a single conversation between a user and Droid. It is the central entity in the system.\n\n**Type**: `FirestoreSession` in `packages/common/src/session/types.ts`  \n**Firestore collection**: `sessions/{sessionId}`\n\n```typescript\n// packages/common/src/session/types.ts (simplified)\nexport interface FirestoreSession {\n  title: string;\n  subtitle: string;\n  createdAt: FieldValue;\n  updatedAt: FieldValue;\n  deletedAt?: FieldValue | null;\n\n  // Ownership\n  owner: string | null;         // User ID\n  createdBy: string;            // User ID\n\n  // Session hierarchy (subagent sessions)\n  parent?: string | null;\n  callingSessionId?: string | null;\n  callingToolUseId?: string | null;\n\n  // State\n  version?: SessionVersion;     // 1 | 2\n  isStarted: boolean;\n  messagesCount?: number;       // Count of user messages only\n\n  // Workspace / sandbox\n  selectedWorkspaceId?: string | null;\n  workspaceSandboxId?: string | null;\n  computerId?: string;\n\n  // Droid execution state\n  droidId?: DroidType | null;\n  droidProcessId: number | null;\n  droidStatus: DroidExecutionStatus | null;\n  droidRequestId: string | null;\n  lastCancelledDroidRequestId?: string | null;\n\n  // Settings\n  sessionSettings?: SessionSettings;\n  /** @deprecated use sessionSettings */\n  agentConfig?: SessionAgentConfig;\n\n  // Routing\n  machineConnectionType?: MachineConnectionType;\n  lockedApiProvider?: string;\n\n  // Archival / search\n  archivedAt?: FieldValue | null;\n  bloomB64?: string;             // Base64 bloom filter for full-text search\n  bloomMigrationComplete?: boolean;\n}\n```\n\n### Session V2 (client view)\n\nThe frontend and daemon use a flattened client-side view of a session, `FactoryDroidSession`, defined in `packages/common/src/sessionV2/types.ts`:\n\n```typescript\n// packages/common/src/sessionV2/types.ts (simplified)\nexport interface FactoryDroidSession {\n  id: string;\n  isLegacy: boolean;\n  messages: FactoryDroidMessage[];\n  messagesCount?: number;\n  machineConnectionType?: MachineConnectionType;\n  workspaceSandboxId?: string | null;\n  selectedWorkspaceId?: string | null;\n  computerId?: string;\n  title?: string;\n  createdAt: number;           // Unix ms\n  updatedAt: number;           // Unix ms\n  owner?: string;\n  privacyLevel?: SessionPrivacyLevel;\n  droidStatus?: DroidExecutionStatus | null;\n  droidRequestId?: string | null;\n  sessionLocation?: SessionCreatedLocation;\n  tags?: SessionTag[];\n  isPinned?: boolean;\n  archivedAt?: string;         // ISO timestamp; presence = archived\n  callingSessionId?: string | null;\n  callingToolUseId?: string | null;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Message\n\nMessages are stored as a sub-collection of a session.\n\n**Firestore collection**: `sessions/{sessionId}/messages/{messageId}`\n\nMessage types are in `packages/common/src/sessionV2/messages/types.ts`. The shape of a message depends on its role:\n\n- `user` — text or structured input from the user\n- `assistant` — text, tool-use blocks, or thinking blocks from the model\n- `tool_result` — result of a tool call (by Droid)\n- `system` — system prompt (not user-visible)\n\nThe content field is an array of typed blocks (text, image, tool_use, tool_result, thinking). This mirrors the Anthropic Messages API structure.\n\n---\n\n## Organization\n\nAn organization groups users, manages billing, and holds integration credentials.\n\n**Type**: `FirestoreOrganization` in `packages/models/src/organization/types.ts`  \n**Firestore collection**: `organizations/{orgId}`\n\nKey fields:\n\n```typescript\nexport interface FirestoreOrganization {\n  id: string;\n  name: string;\n  description?: string | null;\n  companyInfo?: CompanyInfo;\n  createdAt: FieldValue;\n  activeIntegrations: Integrations;      // Which integrations are enabled\n  disabledUserIntegrations: Integrations;\n  onboarded: boolean;\n  deactivated: boolean;\n  stripeCustomerId: string;\n  subscription: OrganizationSubscription;\n  review: ReviewConfig;\n  url: string | null;\n  toolSettings?: ToolSettings;\n  securityPolicy?: SecurityPolicy;\n  tags?: Record<string, boolean>;\n}\n```\n\n### Subscription\n\n`OrganizationSubscription` (in `packages/models/src/organization/types.ts`) holds:\n\n- `factoryTier` — tier enum (`free`, `team`, `max`, `ultra`)\n- `orbSubscription` — full Orb subscription object\n- `overageLimits` — token caps for premium/standard usage\n- `freeTrialAllocation` — token grant for trial\n- `overdueAt` — set when invoices are unpaid; blocks access\n- `scheduledCancellationReason` — why end-of-term cancellation is set\n- `overagePreference` — user opt-in/out for overage billing\n\n---\n\n## User profile\n\nIndividual user settings are stored on the `UserProfile` document inside each organization.\n\n**Firestore path**: `organizations/{orgId}/users/{userId}`\n\nKey fields from `packages/common/src/organization/types.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nexport interface UserProfile {\n  // Basic info\n  firstName?: string | null;\n  lastName?: string | null;\n  email: string;\n  photoUrl?: string | null;\n  // TODO: Make these required after backfilling existing Firebase profiles\n\n  // Onboarding\n  onboarding: UserProfileOnboardingTracker;\n\n  // Machine connection preference\n  lastConnectedMachineInfo?: LastConnectedMachineInfo;\n\n  // Integration usernames (e.g., GitHub handle)\n  integrationUsernames?: UserProfileIntegrationUsernames;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Droid / agent types\n\nThe `packages/common/src/droid/` directory contains types for the agent execution protocol — the messages exchanged between CLI and daemon over JSON-RPC. Key schemas include:\n\n- `InitializeSessionRequest` / `InitializeSessionResult` — start a new droid session\n- `AddUserMessageRequest` / `AddUserMessageResult` — send a message to the running agent\n- `InterruptSessionRequest` — stop the running agent\n- `MissionStateSchema` — multi-agent mission structure (orchestrator + workers)\n- `ToolConfirmationDetailsSchema` — data for requesting user approval of a tool call\n- `AskUserRequest` / `AskUserResponse` — Droid asking the user a question mid-run\n\nThese types are defined as Zod schemas in `packages/common/src/droid/schemas/` and inferred with `z.infer<>`.\n\n---\n\n## Workspace\n\nA workspace is a sandboxed code environment (backed by E2B) attached to a remote session.\n\n**Firestore collection**: `workspaces/{workspaceId}`\n\nTypes are in `packages/models/src/workspace/`. Key fields include `sandboxId`, `repoUrl`, `createdBy`, `organizationId`, and `status` (enum: `active`, `paused`, `terminated`).\n\n---\n\n## Relationships overview\n\n```mermaid\nerDiagram\n    Organization ||--o{ UserProfile : \"has members\"\n    Organization ||--o{ Session : \"owns\"\n    Session ||--o{ Message : \"contains\"\n    Session ||--o| Workspace : \"backed by\"\n    Session ||--o{ Session : \"spawns (subagent)\"\n    Organization ||--o| OrganizationSubscription : \"has\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Where to find types\n\n| Model | Canonical source |\n|-------|-----------------|\n| Session (Firestore) | `packages/common/src/session/types.ts` |\n| Session (client view) | `packages/common/src/sessionV2/types.ts` |\n| Session messages | `packages/common/src/sessionV2/messages/types.ts` |\n| Organization | `packages/models/src/organization/types.ts` |\n| User profile | `packages/common/src/organization/types.ts` |\n| Subscription | `packages/models/src/organization/types.ts` |\n| Droid/agent protocol | `packages/common/src/droid/schemas/` |\n| Workspace | `packages/models/src/workspace/` |\n| Feature flags | `packages/common/src/feature-flags/` |\n\n## Related\n\n- [Packages: common](../packages/common.md)\n- [Backend API](../apps/backend.md)\n- [Configuration](./configuration.md)\n",
