            "content": "# Dependencies\n\nThis page lists the key external dependencies across factory-mono: what they do, which apps use them, and version notes. Internal `@factory/*` packages are not listed here — see the [packages section](../packages/) for those.\n\nVersions are sourced from `apps/cli/package.json`, `apps/backend/package.json`, and the root `package.json`.\n\n---\n\n## LLM SDKs\n\n### Anthropic SDK\n\n| | |\n|--|--|\n| Package | `@anthropic-ai/sdk` |\n| Version | `^0.70.0` |\n| Used by | `apps/cli` (direct streaming), `apps/backend` (proxy) |\n| Docs | https://docs.anthropic.com/en/api |\n\nThe CLI uses `@anthropic-ai/sdk` to stream Claude responses directly in exec mode. In interactive mode, LLM calls are proxied through the backend (`PROXY_FUNCTION_URL`) to avoid exposing API keys in the CLI binary. The `packages/droid-core` package contains the streaming core that wraps this SDK.\n\n### OpenAI SDK\n\n| | |\n|--|--|\n| Package | `openai` |\n| Version | `^6.25.0` |\n| Used by | `apps/backend` (proxy) |\n| Docs | https://platform.openai.com/docs/api-reference |\n\nThe backend proxy routes requests to OpenAI-compatible endpoints. `packages/droid-core/src/llms/provider/openai/` contains the streaming adapter.\n\n### Google GenAI SDK\n\n| | |\n|--|--|\n| Package | `@google/genai` |\n| Version | `1.31.0` |\n| Used by | `apps/backend` (proxy for Gemini) |\n| Docs | https://ai.google.dev/api |\n\nUsed for Gemini model support via the backend proxy.\n\n---\n\n## Authentication\n\n### WorkOS\n\n| | |\n|--|--|\n| Package (backend) | `@workos-inc/node` `^7.79.3` |\n| Package (frontend) | `@workos-inc/authkit-react` (via `packages/frontend`) |\n| Used by | `apps/backend`, `apps/desktop`, `apps/web`, CLI auth flow |\n| Docs | https://workos.com/docs |\n\nWorkOS handles SSO, organization management, and user management. The CLI authenticates using WorkOS user management (email/password or SSO). The backend uses `@workos-inc/node` for server-side session validation and webhook processing.\n\nKey env vars: `WORKOS_API_KEY`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_WORKOS_CLIENT_ID`.\n\n---\n\n## Billing\n\n### Orb\n\n| | |\n|--|--|\n| Package | `orb-billing` `^4.33.0` |\n| Used by | `apps/backend` |\n| Docs | https://docs.withorb.com |\n\nOrb manages subscription tiers, seat counts, token usage meters, and invoicing. The backend syncs subscription state from Orb webhooks and stores the result in Firestore (`OrganizationSubscription.orbSubscription`). See `apps/backend/src/services/orb/` for integration code.\n\n---\n\n## Firebase\n\n### Firebase Admin SDK\n\n| | |\n|--|--|\n| Package | `firebase-admin` `^12.0.0` |\n| Used by | `apps/backend`, `packages/models` |\n| Docs | https://firebase.google.com/docs/admin/setup |\n\nServer-side Firestore access, Auth token verification, and Cloud Storage. All Firestore reads/writes on the backend go through this SDK.\n\n### Firebase (client)\n\n| | |\n|--|--|\n| Package | `firebase` `^11.1.0` |\n| Used by | `apps/backend` (some client-mode ops), `packages/frontend` |\n\nUsed for real-time Firestore listeners in the frontend (session list, message stream).\n\n---\n\n## Sandbox / compute\n\n### E2B\n\n| | |\n|--|--|\n| Package | `e2b` `^2.14.0` |\n| Used by | `apps/backend` |\n| Docs | https://e2b.dev/docs |\n\nE2B provides isolated code execution sandboxes (Linux VMs) for remote workspace sessions. The backend creates, manages, and terminates E2B sandboxes. See `apps/backend/src/features/workspace/e2b/` and `apps/backend/src/services/computer/e2b/`.\n\n---\n\n## Feature flags\n\n### Statsig\n\n| | |\n|--|--|\n| Package (backend) | `@statsig/statsig-node-core` `^0.6.1` |\n| Used by | `apps/backend`, `packages/frontend` (via `NEXT_PUBLIC_STATSIG_SDK_KEY`) |\n| Docs | https://docs.statsig.com |\n\nStatsig provides feature gates, dynamic configs, and experiments. The backend evaluates flags server-side; the frontend uses the client SDK for user-level gates. See [Feature flags](../features/feature-flags.md) for usage patterns.\n\n---\n\n## Error monitoring\n\n### Sentry\n\n| | |\n|--|--|\n| Package (backend) | `@sentry/nextjs` `^10.27.0`, `@sentry/node` `^10.27.0` |\n| Package (CLI) | `@sentry/node` (via packages) |\n| Docs | https://docs.sentry.io |\n\nCaptures exceptions and performance traces. The daemon has a TODO to get its own Sentry project (currently shares the backend project). Key env: `NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_CLIENT_ID`.\n\n---\n\n## CLI TUI framework\n\n### Ink\n\n| | |\n|--|--|\n| Package | `ink` `6.7.0` |\n| Used by | `apps/cli` |\n| Docs | https://github.com/vadimdemedes/ink |\n\nInk renders React component trees to the terminal. The CLI's entire TUI — chat view, mission control, keyboard input — is built with Ink. The fixed version `6.7.0` is intentional; upgrading requires validating all terminal interaction tests.\n\n---\n\n## Schema validation\n\n### Zod\n\n| | |\n|--|--|\n| Package | `zod` `^3.25.74` |\n| Used by | `apps/cli`, `apps/backend`, `packages/droid-core`, `packages/common` |\n| Docs | https://zod.dev |\n\nZod is the standard validation library across the monorepo. All JSON-RPC message schemas in `packages/common/src/droid/schemas/` are Zod schemas. Tool input/output schemas in `packages/droid-core` are Zod schemas.\n\n---\n\n## State management\n\n### Redux Toolkit\n\n| | |\n|--|--|\n| Package | `@reduxjs/toolkit` (via `packages/frontend`) |\n| Version | `~2.x` |\n| Used by | `apps/web`, `apps/desktop`, `packages/frontend` |\n| Docs | https://redux-toolkit.js.org |\n\nThe web and desktop frontends use Redux Toolkit with entity adapters for session, message, and workspace state. See `docs/frontend.md` for state management conventions.\n\n---\n\n## Desktop\n\n### Electron (via Forge)\n\n| | |\n|--|--|\n| Package | `electron` + `@electron-forge/*` |\n| Used by | `apps/desktop` |\n| Docs | https://www.electronjs.org/docs |\n\nThe desktop app wraps the web frontend in Electron and manages the daemon process as a child process. Forge handles packaging, code signing, and auto-update distribution.\n\n---\n\n## Observability\n\n### OpenTelemetry\n\n| | |\n|--|--|\n| Packages | `@opentelemetry/api`, `@opentelemetry/sdk-trace-node`, `@opentelemetry/sdk-metrics`, `@opentelemetry/exporter-trace-otlp-http` |\n| Version | `~1.x / 2.x` |\n| Used by | `apps/cli`, `apps/daemon`, `apps/backend` |\n| Docs | https://opentelemetry.io/docs |\n\nControlled by `FACTORY_OTEL_ENABLED`. Traces and metrics are exported to an OTLP collector. The CLI sends spans for agent turns, tool executions, and LLM calls.\n\n---\n\n## MCP (Model Context Protocol)\n\n### MCP SDK\n\n| | |\n|--|--|\n| Package | `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk` `^1.26.0` |\n| Used by | `apps/cli` (as MCP client), `apps/backend` (as MCP server in some contexts) |\n| Docs | https://spec.modelcontextprotocol.io |\n\nThe CLI connects to MCP servers to expose additional tools to the agent. `apps/cli/src/mcp/McpHub.ts` manages connections.\n\n---\n\n## Other notable libraries\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `commander` | `^11.0.0` | CLI argument parsing |\n| `bun-pty` | `^0.4.8` | PTY (pseudo-terminal) for shell tool execution |\n| `ink-testing-library` | `^4.0.0` | Testing Ink components |\n| `lodash-es` | `^4.17.23` | Utility functions (ES module build) |\n| `uuid` | `^9.0.0` | UUID generation |\n| `semver` | `^7.7.2` | Version comparison (auto-update logic) |\n| `ws` | `^8.19.0` | WebSocket client (daemon↔CLI and CLI↔frontend) |\n| `fdir` | `^6.5.0` | Fast directory traversal |\n| `picomatch` | `^4.0.3` | Glob pattern matching |\n| `diff` | `^8.0.3` | Text diff (file edit tool) |\n| `i18next` | `^25.8.13` | Internationalisation framework |\n| `react-i18next` | `^16.5.4` | React bindings for i18next |\n| `next-auth` | `^4.24.11` | Session management for Next.js |\n| `firebase-admin` | `^12.0.0` | Server-side Firestore/Auth |\n\n## Related\n\n- [Configuration](./configuration.md) — environment variable keys for services listed here\n- [Feature flags](../features/feature-flags.md) — Statsig usage\n",
